ississippi-lead|title=Team Marco Announces Mississippi Leadership Team}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n}}\n;[[Republican National Committee]] members (current)\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Bill Armistead]], chair of [[Alabama Republican Party|Alabama GOP]] (2011\u20132015)<ref name=\"marcoal\">{{cite news|url=http://www.al.com/news/index.ssf/2015/10/former_gop_chief_bill_armistea.html |title= Former GOP chief Bill Armistead, State Rep. Will Ainsworth co-chairing Alabama for Marco Rubio committee |newspaper=The Birmingham News |date=October 30, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Jerry Labriola Jr.]]<!-- born 1958or1957 and thus NOT the same as CT state sen [[Jerry Labriola]] born 1931 who is a bluelink -->, chair of [[Republican Party of Connecticut|Connecticut GOP]] (2011\u20132015).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.courant.com/2011-06-29/community/hc-gop-picks-leader-0629-20110628_1_new-chairman-party-committee-jerry-labriola |title=Labriola: Connecticut Republicans Choose Jerry Labriola Jr. As Party Chairman - tribunedigital-thecourant |publisher=Articles.courant.com |date=2011-06-29 |accessdate=2015-07-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Pazniokas |first=Mark |url=http://ctmirror.org/2015/06/23/live-from-the-ct-gop-romano-in-early-lead/ |title=Connecticut GOP picks J.R. Romano, 36, as state chair |publisher=The CT Mirror |date=2015-06-23 |accessdate=2015-07-23}}</ref>\n}}\n;Republican National Committee members (former)\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Alec Poitevint]], former [[Georgia Republican Party|Georgia GOP]] chair<ref>{{cite web|url=http://politics.blog.ajc.com/2016/02/11/marco-rubio-picks-up-another-establishment-georgia-republican-endorsement/|title=Marco Rubio picks up another establishment Georgia Republican endorsement|work=The Atlanta Journal-Constitution|date=February 11, 2016}}</ref>\n* John McCarthy, former [[Kentucky Republican Party|Kentucky GOP]] chair<ref name=\"marcokent\"/>\n* [[Charlie Webster (poli