ael Hebert]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Robert Helm]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Mark Higley]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Robert LaClair]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Marcia Martel]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Corey Parent]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Constance Quimby]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Brian K. Savage]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Butch Shaw]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Harvey Smith (Vermont politician)|Harvey Smith]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Vicki Strong]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Job Tate]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Thomas Terenzini]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Warren Van Wyck]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Kurt Wright]],<ref name=\"marcovt\"/> [[Thomas F. Koch]] (former),<ref name=\"marcovt2\"/> [[Pat McDonald (politician)|Pat McDonald]] (former)<ref name=\"marcovt2\"/>\n* Virginia State Senator: [[Bryce Reeves]]<ref name=\"marcova\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/virginia-politics/rubio-rolls-out-va-campaign-leaders-and-long-list-of-endorsements/2015/12/11/f1df41bc-a035-11e5-a3c5-c77f2cc5a43c_story.html|title=Rubio rolls out Va. campaign leaders and long list of endorsements|work=The Washington Post|date=December 11, 2015}}</ref>\n* Ten Virginia State Delegates: [[Tim Hugo]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2015/09/03/rubio-names-chairman-for-key-swing-state-of-virginia/ |title= Rubio names chairman for key swing state of Virginia |work=The Washington Post |date=September 3, 2015}}</ref> [[Kirk Cox]] (Majority Leader),<ref name=\"marcova\"/> [[Kathy Byron]],<ref name=\"marcova\"/> [[Edward T. Scott]],<ref name=\"marcova\"/> [[Rich Anderson (Virginia politician)|Rich Anderson]],<ref name=\"marcova\"/> [[Jay Leftwich]],<ref name=\"marcova\"/> [[Michael Webert]],<ref name=\"marcova\"/> [[Jason Miyares]] (member-elect),<ref name=\"marcova\"/> [[Terry Kilgore]],<ref name=\"marva\"/> [[John O'Bannon]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://marcorubio.com/news/new-endorsements-rubio-virginia/|title=Team Marco Announces Gr