rma/>\n* [[Larry Ellison]], co-founder and former CEO of [[Oracle Corporation]]<ref name=\"ellison\">{{cite web|url=http://pjmedia.com/tatler/2015/05/13/oracles-larry-ellison-will-host-big-money-fund-raiser-for-rubio/|title=Oracle's Larry Ellison to host fundraiser for Rubio|work=The PJ Tatler|date=2015-05-13}}</ref>\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Fanjul|Jose \"Pepe\" Fanjul]], [[Fanjul Corp|sugar industry]]<ref name=201540721yahooNews />\n* [[Paul Singer (businessman)|Paul Singer]], businessman, investor<ref name=\"singer\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/31/us/politics/paul-singer-influential-billionaire-throws-support-to-marco-rubio-for-president.html |title=Paul Singer, Influential Billionaire, Throws Support to Marco Rubio for President |work=The New York Times |date=October 30, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Frank L. VanderSloot]], entrepreneur, radio network owner, rancher<ref name=\"vandersloot\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2015/11/18/rubio-lands-billionaire-gop-donor-frank-vandersloot/ |title=Rubio lands billionaire GOP donor Frank VanderSloot |work=The Washington Post |date=November 18, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[John Rakolta]], CEO of Walbridge<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2015/11/john-rakolta-supports-marco-rubio-216263 |title=Top Romney ally backs Rubio |publisher=Politico |date=November 30, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Kenneth C. Griffin]], founder and CEO of Citadel<ref name=\"griffin\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2015/12/09/hedge-fund-manager-ken-griffin-backing-marco-rubio-for-president.html|title=Hedge fund manager Ken Griffin backing Marco Rubio for president|publisher=CNBC|date=December 9, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Art Pope]], philanthropist and businessman<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsobserver.com/news/politics-government/politics-columns-blogs/under-the-dome/article49022190.html|title=Republican donor Art Pope backs Marco Rubio for president|work=The News & Observer|date=December 10, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Gary Shapir