{"title_page": "Kathy Ireland", "text_new": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Kathy Ireland\n| image        = Kathy Ireland April 2020.png\n| caption      = Ireland in April 2020\n| birth_name   = Kathleen Marie Ireland\n| birth_place  = [[Glendale, California]], U.S.\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1963|3|20}}\n| occupation   = Model, actress, entrepreneur, businesswoman, author\n| spouse       = {{marriage|Greg Olsen|1988}}\n| net worth    = {{increase}} $420 million (''Forbes'' 2015)<ref name=Forbes420>{{cite news|last1=Robehmed|first1=Natalie|title=How Kathy Ireland Built A $420 Million Fortune|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2015/05/27/how-kathy-ireland-built-a-420-million-fortune/|accessdate=August 31, 2017|work=[[Forbes]]|date=May 27, 2015}}</ref>\n| children     = 3<ref>{{cite web|last=Perry|first=Katie|title=A Beautiful Life|url=http://www.carmelmagazine.com/archive/09ho/kathy-ireland.shtml|work=Carmel Magazine|accessdate=July 9, 2013}}</ref> \n| height       = {{height|ft=5|in=10}}\n| signature    = Kathy Ireland Signature.svg\n| website      = {{URL|www.KathyIreland.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Kathleen Marie Ireland''' (born March 20, 1963) is an American model and actress turned author and entrepreneur.<ref name=MostEntrepreneurial /><ref name=forbes /><ref name=ForbesMoira>{{cite news|last=Forbes|first=Moira|title=Kathy Ireland: Swimsuit Cover Girl Turned $2 Billion Business Model?|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/moiraforbes/2012/02/13/kathy-ireland-swimsuit-covergirl-turned-model-entrepreneur/|accessdate=July 7, 2013|newspaper=Forbes|date=February 13, 2012}}</ref> Ireland was a [[supermodel]] in the 1980s and 1990s, best known for appearing in 13 consecutive ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' swimsuit issues.<ref name=\"ForbesMoira\" /> In 1993, she founded a brand marketing company, kathy ireland Worldwide (kiWW), which has made her one of the wealthiest former models in the world.<ref name=forbes>{{cite news |last=Pomerantz |first=Dorothy |title=How Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Model Kathy Ireland Became a $350 Million Mogul|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/02/08/how-sports-illustrated-swimsuit-model-kathy-ireland-became-a-350-million-mogul/ |work=Forbes |date=February 8, 2012 |accessdate=September 2, 2012}}</ref><ref name=Inc.>{{cite news|last=Welch|first=Liz|title=Ireland graced the cover of Sports Illustrated's|url=http://www.inc.com/magazine/20091201/the-way-i-work-kathy-ireland.html|accessdate=July 7, 2013|newspaper=Inc.|date=December 1, 2009}}</ref><ref name=People>{{cite web|last=Rizzo|first=Monica|title=Kathy Ireland's Shocking Weight Gain (and Loss)|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20269449,00.html|work=People|accessdate=July 6, 2012}}</ref> As a result of her career as a businesswoman, she had made a $420 million personal fortune by 2015.<ref name=Forbes420/> In 2012, $2 billion worth of products bearing her company's brand were sold.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/kathy-ireland-is-a-2-billion-model-preneur |title=Kathy Ireland is a $2 billion 'model-preneur' |last=Moraski |first=Lauren |date=February 24, 2012 |publisher=CBS News |access-date=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe has remained involved with various charities and non-profit organizations dedicated to education, emergency response and training for children, disease research and management, and HIV/AIDS.<ref name=\"About kiWW\"/>\n\n==Early life==\nKathy Ireland was born in [[Glendale, California]], the daughter of John and Barbara Ireland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/48/Kathy-Ireland.html|title=Kathy Ireland Biography (1963-)|publisher=FilmReference.com}}</ref> She graduated from San Marcos High School near Santa Barbara, California.{{Citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\n==Modeling and acting career==\n===Modeling===\nWhen Ireland was sixteen in 1979, she was scouted at her high school by [[Elite Model Management]].<ref name=\"BofM\">{{cite book |last=Segal|first=Gillian Zoe|authorlink=|date=April 14, 2015|title=Getting There: A Book of Mentors |publisher=Abrams Image|url=https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/getting-there-gillian-zoe-segal/1120333492|isbn=9781419715709}}</ref>\n\nShe has appeared on covers for ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'',<ref name=\"eonline\">{{cite news |url=http://www.eonline.com/celebrities/profile/index.jsp?uuid=67c3c82c-7d5a-4e66-8d20-7cfc12989337 |title=Kathy Ireland \u2013 Profile |publisher=E! |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080423113319/http://www.eonline.com/celebrities/profile/index.jsp?uuid=67c3c82c-7d5a-4e66-8d20-7cfc12989337 |archivedate=April 23, 2008 |accessdate=September 2, 2012}}</ref> [[Forbes (magazine)|''Forbes'']],<ref name=\"forbes\"/> and [[Mademoiselle (magazine)|''Mademoiselle'']].\n\nAs a teenager, Ireland reported that a photographer once \"crossed the line\" with her and wanted her to pose topless.  She did not feel comfortable and he did not respect her \"no.\"  He reportedly pushed her and got physical and she \"decked him.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/147116_kathy_ireland_opens_up_for_the_first_time_about_her_uncomfortable_modeling_experience_at_17//|title=Kathy Ireland Opens Up For the First Time About Her Uncomfortable Modeling Experience at 17 |work=Entertainment Tonight| accessdate=June 6, 2014}}</ref>\n\nDuring ''Sports Illustrated'' swimsuit's 50th Anniversary event, Ireland's 1989 cover was awarded \"The Greatest Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Cover Of All Time\" by its publisher.<ref>{{Cite newspaper|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/04/sports-illustrated-swimsuit-50-years-of-beautiful_n_4721807.html|title='Sports Illustrated Swimsuit: 50 Years Of Beautiful' Declares Kathy Ireland 1989 'Greatest Cover Of All Time' |date=February 4, 2014 |journal=Huffington Post | accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Film and television===\nIreland has appeared in a number of television and movie roles. Her first movie, 1988's ''[[Alien from L.A.]]'', was later skewered during the fifth season of ''[[Mystery Science Theater 3000]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/mystery-science-theater-3000/alien-from-l.a./episode/46964/summary.html|title=Mystery Science Theater 3000|date=November 20, 1993|publisher=TV.com|accessdate=July 31, 2008}}</ref>\n\nIreland's other appearances include ''[[Melrose Place]]'', ''[[Boy Meets World]]'', ''[[The Larry Sanders Show]]'', ''[[Muppets Tonight]]'', ''[[Side Out]]'', ''[[Mr. Destiny]]'', ''[[Necessary Roughness (film)|Necessary Roughness]]'', ''[[Mom and Dad Save the World]]'', ''National Lampoon's [[Loaded Weapon 1]]'' (as Miss. Destiny Demeanor), ''[[Once Upon a Christmas (film)|Once Upon a Christmas]]'', and its sequel ''[[Twice Upon a Christmas]]''.\n\nShe also participated in the ninth season of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 9)|Dancing with the Stars]]'', where Ireland and her partner [[Tony Dovolani]] were the third couple eliminated in the second week of competition.\n\nIn 2016, she made an appearance in the sixth episode of the fourth season of ''[[The Profit (TV series)|The Profit]]'', offering advice for the CEO of Murchison-Hume, Max Kater.<ref name=ProfitYT>{{cite episode |title=Murchison-Hume |series=[[The Profit (TV series)|The Profit]] |date=September 27, 2016 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zG2MqRjZqXM |network=[[CNBC]] |season=4 |number=6 |last=Lemonis |first=Marcus (host)|author-link=Marcus Lemonis}}</ref><ref name=Profit>{{cite web|title='The Profit' Q&A: 5 questions with supermodel & entrepreneur Kathy Ireland|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2016/09/28/the-profit-5-questions-with-supermodel-entrepreneur-kathy-ireland.html|date=September 28, 2016|publisher=[[CNBC]]|accessdate=May 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Entrepreneurship==\n===Kathy Ireland Worldwide===\n{{Main|Kathy ireland Worldwide}}\nFounded in 1993 as a brand marketing firm in an exclusive business relationship with [[Kmart]], kathy ireland Worldwide (or kiWW, for short) grew to become one of the world's most valuable global licensors after cutting its ties to the [[department store chain]] in 2003. It has consistently ranked among the top 50 licensors,<ref name=RankingBrands>{{cite web|title=Kathy Ireland Worldwide|website=rankingthebrands.com|url=https://www.rankingthebrands.com/Brand-detail.aspx?brandID=3752}}</ref> most recently standing at No. 26 on License Global's \"Top 150 Global Licensors\" 2019 list with $2.6 billion in retail sales.<ref name=LicenseGlobal>{{cite magazine|author-last=Listanti|author-first=Tony|magazine=License Global|volume=17|number=2|title=Top 150 Global Licensors|url=https://www.licenseglobal.com/sites/default/files/License%20Global%27s%20Top%20150%20Leading%20Licensors%20-%20August%202019.pdf|page=13|date=May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://images2.advanstar.com/PixelMags/license-global/digitaledition/05-2015-top150.html#16|title=Kathy Ireland Worldwide|date=May 2015|accessdate=June 16, 2015|magazine=License Global}}</ref> Since its foundation, kathy ireland Worldwide has expanded into many different categories of products, including Home, Fashion Apparel, Wedding, Fine Jewelry, Baby, Children's Toys and books, Publishing, Pet Care, Crafts and Gifts.<ref name=LicenseGlobal /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.licensemag.com/license-global/top-150-global-licensors |title=Top 150 Global Licensors: Kathy Ireland Worldwide | work=License Global |date=May 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\n====1993-2003: Foundation and the Kmart years====\nIn 1993, Kathy Ireland's name on a line of socks sold 100 million pairs and [[Kmart]] took notice, subsequently giving Ireland her own clothing line including swimwear, active wear, accessories, sweaters and more.<ref name=\"ModelMogul\">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/celebrities/forbes/2004/0705/116.html|title=The Model Mogul |last=Blakeley|first=Kiri|date=May 7, 2004 |work=Forbes|accessdate=August 1, 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604012658/http://www.forbes.com/forbes/2004/0705/116.html|archivedate=June 4, 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"WWD\">{{cite magazine |last=Brown |first=Rachel |date=May 7, 2012 |title=WWD In Person: Kathy Ireland |url=http://www.americanlegend.com/wp-content/uploads/WWD_KathyIreland-2012-05-07.pdf |magazine=[[Women's Wear Daily|WWD]]|access-date=August 31, 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170901025649/http://www.americanlegend.com/wp-content/uploads/WWD_KathyIreland-2012-05-07.pdf |archive-date=September 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nBuoyed by the initial success, Ireland founded kathy ireland Worldwide, at the beginning a brand marketing firm, which she and her related trusts own in its entirety.<ref>{{cite book | title=Contemporary Business |url=https://books.google.com/?id=nR8b-X43b8kC |isbn=9780324359299| edition=12|publisher=Thomson South-Western | first=David L. |last=Kurtz | page=8|year=2007}}</ref> The company concentrated on building its business in home products after 2003, when it cut its exclusive ties to Kmart.<ref name=\"WWD\"/>\n\n====2003-2013: Continuous growth====\n[[File:Kathy Ireland, Warren Buffett and Bill Gates at the 2015 Berkshire Hathaway Shareholders Meeting.jpg|thumb|Warren Buffett, Ireland, and Bill Gates at the 2015 Berkshire Hathaway Shareholders Meeting]] At the advice of [[Warren Buffett]], Ireland's friend and mentor,<ref name=Buffett>{{cite magazine|author-last=Taylor|author-first=Chris|url=http://fortune.com/2016/07/18/kathy-ireland-warren-buffett/|title=Model-Turned-Entrepreneur Kathy Ireland Talks About Getting Advice From Warren Buffett|magazine=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]|date=July 18, 2016|accessdate=May 9, 2018}}</ref> kathy ireland Worldwide soon entered into the home furnishings business. \"Fashion and apparel is consistently changing, but in home it's more consistent,\" Buffett said.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kathy Ireland: Model Mogul|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Nightline/video/ireland-kathy-model-mogul-moms-business-16129447|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=June 8, 2015}}</ref> To this day, Buffett opens each [[Berkshire Hathaway]] shareholder meeting with Ireland and [[Bill Gates]].\n\nAlready in 2004, Ireland's annual take was thought to be around $10 million. ''[[Forbes]]'' described Ireland as a \"prototype for model-turned-mogul\" in a 2006 article about the trend of ''modelpreneurs''.<ref name=\"Slideshow\">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2008/07/17/supermodel-entrepreneur-gisele-ent-sales-cx_kb_0717modelpreneurs_slide_11.html?thisSpeed=20000 |title=Models Turned Moguls |last=Blakeley |first=Kiri |date=December 6, 2006 |work=Forbes |accessdate=August 1, 2008 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130102191156/http://www.forbes.com/2008/07/17/supermodel-entrepreneur-gisele-ent-sales-cx_kb_0717modelpreneurs_slide_11.html?thisSpeed=20000 |archivedate=January 2, 2013 |url-status = dead|df= }}</ref> By 2004, kathy ireland Worldwide was marketing products from 16 manufacturers - including those of Nourison<ref name=\"Nourison partners with Kathy Ireland for new line of rugs\">{{cite web|url=http://www.furnituretoday.com/article/392678-nourison-partners-with-kathy-ireland-for-new-line-of-rugs |title=Nourison partners with Kathy Ireland for new line of rugs|work=[[Furniture Today]]|accessdate=February 4, 2015}}</ref> and Pacific Coast Lighting<ref name=\"MostEntrepreneurial\">{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/lifestyle/2006/02/02/fashion-supermodels-licensing-cz_kb_0203fashion2_ls.html |title=Most Entrepreneurial Supermodels |last=Blakeley |first=Kiri |date=December 6, 2006 |work=Forbes |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080923071255/http://www.forbes.com/lifestyle/2006/02/02/fashion-supermodels-licensing-cz_kb_0203fashion2_ls.html |archivedate=September 23, 2008 |accessdate=September 2, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"ModelMogul\" /> - selling them in over 34,000 retail locations in as many as 14 countries.<ref name=\"MostEntrepreneurial\" />\n\nBetween 2005 and 2012, products bearing Ireland's brand generated $2 billion in annual retail sales and the company became a leader in its industry.<ref name=\"MostEntrepreneurial\" /><ref name=forbes/><ref name=\"About kiWW\">{{cite web|title=About Kathy Ireland at kiWW|url=http://www.kathyireland.com/about-kathy|website=KathyIreland.com|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> In a May 2012 ''[[British Vogue]]'' article, Ireland was called the world's richest model.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2012/05/24/anne-v---anne-vyalitsyna-model-victorias-secret-maroon-5 | work=British Vogue | title=Meet Anne V | accessdate=May 25, 2012 | date=May 24, 2012}}</ref>\n\nAfterwards Ireland started designing wedding dresses and social occasion gowns. She launched her line of wedding gowns by presenting a runway fashion show at the Festival of Brides held in [[Disneyland Resort]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thisfairytalelife.com/festival-of-brides-2012-at-the-disneyland-hotel/ |title=Festival of Brides 2012 at the Disneyland Hotel |website=ThisFairytaleLife.com |date=February 27, 2012 |accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> Sterling/Winters Company is a wholly owned subsidiary of kathy ireland Worldwide, which is the management company for multi-Grammy Award-winning artist [[Janet Jackson]].<ref name=Forbes420/><ref name=SWJJ>{{cite news|title=Inside Janet Jackson's Comeback Gamble and the Hurdle of the 'Aging Diva' Stereotype|work=Billboard|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6641067/inside-janet-jackson-comeback-gamble-aging-divas|first1=Melinda|last1=Newman|first2=Gail|last2=Mitchell|date=July 23, 2015|accessdate=October 6, 2015}}</ref><ref name=SWJJ2>{{cite web|title=The Surprising Link Between Kathy Ireland and Janet Jackson|work=[[Forbes]]|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/02/08/the-surprising-link-between-kathy-ireland-and-janet-jackson/|first=Dorothy|last=Pomerantz|date=February 8, 2012|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[American Legend]] launched a Kathy Ireland collection consisting of 30 styles, which was featured at [[Macy's]] beginning in Fall 2011.<ref name=\"WWD\"/> Ireland is chief designer for Royal Footwear & Accessories (The RFA Group).<ref>{{cite web |last=Alexander |first=Ella |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2013/06/13/kathy-ireland-launches-shoe-line-with-royal-footwear--accessories-group |title=Want to Walk in Supermodel Shoes? |work=British Vogue |date=June 13, 2013}}</ref> She has established a relationship with manufacturer [[Gorham Manufacturing Company|Gorham]] designing dinnerware, glassware and flatware.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hfnmag.com/tabletop-gifts/gorham-catches-wave-new-kathy-ireland-collection |title=Gorham Catches a Wave with New Kathy Ireland Collection |work=HFN Magazine |date=October 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIreland designed a collection of jewelry inspired by [[Elizabeth Taylor]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2012/07/31/kathy-ireland-on-how-to-be-a-supermogul |title=Pretty Successful |work=British Vogue |date=31 July 2012 |accessdate=August 1, 2012}}</ref> She welcomed Taylor's dogs, Gracie and Delilah, into her home, also inspirations for her collection of pet care products.<ref name=Forbes420/> Ireland launched a collection of pet products called Loved Ones, which includes furniture, bowls, collars, toys and luxury bedding. She teamed up with Worldwise Inc., a pet products company based in San Rafael, California, to create the pet collection.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Kathy Ireland launches pet line with Worldwise called Loved Ones - Bizwomen|url = http://www.bizjournals.com/bizwomen/news/2014/03/kathy-ireland-wants-your-pet-to-have-style-and-she.html|website = The Business Journals|accessdate = September 21, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Kathy Ireland Loved Ones... finding solutions for families, especially busy moms|url = http://lovedonesproducts.com|website = lovedonesproducts.com|accessdate = September 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\n====2013-present: Strategic relationships====\nIn 2013, kathy ireland Worldwide entered into a licensing agreement with rug manufacturer Nourison, to create a new collection of affordable area rugs.<ref name=\"Nourison partners with Kathy Ireland for new line of rugs\"/> Since that time, Kathy Ireland Home by Nourison has expanded to include more than 20 distinct rug collections.\n\nIn 2016, in association with Paul Raps New York,<ref name=FoxBusiness>{{cite news |last=Fernandez |first=Henry |date=May 2, 2016 |title= From Model to Mogul: Kathy Ireland\u2019s New Diamond Business|url=http://www.foxbusiness.com/features/2016/05/02/from-model-to-mogul-kathy-ireland-s-new-diamond-business.html |publisher=[[Fox Business Network]] |access-date=August 5, 2017 }}</ref> Yaron Turgeman from Taly Diamonds and Roland Krainz from Krainz Creations,<ref name=FashionNetwork>{{cite news |last=Mantor |first=Cassidy |date=June 2, 2017 |title=  Diamonds by Kathy Ireland debuts|url=http://us.fashionnetwork.com/news/Diamonds-by-Kathy-Ireland-debuts,834388.html |work=Fashion Network |access-date=August 5, 2017}}</ref> Kathy Ireland launched \"Diamonds by Kathy Ireland\", a collection of sixty-five jewelry pieces: engagement rings, wedding bands, patent-pending earrings, bracelets and pendants.<ref name=FashionNetwork /> The collection premiered at the 2017 Luxury and JCK shows in [[Las Vegas]].<ref name=PRNews>{{cite news |date=June 2, 2017 |title=Diamonds by kathy ireland\u00ae to Debut at the 2017 Luxury and JCK Shows |url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/diamonds-by-kathy-ireland-to-debut-at-the-2017-luxury-and-jck-shows-300467733.html |work=PR News Wire |access-date=August 5, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=June 5, 2017 |title=Diamonds by kathy ireland\u00ae Debuted at the 2017 Luxury and JCK shows|url=http://luxexpose.com/diamonds-by-kathy-ireland-debuted-at-the-2017-luxury-and-jck-shows/ |work=Lux Expos\u00e9 |access-date=August 5, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n<div>In January 2017, Ireland teamed with Michael Amini to create a new home-furnishings line.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Amini/Kathy Ireland Home Designs to launch in 2017|url=http://www.furnituretoday.com/article/539508-michael-amini-kathy-ireland-home-designs-launch-2017|author-last=Hodnett|author-first=Cindy W.|accessdate=December 19, 2017|date=January 23, 2017|newspaper=[[Furniture Today]]}}</ref> The line, consisting of  bedroom pieces, occasional tables, couches, chairs and dining sets,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.greensboro.com/news/local_news/model-turned-mogul-kathy-ireland-unveils-furniture-line-in-high/article_06b35ee0-5779-5dc4-8a50-899c37ee4d24.html|title= Model turned mogul: Kathy Ireland unveils furniture line in High Point |author-last=Lopez|author-first=Robert C.|work=Greensboro News & Record|accessdate=December 19, 2017|date=October 16, 2017}}</ref> debuted in October 2017, at the [[High Point Market]] [[trade show]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.highpoint.edu/blog/2017/10/high-point-market-provides-experiential-learning-opportunities-for-hpu-students/|title=High Point Market Provides Experiential Learning Opportunities for HPU Students|accessdate=December 19, 2017|date=October 18, 2017|publisher=[[High Point University]]}}</ref></div>\nAlso in January 2017, [[American Family Insurance]] tapped Kathy Ireland for an ambassador role. To launch their relationship, Ireland was the keynote speaker for their Dream Fearlessly campaign.<ref name=Amfam>{{cite web|url=https://newsroom.amfam.com/american-family-insurance-one-saturday-to-dream-fearlessly-event-held-in-portland-oregon/|title=American Family Insurance and Kathy launch Dream Fearlessly|publisher=[[American Family Insurance]]|date=November 12, 2017|accessdate=November 12, 2017}}</ref> In July 2018, [[Fox Business Network|Fox Business]] reported that Ireland has ventured into the [[shipping container]] business, partnering with [[SG Blocks]], an innovative company renowned for designing and constructing numerous container-based buildings and structures in the United States.<ref name=ShippingContainers>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxbusiness.com/features/kathy-ireland-ventures-into-shipping-container-business|title=Kathy Ireland ventures into shipping container business|first=Elka|last=Worner|publisher=[[Fox Business Network]]|date=July 2, 2018|accessdate=August 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 May 2019, singer and actress [[Vanessa Williams]] signed a management and partnership agreement with Kathy Ireland Worldwide.<ref name=VanessaWilliams>{{cite web|url=https://www.licenseglobal.com/agency-appointments/vanessa-williams-joins-kiww|title=Vanessa Williams Joins kiWW|first=License|last=Global|publisher=[[License Global]]|date=May 8, 2019|accessdate=May 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn late 2019, Padlist launched with Kathy Ireland as the Chief Editor & Brand Strategist alongside Co-Founders Blake Van Leer and Lindsay Van Leer. The platform offers an innovative, tech-savvy approach to rental solutions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wraltechwire.com/2019/11/18/kathy-ireland-signs-on-with-charlotte-startup-real-estate-platform/|title=Kathy Ireland signs on with real estate tech platform |access-date=November 18, 2019|publisher=Tech Wire}}</ref>\n\n===Other projects===\n====Fitness videos====\nSince 1994, Ireland has published several fitness videos that led to her design of athletic apparel and launched her brand licensing of fitness equipment.<ref name=\"Kathy Ireland Biography\">{{cite web|url=http://www.20hotmodels.com/models/KathyIreland/biography.htm |title=Kathy Ireland Biography|accessdate=February 2, 2015}}</ref> Several of these were [[VSDA]] Award-winning, including ''Total Fitness Workout'', ''Core Workout'', ''Absolutely Fit'', ''Advanced Sports Fitness'', ''Reach and Health'' and ''Body Specifics'', which was awarded Fitness Video Of The Year.<ref name=\"Kathy Ireland Biography\" />\n\n====Writing====\nIreland has written numerous books, most of them for children. Her debut effort (with Laura Morton), ''Powerful Inspirations: Eight Lessons that Will Change Your Life'', was published in 2002.<ref>{{Cite book |title=Powerful Inspirations |isbn = 978-0385503075|last1 = Ireland|first1 = Kathy|last2 = Morton|first2 = Laura|year = 2002}}</ref> ''Real Solutions for Busy Moms: Your Guide to Success and Sanity'' and ''Real Solutions: 52 God Inspired Messages from My Heart'' were published in 2009. ''Mona's Favorite Words'', ''What Do Mommies Do?'' and ''An Angel Called Hope'', her first three children's books, were released in November 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000BUTA5U|title=Story Reader 3-Pack with Kathy Ireland: An Angel Called Hope, Mona's Favorite Words and What Do Mommies Do?|via=Amazon.com}}</ref> Since 2013, she has published few more for [[Bendon Publishing International|Bendon]]: ''Where Are the Bears'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-where-are-the-bears-lift-a-flap-storybook|title=Kathy Ireland Where Are The Bears Lift-a-Flap Storybook|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> ''Choo-Choo Colors'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-choo-choo-colors-lift-a-flap-storybook|title=Kathy Ireland Choo Choo Colors Lift-a-Flap Storybook|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> ''Who Wears What'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-who-wears-what-touch-and-feel-board-book|title=Kathy Ireland \"Who Wears What?\" Touch-and-feel Board Book|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> ''P-O-T-T-Y'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-p-o-t-t-y-storybook|title=Kathy Ireland \"P-O-T-T-Y\" Storybook|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> ''Gracie & Delilah: A Tale of Two Precious Pups'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Bendon-Gracie-Delilah-Tale-Precious/dp/B017MHRTA2|title=Bendon Gracie & Delilah: A Tale of Two Precious Pups Book|via=Amazon.com|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> and the three-book collection ''A Big Kid Book Set'', consisting of ''Proud to Potty'', ''Brush Up'' and ''Tubbie Time''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-a-big-kid-book-set|title=Kathy Ireland A Big Kid Book Set|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> \nShe has also written six more \"blocky books\", published by [[Bendon Publishing International|Bendon]] as well: ''Cow'', ''Sheep'', and ''Pig'', from the \"Farm Friends Blocky Books\" series<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Bendon-Publishing-Ireland-Friends-Blocky/dp/B00M3DGB2S/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1498776012&sr=8-1&keywords=kathy+ireland+Farm+Blocky|title=Bendon Publishing Kathy Ireland Farm Friends Blocky Book Box Set|via=Amazon.com|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> and ''Giraffe'', ''Lion'', and ''Zebra'', from the \"Safari Friends Blocky Books\" series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Bendon-Publishing-Ireland-Safari-Friends/dp/B00M3DPA7A/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1498775994&sr=8-1&keywords=kathy+ireland&refinements=p_89%3ABendon+Inc.|title=Bendon Publishing Kathy Ireland Safari Friends Blocky Book Box Set|via=Amazon.com|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> In 2020 Kathy Ireland Released her first novel 'Fashion Jungle' with #1 New York Times Bestselling Author Rachel Van Dyken. The novel is based on true events from her storied career in the modeling industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxbusiness.com/lifestyle/kathy-ireland-fashion-jungle-sports-illustrated|title=nside Kathy Ireland's iconic Sports Illustrated cover, new novel 'Fashion Jungle'|access-date=January 28, 2020|publisher=Fox Business}}</ref>\n\n====Public speaking====\nIreland has delivered numerous keynote speeches at corporate events, industry conventions, expos, entrepreneurial events, social media conferences<ref>{{cite web|title=Social Media Day|publisher=FreshConsulting.com|url=http://www.freshconsulting.com/social-media-day|date=March 3, 2012|accessdate=February 6, 2015}}</ref> and pro-life events.<ref>{{cite web|last=Walker|first=Kristen|url=http://www.lifenews.com/2011/11/15/kathy-ireland-raises-funds-for-abortion-alternatives-group/|title=Kathy Ireland Raises Funds for Abortion Alternatives Group|date=April 15, 2011|publisher=LifeNews|location=Washington, DC|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe spoke at the fourth Youth Assembly at the United Nations Headquarters on August 13, 2007, encouraging young people to engage in activities aimed at ending poverty.<ref name=\"un\">{{cite news|url=http://hfbusiness.com/News/Daily-News-Archive/ArticleId/8651/kathy-ireland-at-the-united-nations|title=Kathy Ireland At The United Nations|work=Home Furnishings Business|date=August 9, 2007|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> Ireland gave a keynote at the [[Googleplex]], the corporate headquarters for [[Google]] on July 12, 2012.{{Citation needed|date=August 2017}} She delivered the keynote at Licensing International Expo 2012 in Las Vegas.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ybltv.com/2012/06/kathy-ireland-worldwide-delivers-keynote-at-licensing-expo-2012/ |title=kathy ireland Worldwide Delivers Keynote at Licensing Expo 2012 |publisher=ybltv.com |date=June 13, 2012}}</ref>\n\nAlong with statesmen [[Barack Obama]] and [[Shimon Peres]], Ireland was the key speaker at the 2012 [[AIPAC]] policy conference in [[Washington, DC]],<ref>{{cite book |last=Collier |first=Marsha |date=November 8, 2012 |title=Social Media Commerce For Dummies |url=https://books.google.com/?id=iR0o5r4_ga4C&dq=aipac+kathy+ireland |location= |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |page= |isbn=9781118461501 |author-link=Marsha Collier}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/2012/03/2012311901213166.html |title=The bully, the beauty and the beast |last=Bishara |first=Marwan |date=March 1, 2012 |publisher=Al Jazeera |access-date= August 5, 2017}}</ref> where she expressed her support for the [[Israeli people]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://jewishjournal.com/mobile_20111212/107431/super-mogul-kathy-ireland-the-new-super-model-for-israel/ |title=Super mogul Kathy Ireland the new super model for Israel |last=Berrin |first=Danielle |date=August 22, 2012 |newspaper=[[The Jewish Journal of Greater Los Angeles|JewishJournal.com]] |access-date= August 5, 2017}}</ref> and warned against the dangers posed by the lack of knowledge about the [[History of Israel|history of the land of Israel]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jns.org/latest-articles/2012/3/5/kathy-ireland-inspired-in-paris-committed-to-israel.html |title=Kathy Ireland: Inspired in Paris, committed to Israel |last=Dovere |first=Maxine |date=March 5, 2012 |publisher=Jewish News Syndicate |access-date= August 5, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805221248/http://www.jns.org/latest-articles/2012/3/5/kathy-ireland-inspired-in-paris-committed-to-israel.html |archive-date=August 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\nKathy Ireland is renowned for her charity work and philanthropic activities, which include [[pro bono]] work for numerous non-profit organizations such as [[March of Dimes]], [[Parent-Teacher Association|PTA]], [[Feed the Children]] and [[City of Hope National Medical Center|City of Hope]].<ref name=GreenTimes>{{cite web|first=Jennifer|last=Schwab|title=Kathy Ireland: Green Times Three|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/jennifer-schwab/kathy-ireland-green-times_b_581853.html|website=[[HuffPost]]|date=October 6, 2010|accessdate=August 23, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn addition, Ireland has lent her estates to charitable organizations such as the [[US Marine Corps]]' [[Toys for Tots]] to generate funds for charity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.midweek.com/content/story/midweek_coverstory/Kathy_Ireland_Toys_For_Tots/P1/|title=Kathy Ireland From Model to Mogul|work=[[MidWeek]]|date=December 15, 2010}}</ref> According to Major Bill Grein of the US Marine Corps, Ireland's company and her book business partner [[Bendon Publishing International]], the world's largest publisher of children's books, donated $10 million to supplement the 2013 annual Toys for Tots gathering and distribution of Christmas gifts for millions of at-risk children and youths.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/a-real-life-santa-role-for-kathy-ireland-234039851.html|title=A Real-Life Santa Role for Kathy Ireland|publisher=2013 Marine Toys For Tots Campaign|date=December 2, 2013| accessdate=August 31, 2017|agency=PR Newswire}}</ref>\n\nOn [[World AIDS Day]] 2017, Ireland donated $100,000 to the Elizabeth Taylor AIDS Foundation (ETAF).<ref>{{cite news|title=Kathy Ireland Contributes $100,000 World AIDS Day Gift to the Elizabeth Taylor AIDS Foundation |url=https://elizabethtayloraidsfoundation.org/kathy-ireland-contributes-100000-world-aids-day-gift/|publisher=Elizabeth Taylor AIDS Foundation|accessdate=December 19, 2017|date=December 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Legacy==\nIn 2015, ''[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]'' named Ireland one of America's 50 most successful self-made women (as measured by their net worth) in its first ever list of the kind.<ref name=Forbes420/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kroll|first1=Luisa|title=Forbes Staff|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/luisakroll/2015/05/27/forbes-first-ever-ranking-of-americas-richest-self-made-women/|accessdate=June 8, 2015|work=Forbes|date=May 27, 2015}}</ref> Lending her name to several thousands of different products,<ref name=\"ABCNews\">{{cite web | url=https://abcnews.go.com/Business/kathy-ireland-model-turned-mogul/story?id=16127302 | last1=Wright | first1=David | last2=Litoff | first2=Alyssa | date=April 12, 2012 | publisher = [[ABC News]] | access-date=November 8, 2018 | title=Kathy Ireland, Model Turned Mogul }}</ref> she has been repeatedly listed as one of the biggest licensors in the world,<ref name=LicenseGlobal /> and compared favourably to [[Martha Stewart]].<ref name=ForbesMoira /><ref name=\"ABCNews\" /> It has been argued that Ireland's branding strategy has paved the way for numerous other \"modelpreneurs,\" serving as the inspiration for the likes of [[Cindy Crawford]] and [[Heidi Klum]].<ref name=\"MostEntrepreneurial\" />\n\nIn addition, Ireland's successful transformation from a cover girl to a multimillion-dollar entrepreneur has been explicitly cited as inspiring by numerous active fashion models. After appearing on the cover of ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' magazine in 2012, in a subsequent ''Today'' show interview, [[Kate Upton]] stated that she would like to follow in the footsteps of other cover girls, specifically [[Heidi Klum]] and Ireland.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pomerantz|first1=Dorothy|title=Kate Upton Wants to Be The Next Kathy Ireland. Can She Do It?|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/02/14/can-kate-upton-become-the-next-kathy-ireland/|accessdate=June 17, 2015|work=Forbes|date=February 14, 2012}}</ref> Three years later, in an interview with [[Matt Lauer]], [[Hannah Jeter]], the 2015 ''Sports Illustrated'' swimsuit cover model, echoed the same sentiments, revealing that she \"would like to model [her] career after someone like Kathy Ireland.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Stump|first1=Scott|title=Hannah Davis on her Sports Illustrated swimsuit cover: It's not that naughty|url=http://www.today.com/popculture/hannah-davis-her-sports-illustrated-swimsuit-cover-its-not-naughty-t1591|accessdate=June 17, 2015|work=Today|date=February 9, 2015}}</ref> Ireland has also been cited as a role model by one of United States' foremost [[plus-size model]]s, [[Ashley Graham (model)|Ashley Graham]],<ref name=ForbesGraham>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/glendatoma/2016/08/30/model-ashley-graham-wants-to-be-the-next-kathy-ireland/|title=Model Ashley Graham Wants To Be The Next Kathy Ireland|first=Glenda|last=Toma|date=August 30, 2016|accessdate=August 24, 2018|work=[[Forbes]]}}</ref> who has singled out her as \"one of her favourite people to follow on Instagram,\" because of her morally conscious online presence and her business savviness.<ref name=PeopleAshleyKathy>{{cite web|title=Ashley Graham Talks Social Media Anxiety and Reveals Her One Instagram No-No|url=https://people.com/style/ashley-graham-instagram-faux-pas-social-media-anxiety/|date=January 12, 2018|last=Pasquini|first=Maria|website=[[People (magazine)|People]]|access-date=November 8, 2018}}</ref> Kathy attended the US Open as a guest of Serena Williams Aug 26, 2019 <ref>{{cite news|last1=Stubblebine|first1=Ray|title=Kathy Ireland attends US Open|url=https://www.wonderwall.com/celebrity/photos/celebrities-2019-us-open-tennis-championships-3020875.gallery?photoId=1061486|accessdate=August 26, 2019|work=Wonderwall|date=August 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Coffey|first1=Wayne|title=Kathy Ireland attends US Open|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/tennis/2019/08/29/serena-williams-beats-caty-mcnally-us-open/2145702001/|accessdate=August 26, 2019|work=USA Today|date=August 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life ==\nIreland married physician Greg Olsen in 1988, and they have three children: Erik, Lily and Chloe.<ref name=\"WWD\"/> She is a devout [[Christians|Christian]] and an [[anti-abortion]] advocate.<ref name=\"christian\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbn.com/700club/features/kathy_ireland-interview.aspx|title=Kathy Ireland: Designing Woman|last=Blim|first=Julie|date=August 20, 2002|publisher=CBN|accessdate=April 21, 2009}}</ref> She has also been outspoken in her support for [[Israel]].\n\nIreland's sister, Cynthia, has a child with [[Down syndrome]]. Ireland wrote an article about her niece and the need for an increase in research.<ref>{{cite interview |last=Ireland |first=Kathy | subject-link= |interviewer=Chet Cooper and Molly Mackin |title=Kathy Ireland |url=https://abilitymagazine.com/Kathy-Ireland.html|work=Ability magazine|location=Los Angeles |date=February 2011|access-date=August 31, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Roberts |first=Julia| url=http://supportforspecialneeds.com/2010/10/19/kathy-ireland-the-tragic-shortfall-in-down-syndrome-research/ |title=Kathy Ireland: The Tragic Shortfall in Down Syndrome Research|date=October 19, 2011|access-date=August 31, 2017 |website=SupportforSpecialNeeds.com}}</ref>\nIn 2009, Ireland appeared on ''[[Larry King Live]]'' to discuss her weight gain and women's health issues. She had gained a pound a year for 25 years and the cumulative effect had become obvious to her in a candid photograph her son had taken.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cnn.com/2009/HEALTH/diet.fitness/05/05/lkl.celebrities.weight/index.html | publisher=CNN | title=Former model: Fret over being fit, not how you look | accessdate=May 7, 2010 | date=May 5, 2009}}</ref>\n\n===Friendship with Elizabeth Taylor===\n[[Elizabeth Taylor]] and Ireland had a close friendship and attended public events together. After Ireland received outspoken criticism for her uneven performance as an on-air host of [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s 2010 pre-Oscar special, Taylor publicly defended Ireland; \"I have never seen anyone epitomize glamour and grace and professionalism like she did.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/elizabeth-taylor-boiling-over-criticism-of-kathy-ireland-at-oscars_article_30043 |title=Elizabeth Taylor 'Boiling' Over Criticism Of Kathy Ireland At Oscars |work=Access Hollywood |date=March 11, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.zimbio.com/photos/Elizabeth+Taylor/Kathy+Ireland/Macy+s+Passport+Gala+Inside/p7FKQJsL6sY |title=Elizabeth Taylor and Kathy Ireland |publisher=[[Zimbio]] |date=September 26, 2008}}.</ref> Ireland publicly credits Taylor as her mentor and for part of her success in life, business, design and philanthropy.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bueno|first= Antoinette|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/132097_Kathy_Ireland_on_Her_Two_Billion_Empire|title=Kathy Ireland on Her Mentor Elizabeth Taylor|work=Entertainment Tonight|date=March 26, 2013|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> Taylor bequeathed her [[Jean Hersholt Humanitarian Award]] to Ireland,<ref name=SWJJ2/> in addition to leaving her a diamond jewelry collection, which Ireland wore at the 2018 [[American Heart Association]]'s \"Go Red for Women\" Dress Show.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cronin|first=Travis|title=NYFW Fall 2018 Front Row Report Day 1: What Cardi B Wore to the Jeremy Scott Show and More|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/stylish/news/ny-fashion-week-fw-2018-day-1-celeb-front-row-looks-gossip/|work=[[Us Weekly|US Magazine]]|date=February 9, 2018|accessdate=March 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Activism and ambassador roles===\nIreland and [[National Football League]] (NFL) [[wide receiver]] [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] are ambassadors for 9-1-1 For Kids, a non-profit organization that specializes in making educational materials to assist emergency dispatchers in teaching children the proper use of 9-1-1 and other general emergency preparedness tips.<ref>{{cite web |first=Ryan |last=Dedmon |url=http://www.9-1-1magazine.com/Dedmon-911-Heroes-Golf-Tourney |title=Dispatchers and Children Honored as 9-1-1 Heroes at Celebrity Golf Tournament |work=9-1-1 Magazine |date=May 29, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130723215857/http://www.9-1-1magazine.com/Dedmon-911-Heroes-Golf-Tourney |archive-date=July 23, 2013}}</ref> In an effort to encourage equality in women's athletics, Ireland has hosted several [[LPGA]] Golf Tournaments, including the [[Kathy Ireland Championship]] from 1999 to 2001<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.lpga.com/content/Chronology90-99.pdf |title=LPGA Tournament Chronology 1990\u20131999 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070920192212/http://www.lpga.com/content/Chronology90-99.pdf |archive-date=September 20, 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lpga.com/content/Chronology2000-2008.pdf |title=LPGA Tournament Chronology 2000\u20132008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110304105055/http://www.lpga.com/content/Chronology2000-2008.pdf |archive-date=March 4, 2011 }}</ref> and the [[Kathy Ireland Greens.com LPGA Classic]] in 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/golfonline/tours/s/breakdown/ireland.html|publisher=ESPN|title=Kathy Ireland Greens.com Classic breakdown}}</ref> On October 15, 2009, Ireland became an international ambassador for the Friends of Sheba Medical Center.<ref>{{cite web|last=Arfa|first=Orit|title=Kathy Ireland Named Sheba Ambassador|url=http://jewishjournal.com/news/los_angeles/community/73684/kathy-ireland-named-sheba-ambassador/|publisher=JewishJournal.com|date=October 28, 2009|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> The following year, she traveled to Israel to film a promotional documentary for the Center; titled ''Holy Land Heroes,'' the film aims to reveal the work done at Sheba with wounded soldiers and terror victims.<ref name=Sheba>{{cite news|first=Ilan|last=Evyatar|title=Born-Again Zionist Supermodel|date=February 12, 2010|accessdate=August 24, 2018|url=https://www.jpost.com/Magazine/Features/Born-again-Zionist-supermodel|work=[[The Jerusalem Post]]}}</ref> In 2019, Ireland was added as the First Woman to the board of NFL Players Association.<ref>{{cite web |title=NFL Players, Inc. Adds Kathy Ireland and Jenny Abramson to Board of Directors |url=https://www.nflpa.com/news/nflplayersinc-adds-kathy-ireland-jenny-abramson-to-board |website=www.nflpa.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kathy Ireland Joins NFL Players Association, Lobbying for CBD |url=https://www.tmz.com/2019/01/31/kathy-ireland-nfl-cbd-marijuana/ |website=TMZ |language=en}}</ref> Ireland also joined the Womens' National Basketball Players Association's (WNBPA) Board of Advocates that same year.<ref>{{cite web |title=WNBA players' union creates board of advocates |url=https://www.espn.com/wnba/story/_/id/27491558? |website=www.ESPN.com}}</ref> Kathy Ireland Joins the National Pediatric Cancer Foundation in 2020 as International Youth Chair.<ref>{{cite web |title=Supermodel-Turned-Supermogul Kathy Ireland Joins National Pediatric Cancer Foundation in Quest to Fast Track Cure |url=https://nationalpcf.org/kathy-ireland-joins-npcf/ |website=www.nationalpcf.org}}</ref>\n\n===Honors and awards===\nOn June 23, 2011, Ireland was honored by the [[Anti-Defamation League]] with the American Heritage Award, presented by the National Home Furnishings Industry.<ref>{{cite web|last=Merritte|first=Tanya|title=ADL to honor Pasquale Natuzzi, Gary Fazio, Kathy Ireland|url=http://www.furnituretoday.com/article/536740-ADL_to_honor_Pasquale_Natuzzi_Gary_Fazio_Kathy_Ireland.php|work=Furniture Today|accessdate=October 7, 2012}}</ref> In 2012, Ireland received the Messenger of Peace Award at the [[Jewish National Fund]] [[Jewish National Fund Tree of Life Award|Tree of Life Gala]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|last=Gr\u0435\u0435nger|first=Nurit|title=Jewish National Fund Still Makes The Difference in Israel|url=http://newsblaze.com/world/israel/jewish-national-fund-still-makes-difference-in-israel_28240/|publisher=NewsBlaze|date=September 10, 2012|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> The same year, Ireland was presented with an honorary Doctorate of Humane Letters by the [[California State University]], which stated that she \"generously uses her power and influence to benefit others, supporting social causes including empowering women, supporting young girls through mentoring, and providing opportunities for girls and women at risk.\"<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://archive.li/20121202102250/http://www.calstate.edu/pa/News/2012/Story/honorary2012.shtml|date=June 20, 2012|archive-date=December 2, 2012|url=http://www.calstate.edu/pa/News/2012/Story/honorary2012.shtml|title=Degrees of Distinction|publisher=California State University|url-status = dead|df=}}</ref> Ireland has been nominated as one of 17 finalists for the first Global Business & Interfaith Peace Award given by the Religious Freedom & Business Foundation (a U.S.-based nonprofit), and the [[United Nations Global Compact]] Business for Peace initiative.<ref>{{cite press release|title=Kathy Ireland Among 17 International CEO Finalists for Religious Freedom & Business Foundation\u2019s Interfaith Peace Awards|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/pr/3014308|agency=Digital Journal|accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> On October 13, 2017, at the \"Meet Kathy Ireland Event\" hosted by Amini, Ireland was presented with [[List of Keys to the City in the United States|the key to the city]] of [[High Point, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eventbrite.com/e/meet-kathy-ireland-at-worlds-largest-furniture-expo-high-point-tickets-38253525324# |title=Meet Kathy Ireland at World's Largest Furniture Expo (High Point) |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=October 13, 2017 |via=[[Eventbrite]] |access-date=October 26, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027024908/https://www.eventbrite.com/e/meet-kathy-ireland-at-worlds-largest-furniture-expo-high-point-tickets-38253525324# |archive-date=October 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1988\n|''[[Alien from L.A.]]''\n|Wanda Saknussemm\n|The film was featured in an episode of [[Mystery Science Theater 3000]]\n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Journey to the Center of the Earth (1989 film)|Journey to the Center of the Earth]]''\n|Wanda Saknussemm\n|\n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Worth Winning]]''\n|Uncredited\n|\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Side Out]]''\n|Marie\n|\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Mr. Destiny]]''\n|Gina\n|\n|-\n|1991\n|''[[Necessary Roughness (film)|Necessary Roughness]]''\n|Lucy Draper\n|\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[Mom and Dad Save the World]]''\n|Semage, Raff's Daughter\n|\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[Danger Island (film)|Danger Island]]''\n|Laura\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Loaded Weapon 1]]''\n|Destiny Demeanor\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Amore!]]''\n|Taylor Christopher\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Perry Mason (TV movies)#A Perry Mason Mystery|A Perry Mason Mystery: The Case of the Wicked Wives]]''\n|Dee Morrison\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Bandit (film series)|Beauty and the Bandit]]''\n|Crystal\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|1995\n|''Backfire!''\n|Jessica Luvintryst\n|\n|-\n|1996\n|''Gridlock''\n|Michele Conner\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|1996\n|''Miami Hustle''\n|Marsha Thomas\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Once Upon a Christmas (film)|Once Upon a Christmas]]''\n|Kristen Claus\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|2001\n|''[[Twice Upon a Christmas]]''\n|Kristen Claus\n|TV Movie\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Episodes\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[Charles in Charge]]''\n|Woman in Line\n|\"Snowed In\"\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Grand (TV series)|Grand]]''\n|Sheila\n|\"Carnegie Hall\"\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[Tales from the Crypt (TV series)|Tales from the Crypt]]''\n|Joyce\n|\"Beauty Rest\"\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Down the Shore]]''\n|Rachel\n|\"Computer Date\"\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[The Larry Sanders Show]]''\n|Herself\n|\"The Breakdown: Part 1\"\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Boy Meets World]]''\n|Alexis\n|\"Model Family\"\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Melrose Place]]''\n|Brittany Maddocks\n|\"Grand Delusions\", \"In-Laws and Outlaws\", \"It's a Bad World After All\" and \"I am Curious, Melrose\"\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[The Watcher (TV series)|The Watcher]]''\n|Pilot\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Deadly Games]]''\n|Amber\n|\"The Camp Counselor: Parts 1 & 2\"\n|-\n|1995\u20131996\n|''[[The Fantastic Four]]''\n|Crystal (Voice)\n|\"Doomsday\", \"The Sentry Sinister\", \"Inhumans Saga: Part 3: Beware the Hidden Land\" and \"Inhumans Saga: Part 2: The Inhumans Among Us\"\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Sabrina, the Teenage Witch]]''\n|Shelley\n|\"Trial by Fury\"\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Suddenly Susan]]''\n|Terri\n|\"Love and Divorce American Style: Part 2\" and \"Love and Divorce American Style: Part 3\"\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Duckman: Private Dick/Family Man|Duckman]]''\n|Susan/Susie\n|\"Vuuck, as in Duck\" and \"Aged Heat 2: Women in Heat\"\n|-\n|1996\u20131997\n|''[[The Incredible Hulk (1996 TV series)|The Incredible Hulk]]''\n|Ogress (Voice)\n|\"Fashion Warriors\", \"Down Memory Lane\" and \"Fantastic Fortitude\"\n|-\n|1998\n|''[[The Lionhearts]]''\n|Survive (Voice)\n|\n|-\n|1998\n|''[[King of the Hill]]''\n|Sylvia\n|\"Peggy's Pageant Fever\"\n|-\n|1999\n|''[[Cosby]]''\n|Kara\n|\"He Who Hesitates is Lucas\"\n|-\n|1999\n|''[[Pensacola: Wings of Gold]]''\n|Sarah\n|\"Tip of the Spear\"\n|-\n|1999\n|''[[Touched by an Angel]]''\n|Karla\n|\"The Last Day of the Rest of Your Life\"\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[Strong Medicine]]''\n|Amber Hutton\n|\"Trauma\"\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[For Your Love]]''\n|Rhonda\n|\"The Helpless Hand\"\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[Totally Spies!]]''\n|Julia Hastings\n|\"A Spy is Born: Part 1\"\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Family Guy]]''\n|Cardboard Cutout\n|\"[[Family Goy]]\"\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q262490|c=category:Kathy Ireland|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|s=no|wikt=no|species=no}}\n*{{official}}\n* {{IMDb name|0001387|Kathy Ireland}}\n* {{Tcmdb name}}\n* {{AllMovie name|34520|Kathy Ireland}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Kathy Ireland navigational boxes\n|list1=\n{{SI Swimsuit Cover Models}}\n{{1980\u20131989 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit}}\n{{1990\u20131999 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit}}\n{{Authority control}}\n}}\n\n{{portalbar|Biography|California|Fashion}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ireland, Kathy}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Glendale, California]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Santa Barbara, California]]\n[[Category:American businesspeople in retailing]]\n[[Category:American children's writers]]\n[[Category:American Christians]]\n[[Category:Female models from California]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:Writers from Glendale, California]]\n[[Category:Writers from Santa Barbara, California]]\n[[Category:Activists from California]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Kathy Ireland\n| image        = Kathy Ireland April 2020.png\n| caption      = Ireland in April 2020\n| birth_name   = Kathleen Marie Ireland\n| birth_place  = [[Glendale, California]], U.S.\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1963|3|20}}\n| occupation   = Model, actress, entrepreneur, businesswoman, author\n| spouse       = {{marriage|Greg Olsen|1988}}\n| net worth    = {{increase}} $420 million (''Forbes'' 2015)<ref name=Forbes420>{{cite news|last1=Robehmed|first1=Natalie|title=How Kathy Ireland Built A $420 Million Fortune|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2015/05/27/how-kathy-ireland-built-a-420-million-fortune/|accessdate=August 31, 2017|work=[[Forbes]]|date=May 27, 2015}}</ref>\n| children     = 3<ref>{{cite web|last=Perry|first=Katie|title=A Beautiful Life|url=http://www.carmelmagazine.com/archive/09ho/kathy-ireland.shtml|work=Carmel Magazine|accessdate=July 9, 2013}}</ref> \n| height       = {{height|ft=5|in=10}}\n| signature    = Kathy Ireland Signature.svg\n| website      = {{URL|www.KathyIreland.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Kathleen Marie Ireland''' (born March 20, 1963) is an American model and actress turned author and entrepreneur.<ref name=MostEntrepreneurial /><ref name=forbes /><ref name=ForbesMoira>{{cite news|last=Forbes|first=Moira|title=Kathy Ireland: Swimsuit Cover Girl Turned $2 Billion Business Model?|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/moiraforbes/2012/02/13/kathy-ireland-swimsuit-covergirl-turned-model-entrepreneur/|accessdate=July 7, 2013|newspaper=Forbes|date=February 13, 2012}}</ref> Ireland was a [[supermodel]] in the 1980s and 1990s, best known for appearing in 13 consecutive ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' swimsuit issues.<ref name=\"ForbesMoira\" /> In 1993, she founded a brand marketing company, kathy ireland Worldwide (kiWW), which has made her one of the wealthiest former models in the world.<ref name=forbes>{{cite news |last=Pomerantz |first=Dorothy |title=How Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Model Kathy Ireland Became a $350 Million Mogul|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/02/08/how-sports-illustrated-swimsuit-model-kathy-ireland-became-a-350-million-mogul/ |work=Forbes |date=February 8, 2012 |accessdate=September 2, 2012}}</ref><ref name=Inc.>{{cite news|last=Welch|first=Liz|title=Ireland graced the cover of Sports Illustrated's|url=http://www.inc.com/magazine/20091201/the-way-i-work-kathy-ireland.html|accessdate=July 7, 2013|newspaper=Inc.|date=December 1, 2009}}</ref><ref name=People>{{cite web|last=Rizzo|first=Monica|title=Kathy Ireland's Shocking Weight Gain (and Loss)|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20269449,00.html|work=People|accessdate=July 6, 2012}}</ref> As a result of her career as a businesswoman, she had made a $420 million personal fortune by 2015.<ref name=Forbes420/> In 2012, $2 billion worth of products bearing her company's brand were sold.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/kathy-ireland-is-a-2-billion-model-preneur |title=Kathy Ireland is a $2 billion 'model-preneur' |last=Moraski |first=Lauren |date=February 24, 2012 |publisher=CBS News |access-date=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe has remained involved with various charities and non-profit organizations dedicated to education, emergency response and training for children, disease research and management, and HIV/AIDS.<ref name=\"About kiWW\"/>\n\n==Early life==\nKathy Ireland was born in [[Glendale, California]], the daughter of John and Barbara Ireland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/48/Kathy-Ireland.html|title=Kathy Ireland Biography (1963-)|publisher=FilmReference.com}}</ref> She graduated from San Marcos High School near Santa Barbara, California.{{Citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\n==Modeling and acting career==\n===Modeling===\nWhen Ireland was sixteen in 1979, she was scouted at her high school by [[Elite Model Management]].<ref name=\"BofM\">{{cite book |last=Segal|first=Gillian Zoe|authorlink=|date=April 14, 2015|title=Getting There: A Book of Mentors |publisher=Abrams Image|url=https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/getting-there-gillian-zoe-segal/1120333492|isbn=9781419715709}}</ref>\n\nShe has appeared on covers for ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'',<ref name=\"eonline\">{{cite news |url=http://www.eonline.com/celebrities/profile/index.jsp?uuid=67c3c82c-7d5a-4e66-8d20-7cfc12989337 |title=Kathy Ireland \u2013 Profile |publisher=E! |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080423113319/http://www.eonline.com/celebrities/profile/index.jsp?uuid=67c3c82c-7d5a-4e66-8d20-7cfc12989337 |archivedate=April 23, 2008 |accessdate=September 2, 2012}}</ref> [[Forbes (magazine)|''Forbes'']],<ref name=\"forbes\"/> and [[Mademoiselle (magazine)|''Mademoiselle'']].\n\nAs a teenager, Ireland reported that a photographer once \"crossed the line\" with her and wanted her to pose topless.  She did not feel comfortable and he did not respect her \"no.\"  He reportedly pushed her and got physical and she \"decked him.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/147116_kathy_ireland_opens_up_for_the_first_time_about_her_uncomfortable_modeling_experience_at_17//|title=Kathy Ireland Opens Up For the First Time About Her Uncomfortable Modeling Experience at 17 |work=Entertainment Tonight| accessdate=June 6, 2014}}</ref>\n\nDuring ''Sports Illustrated'' swimsuit's 50th Anniversary event, Ireland's 1989 cover was awarded \"The Greatest Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Cover Of All Time\" by its publisher.<ref>{{Cite newspaper|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/04/sports-illustrated-swimsuit-50-years-of-beautiful_n_4721807.html|title='Sports Illustrated Swimsuit: 50 Years Of Beautiful' Declares Kathy Ireland 1989 'Greatest Cover Of All Time' |date=February 4, 2014 |journal=Huffington Post | accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Film and television===\nIreland has appeared in a number of television and movie roles. Her first movie, 1988's ''[[Alien from L.A.]]'', was later skewered during the fifth season of ''[[Mystery Science Theater 3000]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/mystery-science-theater-3000/alien-from-l.a./episode/46964/summary.html|title=Mystery Science Theater 3000|date=November 20, 1993|publisher=TV.com|accessdate=July 31, 2008}}</ref>\n\nIreland's other appearances include ''[[Melrose Place]]'', ''[[Boy Meets World]]'', ''[[The Larry Sanders Show]]'', ''[[Muppets Tonight]]'', ''[[Side Out]]'', ''[[Mr. Destiny]]'', ''[[Necessary Roughness (film)|Necessary Roughness]]'', ''[[Mom and Dad Save the World]]'', ''National Lampoon's [[Loaded Weapon 1]]'' (as Miss. Destiny Demeanor), ''[[Once Upon a Christmas (film)|Once Upon a Christmas]]'', and its sequel ''[[Twice Upon a Christmas]]''.\n\nShe also participated in the ninth season of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 9)|Dancing with the Stars]]'', where Ireland and her partner [[Tony Dovolani]] were the third couple eliminated in the second week of competition.\n\nIn 2016, she made an appearance in the sixth episode of the fourth season of ''[[The Profit (TV series)|The Profit]]'', offering advice for the CEO of Murchison-Hume, Max Kater.<ref name=ProfitYT>{{cite episode |title=Murchison-Hume |series=[[The Profit (TV series)|The Profit]] |date=September 27, 2016 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zG2MqRjZqXM |network=[[CNBC]] |season=4 |number=6 |last=Lemonis |first=Marcus (host)|author-link=Marcus Lemonis}}</ref><ref name=Profit>{{cite web|title='The Profit' Q&A: 5 questions with supermodel & entrepreneur Kathy Ireland|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2016/09/28/the-profit-5-questions-with-supermodel-entrepreneur-kathy-ireland.html|date=September 28, 2016|publisher=[[CNBC]]|accessdate=May 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Entrepreneurship==\n===Kathy Ireland Worldwide===\n{{Main|Kathy ireland Worldwide}}\nFounded in 1993 as a brand marketing firm in an exclusive business relationship with [[Kmart]], kathy ireland Worldwide (or kiWW, for short) grew to become one of the world's most valuable global licensors after cutting its ties to the [[department store chain]] in 2003. It has consistently ranked among the top 50 licensors,<ref name=RankingBrands>{{cite web|title=Kathy Ireland Worldwide|website=rankingthebrands.com|url=https://www.rankingthebrands.com/Brand-detail.aspx?brandID=3752}}</ref> most recently standing at No. 26 on License Global's \"Top 150 Global Licensors\" 2019 list with $2.6 billion in retail sales.<ref name=LicenseGlobal>{{cite magazine|author-last=Listanti|author-first=Tony|magazine=License Global|volume=17|number=2|title=Top 150 Global Licensors|url=https://www.licenseglobal.com/sites/default/files/License%20Global%27s%20Top%20150%20Leading%20Licensors%20-%20August%202019.pdf|page=13|date=May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://images2.advanstar.com/PixelMags/license-global/digitaledition/05-2015-top150.html#16|title=Kathy Ireland Worldwide|date=May 2015|accessdate=June 16, 2015|magazine=License Global}}</ref> Since its foundation, kathy ireland Worldwide has expanded into many different categories of products, including Home, Fashion Apparel, Wedding, Fine Jewelry, Baby, Children's Toys and books, Publishing, Pet Care, Crafts and Gifts.<ref name=LicenseGlobal /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.licensemag.com/license-global/top-150-global-licensors |title=Top 150 Global Licensors: Kathy Ireland Worldwide | work=License Global |date=May 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\n====1993-2003: Foundation and the Kmart years====\nIn 1993, Kathy Ireland's name on a line of socks sold 100 million pairs and [[Kmart]] took notice, subsequently giving Ireland her own clothing line including swimwear, active wear, accessories, sweaters and more.<ref name=\"ModelMogul\">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/celebrities/forbes/2004/0705/116.html|title=The Model Mogul |last=Blakeley|first=Kiri|date=May 7, 2004 |work=Forbes|accessdate=August 1, 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604012658/http://www.forbes.com/forbes/2004/0705/116.html|archivedate=June 4, 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"WWD\">{{cite magazine |last=Brown |first=Rachel |date=May 7, 2012 |title=WWD In Person: Kathy Ireland |url=http://www.americanlegend.com/wp-content/uploads/WWD_KathyIreland-2012-05-07.pdf |magazine=[[Women's Wear Daily|WWD]]|access-date=August 31, 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170901025649/http://www.americanlegend.com/wp-content/uploads/WWD_KathyIreland-2012-05-07.pdf |archive-date=September 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nBuoyed by the initial success, Ireland founded kathy ireland Worldwide, at the beginning a brand marketing firm, which she and her related trusts own in its entirety.<ref>{{cite book | title=Contemporary Business |url=https://books.google.com/?id=nR8b-X43b8kC |isbn=9780324359299| edition=12|publisher=Thomson South-Western | first=David L. |last=Kurtz | page=8|year=2007}}</ref> The company concentrated on building its business in home products after 2003, when it cut its exclusive ties to Kmart.<ref name=\"WWD\"/>\n\n====2003-2013: Continuous growth====\n[[File:Kathy Ireland, Warren Buffett and Bill Gates at the 2015 Berkshire Hathaway Shareholders Meeting.jpg|thumb|Warren Buffett, Ireland, and Bill Gates at the 2015 Berkshire Hathaway Shareholders Meeting]] At the advice of [[Warren Buffett]], Ireland's friend and mentor,<ref name=Buffett>{{cite magazine|author-last=Taylor|author-first=Chris|url=http://fortune.com/2016/07/18/kathy-ireland-warren-buffett/|title=Model-Turned-Entrepreneur Kathy Ireland Talks About Getting Advice From Warren Buffett|magazine=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]|date=July 18, 2016|accessdate=May 9, 2018}}</ref> kathy ireland Worldwide soon entered into the home furnishings business. \"Fashion and apparel is consistently changing, but in home it's more consistent,\" Buffett said.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kathy Ireland: Model Mogul|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Nightline/video/ireland-kathy-model-mogul-moms-business-16129447|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=June 8, 2015}}</ref> To this day, Buffett opens each [[Berkshire Hathaway]] shareholder meeting with Ireland and [[Bill Gates]].\n\nAlready in 2004, Ireland's annual take was thought to be around $10 million. ''[[Forbes]]'' described Ireland as a \"prototype for model-turned-mogul\" in a 2006 article about the trend of ''modelpreneurs''.<ref name=\"Slideshow\">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2008/07/17/supermodel-entrepreneur-gisele-ent-sales-cx_kb_0717modelpreneurs_slide_11.html?thisSpeed=20000 |title=Models Turned Moguls |last=Blakeley |first=Kiri |date=December 6, 2006 |work=Forbes |accessdate=August 1, 2008 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130102191156/http://www.forbes.com/2008/07/17/supermodel-entrepreneur-gisele-ent-sales-cx_kb_0717modelpreneurs_slide_11.html?thisSpeed=20000 |archivedate=January 2, 2013 |url-status = dead|df= }}</ref> By 2004, kathy ireland Worldwide was marketing products from 16 manufacturers - including those of Nourison<ref name=\"Nourison partners with Kathy Ireland for new line of rugs\">{{cite web|url=http://www.furnituretoday.com/article/392678-nourison-partners-with-kathy-ireland-for-new-line-of-rugs |title=Nourison partners with Kathy Ireland for new line of rugs|work=[[Furniture Today]]|accessdate=February 4, 2015}}</ref> and Pacific Coast Lighting<ref name=\"MostEntrepreneurial\">{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/lifestyle/2006/02/02/fashion-supermodels-licensing-cz_kb_0203fashion2_ls.html |title=Most Entrepreneurial Supermodels |last=Blakeley |first=Kiri |date=December 6, 2006 |work=Forbes |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080923071255/http://www.forbes.com/lifestyle/2006/02/02/fashion-supermodels-licensing-cz_kb_0203fashion2_ls.html |archivedate=September 23, 2008 |accessdate=September 2, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"ModelMogul\" /> - selling them in over 34,000 retail locations in as many as 14 countries.<ref name=\"MostEntrepreneurial\" />\n\nBetween 2005 and 2012, products bearing Ireland's brand generated $2 billion in annual retail sales and the company became a leader in its industry.<ref name=\"MostEntrepreneurial\" /><ref name=forbes/><ref name=\"About kiWW\">{{cite web|title=About Kathy Ireland at kiWW|url=http://www.kathyireland.com/about-kathy|website=KathyIreland.com|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> In a May 2012 ''[[British Vogue]]'' article, Ireland was called the world's richest model.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2012/05/24/anne-v---anne-vyalitsyna-model-victorias-secret-maroon-5 | work=British Vogue | title=Meet Anne V | accessdate=May 25, 2012 | date=May 24, 2012}}</ref>\n\nAfterwards Ireland started designing wedding dresses and social occasion gowns. She launched her line of wedding gowns by presenting a runway fashion show at the Festival of Brides held in [[Disneyland Resort]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thisfairytalelife.com/festival-of-brides-2012-at-the-disneyland-hotel/ |title=Festival of Brides 2012 at the Disneyland Hotel |website=ThisFairytaleLife.com |date=February 27, 2012 |accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> Sterling/Winters Company is a wholly owned subsidiary of kathy ireland Worldwide, which is the management company for multi-Grammy Award-winning artist [[Janet Jackson]].<ref name=Forbes420/><ref name=SWJJ>{{cite news|title=Inside Janet Jackson's Comeback Gamble and the Hurdle of the 'Aging Diva' Stereotype|work=Billboard|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6641067/inside-janet-jackson-comeback-gamble-aging-divas|first1=Melinda|last1=Newman|first2=Gail|last2=Mitchell|date=July 23, 2015|accessdate=October 6, 2015}}</ref><ref name=SWJJ2>{{cite web|title=The Surprising Link Between Kathy Ireland and Janet Jackson|work=[[Forbes]]|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/02/08/the-surprising-link-between-kathy-ireland-and-janet-jackson/|first=Dorothy|last=Pomerantz|date=February 8, 2012|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[American Legend]] launched a Kathy Ireland collection consisting of 30 styles, which was featured at [[Macy's]] beginning in Fall 2011.<ref name=\"WWD\"/> Ireland is chief designer for Royal Footwear & Accessories (The RFA Group).<ref>{{cite web |last=Alexander |first=Ella |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2013/06/13/kathy-ireland-launches-shoe-line-with-royal-footwear--accessories-group |title=Want to Walk in Supermodel Shoes? |work=British Vogue |date=June 13, 2013}}</ref> She has established a relationship with manufacturer [[Gorham Manufacturing Company|Gorham]] designing dinnerware, glassware and flatware.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hfnmag.com/tabletop-gifts/gorham-catches-wave-new-kathy-ireland-collection |title=Gorham Catches a Wave with New Kathy Ireland Collection |work=HFN Magazine |date=October 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIreland designed a collection of jewelry inspired by [[Elizabeth Taylor]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2012/07/31/kathy-ireland-on-how-to-be-a-supermogul |title=Pretty Successful |work=British Vogue |date=31 July 2012 |accessdate=August 1, 2012}}</ref> She welcomed Taylor's dogs, Gracie and Delilah, into her home, also inspirations for her collection of pet care products.<ref name=Forbes420/> Ireland launched a collection of pet products called Loved Ones, which includes furniture, bowls, collars, toys and luxury bedding. She teamed up with Worldwise Inc., a pet products company based in San Rafael, California, to create the pet collection.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Kathy Ireland launches pet line with Worldwise called Loved Ones - Bizwomen|url = http://www.bizjournals.com/bizwomen/news/2014/03/kathy-ireland-wants-your-pet-to-have-style-and-she.html|website = The Business Journals|accessdate = September 21, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Kathy Ireland Loved Ones... finding solutions for families, especially busy moms|url = http://lovedonesproducts.com|website = lovedonesproducts.com|accessdate = September 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\n====2013-present: Strategic relationships====\nIn 2013, kathy ireland Worldwide entered into a licensing agreement with rug manufacturer Nourison, to create a new collection of affordable area rugs.<ref name=\"Nourison partners with Kathy Ireland for new line of rugs\"/> Since that time, Kathy Ireland Home by Nourison has expanded to include more than 20 distinct rug collections.\n\nIn 2016, in association with Paul Raps New York,<ref name=FoxBusiness>{{cite news |last=Fernandez |first=Henry |date=May 2, 2016 |title= From Model to Mogul: Kathy Ireland\u2019s New Diamond Business|url=http://www.foxbusiness.com/features/2016/05/02/from-model-to-mogul-kathy-ireland-s-new-diamond-business.html |publisher=[[Fox Business Network]] |access-date=August 5, 2017 }}</ref> Yaron Turgeman from Taly Diamonds and Roland Krainz from Krainz Creations,<ref name=FashionNetwork>{{cite news |last=Mantor |first=Cassidy |date=June 2, 2017 |title=  Diamonds by Kathy Ireland debuts|url=http://us.fashionnetwork.com/news/Diamonds-by-Kathy-Ireland-debuts,834388.html |work=Fashion Network |access-date=August 5, 2017}}</ref> Kathy Ireland launched \"Diamonds by Kathy Ireland\", a collection of sixty-five jewelry pieces: engagement rings, wedding bands, patent-pending earrings, bracelets and pendants.<ref name=FashionNetwork /> The collection premiered at the 2017 Luxury and JCK shows in [[Las Vegas]].<ref name=PRNews>{{cite news |date=June 2, 2017 |title=Diamonds by kathy ireland\u00ae to Debut at the 2017 Luxury and JCK Shows |url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/diamonds-by-kathy-ireland-to-debut-at-the-2017-luxury-and-jck-shows-300467733.html |work=PR News Wire |access-date=August 5, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=June 5, 2017 |title=Diamonds by kathy ireland\u00ae Debuted at the 2017 Luxury and JCK shows|url=http://luxexpose.com/diamonds-by-kathy-ireland-debuted-at-the-2017-luxury-and-jck-shows/ |work=Lux Expos\u00e9 |access-date=August 5, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n<div>In January 2017, Ireland teamed with Michael Amini to create a new home-furnishings line.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Amini/Kathy Ireland Home Designs to launch in 2017|url=http://www.furnituretoday.com/article/539508-michael-amini-kathy-ireland-home-designs-launch-2017|author-last=Hodnett|author-first=Cindy W.|accessdate=December 19, 2017|date=January 23, 2017|newspaper=[[Furniture Today]]}}</ref> The line, consisting of  bedroom pieces, occasional tables, couches, chairs and dining sets,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.greensboro.com/news/local_news/model-turned-mogul-kathy-ireland-unveils-furniture-line-in-high/article_06b35ee0-5779-5dc4-8a50-899c37ee4d24.html|title= Model turned mogul: Kathy Ireland unveils furniture line in High Point |author-last=Lopez|author-first=Robert C.|work=Greensboro News & Record|accessdate=December 19, 2017|date=October 16, 2017}}</ref> debuted in October 2017, at the [[High Point Market]] [[trade show]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.highpoint.edu/blog/2017/10/high-point-market-provides-experiential-learning-opportunities-for-hpu-students/|title=High Point Market Provides Experiential Learning Opportunities for HPU Students|accessdate=December 19, 2017|date=October 18, 2017|publisher=[[High Point University]]}}</ref></div>\nAlso in January 2017, [[American Family Insurance]] tapped Kathy Ireland for an ambassador role. To launch their relationship, Ireland was the keynote speaker for their Dream Fearlessly campaign.<ref name=Amfam>{{cite web|url=https://newsroom.amfam.com/american-family-insurance-one-saturday-to-dream-fearlessly-event-held-in-portland-oregon/|title=American Family Insurance and Kathy launch Dream Fearlessly|publisher=[[American Family Insurance]]|date=November 12, 2017|accessdate=November 12, 2017}}</ref> In July 2018, [[Fox Business Network|Fox Business]] reported that Ireland has ventured into the [[shipping container]] business, partnering with [[SG Blocks]], an innovative company renowned for designing and constructing numerous container-based buildings and structures in the United States.<ref name=ShippingContainers>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxbusiness.com/features/kathy-ireland-ventures-into-shipping-container-business|title=Kathy Ireland ventures into shipping container business|first=Elka|last=Worner|publisher=[[Fox Business Network]]|date=July 2, 2018|accessdate=August 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 May 2019, singer and actress [[Vanessa Williams]] signed a management and partnership agreement with Kathy Ireland Worldwide.<ref name=VanessaWilliams>{{cite web|url=https://www.licenseglobal.com/agency-appointments/vanessa-williams-joins-kiww|title=Vanessa Williams Joins kiWW|first=License|last=Global|publisher=[[License Global]]|date=May 8, 2019|accessdate=May 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn late 2019, Padlist launched with Kathy Ireland as the Chief Editor & Brand Strategist alongside Co-Founders Blake Van Leer and Lindsay Van Leer. The platform offers an innovative, tech-savvy approach to rental solutions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wraltechwire.com/2019/11/18/kathy-ireland-signs-on-with-charlotte-startup-real-estate-platform/|title=Kathy Ireland signs on with real estate tech platform |access-date=November 18, 2019|publisher=Tech Wire}}</ref>\n\n===Other projects===\n====Fitness videos====\nSince 1994, Ireland has published several fitness videos that led to her design of athletic apparel and launched her brand licensing of fitness equipment.<ref name=\"Kathy Ireland Biography\">{{cite web|url=http://www.20hotmodels.com/models/KathyIreland/biography.htm |title=Kathy Ireland Biography|accessdate=February 2, 2015}}</ref> Several of these were [[VSDA]] Award-winning, including ''Total Fitness Workout'', ''Core Workout'', ''Absolutely Fit'', ''Advanced Sports Fitness'', ''Reach and Health'' and ''Body Specifics'', which was awarded Fitness Video Of The Year.<ref name=\"Kathy Ireland Biography\" />\n\n====Writing====\nIreland has written numerous books, most of them for children. Her debut effort (with Laura Morton), ''Powerful Inspirations: Eight Lessons that Will Change Your Life'', was published in 2002.<ref>{{Cite book |title=Powerful Inspirations |isbn = 978-0385503075|last1 = Ireland|first1 = Kathy|last2 = Morton|first2 = Laura|year = 2002}}</ref> ''Real Solutions for Busy Moms: Your Guide to Success and Sanity'' and ''Real Solutions: 52 God Inspired Messages from My Heart'' were published in 2009. ''Mona's Favorite Words'', ''What Do Mommies Do?'' and ''An Angel Called Hope'', her first three children's books, were released in November 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000BUTA5U|title=Story Reader 3-Pack with Kathy Ireland: An Angel Called Hope, Mona's Favorite Words and What Do Mommies Do?|via=Amazon.com}}</ref> Since 2013, she has published few more for [[Bendon Publishing International|Bendon]]: ''Where Are the Bears'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-where-are-the-bears-lift-a-flap-storybook|title=Kathy Ireland Where Are The Bears Lift-a-Flap Storybook|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> ''Choo-Choo Colors'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-choo-choo-colors-lift-a-flap-storybook|title=Kathy Ireland Choo Choo Colors Lift-a-Flap Storybook|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> ''Who Wears What'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-who-wears-what-touch-and-feel-board-book|title=Kathy Ireland \"Who Wears What?\" Touch-and-feel Board Book|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> ''P-O-T-T-Y'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-p-o-t-t-y-storybook|title=Kathy Ireland \"P-O-T-T-Y\" Storybook|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> ''Gracie & Delilah: A Tale of Two Precious Pups'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Bendon-Gracie-Delilah-Tale-Precious/dp/B017MHRTA2|title=Bendon Gracie & Delilah: A Tale of Two Precious Pups Book|via=Amazon.com|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> and the three-book collection ''A Big Kid Book Set'', consisting of ''Proud to Potty'', ''Brush Up'' and ''Tubbie Time''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bendonpub.com/products/kathy-ireland-a-big-kid-book-set|title=Kathy Ireland A Big Kid Book Set|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> \nShe has also written six more \"blocky books\", published by [[Bendon Publishing International|Bendon]] as well: ''Cow'', ''Sheep'', and ''Pig'', from the \"Farm Friends Blocky Books\" series<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Bendon-Publishing-Ireland-Friends-Blocky/dp/B00M3DGB2S/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1498776012&sr=8-1&keywords=kathy+ireland+Farm+Blocky|title=Bendon Publishing Kathy Ireland Farm Friends Blocky Book Box Set|via=Amazon.com|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> and ''Giraffe'', ''Lion'', and ''Zebra'', from the \"Safari Friends Blocky Books\" series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Bendon-Publishing-Ireland-Safari-Friends/dp/B00M3DPA7A/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1498775994&sr=8-1&keywords=kathy+ireland&refinements=p_89%3ABendon+Inc.|title=Bendon Publishing Kathy Ireland Safari Friends Blocky Book Box Set|via=Amazon.com|access-date=June 30, 2017|publisher=Bendon, Inc.}}</ref> In 2020 Kathy Ireland Released her first novel 'Fashion Jungle' with #1 New York Times Bestselling Author Rachel Van Dyken. The novel is based on true events from her storied career in the modeling industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxbusiness.com/lifestyle/kathy-ireland-fashion-jungle-sports-illustrated|title=nside Kathy Ireland's iconic Sports Illustrated cover, new novel 'Fashion Jungle'|access-date=January 28, 2020|publisher=Fox Business}}</ref>\n\n====Public speaking====\nIreland has delivered numerous keynote speeches at corporate events, industry conventions, expos, entrepreneurial events, social media conferences<ref>{{cite web|title=Social Media Day|publisher=FreshConsulting.com|url=http://www.freshconsulting.com/social-media-day|date=March 3, 2012|accessdate=February 6, 2015}}</ref> and pro-life events.<ref>{{cite web|last=Walker|first=Kristen|url=http://www.lifenews.com/2011/11/15/kathy-ireland-raises-funds-for-abortion-alternatives-group/|title=Kathy Ireland Raises Funds for Abortion Alternatives Group|date=April 15, 2011|publisher=LifeNews|location=Washington, DC|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe spoke at the fourth Youth Assembly at the United Nations Headquarters on August 13, 2007, encouraging young people to engage in activities aimed at ending poverty.<ref name=\"un\">{{cite news|url=http://hfbusiness.com/News/Daily-News-Archive/ArticleId/8651/kathy-ireland-at-the-united-nations|title=Kathy Ireland At The United Nations|work=Home Furnishings Business|date=August 9, 2007|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> Ireland gave a keynote at the [[Googleplex]], the corporate headquarters for [[Google]] on July 12, 2012.{{Citation needed|date=August 2017}} She delivered the keynote at Licensing International Expo 2012 in Las Vegas.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ybltv.com/2012/06/kathy-ireland-worldwide-delivers-keynote-at-licensing-expo-2012/ |title=kathy ireland Worldwide Delivers Keynote at Licensing Expo 2012 |publisher=ybltv.com |date=June 13, 2012}}</ref>\n\nAlong with statesmen [[Barack Obama]] and [[Shimon Peres]], Ireland was the key speaker at the 2012 [[AIPAC]] policy conference in [[Washington, DC]],<ref>{{cite book |last=Collier |first=Marsha |date=November 8, 2012 |title=Social Media Commerce For Dummies |url=https://books.google.com/?id=iR0o5r4_ga4C&dq=aipac+kathy+ireland |location= |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |page= |isbn=9781118461501 |author-link=Marsha Collier}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/2012/03/2012311901213166.html |title=The bully, the beauty and the beast |last=Bishara |first=Marwan |date=March 1, 2012 |publisher=Al Jazeera |access-date= August 5, 2017}}</ref> where she expressed her support for the [[Israeli people]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://jewishjournal.com/mobile_20111212/107431/super-mogul-kathy-ireland-the-new-super-model-for-israel/ |title=Super mogul Kathy Ireland the new super model for Israel |last=Berrin |first=Danielle |date=August 22, 2012 |newspaper=[[The Jewish Journal of Greater Los Angeles|JewishJournal.com]] |access-date= August 5, 2017}}</ref> and warned against the dangers posed by the lack of knowledge about the [[History of Israel|history of the land of Israel]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jns.org/latest-articles/2012/3/5/kathy-ireland-inspired-in-paris-committed-to-israel.html |title=Kathy Ireland: Inspired in Paris, committed to Israel |last=Dovere |first=Maxine |date=March 5, 2012 |publisher=Jewish News Syndicate |access-date= August 5, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805221248/http://www.jns.org/latest-articles/2012/3/5/kathy-ireland-inspired-in-paris-committed-to-israel.html |archive-date=August 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\nKathy Ireland is renowned for her charity work and philanthropic activities, which include [[pro bono]] work for numerous non-profit organizations such as [[March of Dimes]], [[Parent-Teacher Association|PTA]], [[Feed the Children]] and [[City of Hope National Medical Center|City of Hope]].<ref name=GreenTimes>{{cite web|first=Jennifer|last=Schwab|title=Kathy Ireland: Green Times Three|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/jennifer-schwab/kathy-ireland-green-times_b_581853.html|website=[[HuffPost]]|date=October 6, 2010|accessdate=August 23, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn addition, Ireland has lent her estates to charitable organizations such as the [[US Marine Corps]]' [[Toys for Tots]] to generate funds for charity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.midweek.com/content/story/midweek_coverstory/Kathy_Ireland_Toys_For_Tots/P1/|title=Kathy Ireland From Model to Mogul|work=[[MidWeek]]|date=December 15, 2010}}</ref> According to Major Bill Grein of the US Marine Corps, Ireland's company and her book business partner [[Bendon Publishing International]], the world's largest publisher of children's books, donated $10 million to supplement the 2013 annual Toys for Tots gathering and distribution of Christmas gifts for millions of at-risk children and youths.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/a-real-life-santa-role-for-kathy-ireland-234039851.html|title=A Real-Life Santa Role for Kathy Ireland|publisher=2013 Marine Toys For Tots Campaign|date=December 2, 2013| accessdate=August 31, 2017|agency=PR Newswire}}</ref>\n\nOn [[World AIDS Day]] 2017, Ireland donated $100,000 to the Elizabeth Taylor AIDS Foundation (ETAF).<ref>{{cite news|title=Kathy Ireland Contributes $100,000 World AIDS Day Gift to the Elizabeth Taylor AIDS Foundation |url=https://elizabethtayloraidsfoundation.org/kathy-ireland-contributes-100000-world-aids-day-gift/|publisher=Elizabeth Taylor AIDS Foundation|accessdate=December 19, 2017|date=December 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Legacy==\nIn 2015, ''[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]'' named Ireland one of America's 50 most successful self-made women (as measured by their net worth) in its first ever list of the kind.<ref name=Forbes420/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kroll|first1=Luisa|title=Forbes Staff|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/luisakroll/2015/05/27/forbes-first-ever-ranking-of-americas-richest-self-made-women/|accessdate=June 8, 2015|work=Forbes|date=May 27, 2015}}</ref> Lending her name to several thousands of different products,<ref name=\"ABCNews\">{{cite web | url=https://abcnews.go.com/Business/kathy-ireland-model-turned-mogul/story?id=16127302 | last1=Wright | first1=David | last2=Litoff | first2=Alyssa | date=April 12, 2012 | publisher = [[ABC News]] | access-date=November 8, 2018 | title=Kathy Ireland, Model Turned Mogul }}</ref> she has been repeatedly listed as one of the biggest licensors in the world,<ref name=LicenseGlobal /> and compared favourably to [[Martha Stewart]].<ref name=ForbesMoira /><ref name=\"ABCNews\" /> It has been argued that Ireland's branding strategy has paved the way for numerous other \"modelpreneurs,\" serving as the inspiration for the likes of [[Cindy Crawford]] and [[Heidi Klum]].<ref name=\"MostEntrepreneurial\" />\n\nIn addition, Ireland's successful transformation from a cover girl to a multimillion-dollar entrepreneur has been explicitly cited as inspiring by numerous active fashion models. After appearing on the cover of ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' magazine in 2012, in a subsequent ''Today'' show interview, [[Kate Upton]] stated that she would like to follow in the footsteps of other cover girls, specifically [[Heidi Klum]] and Ireland.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pomerantz|first1=Dorothy|title=Kate Upton Wants to Be The Next Kathy Ireland. Can She Do It?|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/02/14/can-kate-upton-become-the-next-kathy-ireland/|accessdate=June 17, 2015|work=Forbes|date=February 14, 2012}}</ref> Three years later, in an interview with [[Matt Lauer]], [[Hannah Jeter]], the 2015 ''Sports Illustrated'' swimsuit cover model, echoed the same sentiments, revealing that she \"would like to model [her] career after someone like Kathy Ireland.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Stump|first1=Scott|title=Hannah Davis on her Sports Illustrated swimsuit cover: It's not that naughty|url=http://www.today.com/popculture/hannah-davis-her-sports-illustrated-swimsuit-cover-its-not-naughty-t1591|accessdate=June 17, 2015|work=Today|date=February 9, 2015}}</ref> Ireland has also been cited as a role model by one of United States' foremost [[plus-size model]]s, [[Ashley Graham (model)|Ashley Graham]],<ref name=ForbesGraham>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/glendatoma/2016/08/30/model-ashley-graham-wants-to-be-the-next-kathy-ireland/|title=Model Ashley Graham Wants To Be The Next Kathy Ireland|first=Glenda|last=Toma|date=August 30, 2016|accessdate=August 24, 2018|work=[[Forbes]]}}</ref> who has singled out her as \"one of her favourite people to follow on Instagram,\" because of her morally conscious online presence and her business savviness.<ref name=PeopleAshleyKathy>{{cite web|title=Ashley Graham Talks Social Media Anxiety and Reveals Her One Instagram No-No|url=https://people.com/style/ashley-graham-instagram-faux-pas-social-media-anxiety/|date=January 12, 2018|last=Pasquini|first=Maria|website=[[People (magazine)|People]]|access-date=November 8, 2018}}</ref> Kathy attended the US Open as a guest of Serena Williams Aug 26, 2019 <ref>{{cite news|last1=Stubblebine|first1=Ray|title=Kathy Ireland attends US Open|url=https://www.wonderwall.com/celebrity/photos/celebrities-2019-us-open-tennis-championships-3020875.gallery?photoId=1061486|accessdate=August 26, 2019|work=Wonderwall|date=August 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Coffey|first1=Wayne|title=Kathy Ireland attends US Open|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/tennis/2019/08/29/serena-williams-beats-caty-mcnally-us-open/2145702001/|accessdate=August 26, 2019|work=USA Today|date=August 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life ==\nIreland married physician Greg Olsen in 1988, and they have three children: Erik, Lily and Chloe.<ref name=\"WWD\"/> She is a devout [[Christians|Christian]] and an [[anti-abortion]] advocate.<ref name=\"christian\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbn.com/700club/features/kathy_ireland-interview.aspx|title=Kathy Ireland: Designing Woman|last=Blim|first=Julie|date=August 20, 2002|publisher=CBN|accessdate=April 21, 2009}}</ref> She has also been outspoken in her support for [[Israel]].\n\nIreland's sister, Cynthia, has a child with [[Down syndrome]]. Ireland wrote an article about her niece and the need for an increase in research.<ref>{{cite interview |last=Ireland |first=Kathy | subject-link= |interviewer=Chet Cooper and Molly Mackin |title=Kathy Ireland |url=https://abilitymagazine.com/Kathy-Ireland.html|work=Ability magazine|location=Los Angeles |date=February 2011|access-date=August 31, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Roberts |first=Julia| url=http://supportforspecialneeds.com/2010/10/19/kathy-ireland-the-tragic-shortfall-in-down-syndrome-research/ |title=Kathy Ireland: The Tragic Shortfall in Down Syndrome Research|date=October 19, 2011|access-date=August 31, 2017 |website=SupportforSpecialNeeds.com}}</ref>\nIn 2009, Ireland appeared on ''[[Larry King Live]]'' to discuss her weight gain and women's health issues. She had gained a pound a year for 25 years and the cumulative effect had become obvious to her in a candid photograph her son had taken.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cnn.com/2009/HEALTH/diet.fitness/05/05/lkl.celebrities.weight/index.html | publisher=CNN | title=Former model: Fret over being fit, not how you look | accessdate=May 7, 2010 | date=May 5, 2009}}</ref>\n\n===Friendship with Elizabeth Taylor===\n[[Elizabeth Taylor]] and Ireland had a close friendship and attended public events together. After Ireland received outspoken criticism for her uneven performance as an on-air host of [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s 2010 pre-Oscar special, Taylor publicly defended Ireland; \"I have never seen anyone epitomize glamour and grace and professionalism like she did.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/elizabeth-taylor-boiling-over-criticism-of-kathy-ireland-at-oscars_article_30043 |title=Elizabeth Taylor 'Boiling' Over Criticism Of Kathy Ireland At Oscars |work=Access Hollywood |date=March 11, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.zimbio.com/photos/Elizabeth+Taylor/Kathy+Ireland/Macy+s+Passport+Gala+Inside/p7FKQJsL6sY |title=Elizabeth Taylor and Kathy Ireland |publisher=[[Zimbio]] |date=September 26, 2008}}.</ref> Ireland publicly credits Taylor as her mentor and for part of her success in life, business, design and philanthropy.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bueno|first= Antoinette|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/132097_Kathy_Ireland_on_Her_Two_Billion_Empire|title=Kathy Ireland on Her Mentor Elizabeth Taylor|work=Entertainment Tonight|date=March 26, 2013|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> Taylor bequeathed her [[Jean Hersholt Humanitarian Award]] to Ireland,<ref name=SWJJ2/> in addition to leaving her a diamond jewelry collection, which Ireland wore at the 2018 [[American Heart Association]]'s \"Go Red for Women\" Dress Show.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cronin|first=Travis|title=NYFW Fall 2018 Front Row Report Day 1: What Cardi B Wore to the Jeremy Scott Show and More|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/stylish/news/ny-fashion-week-fw-2018-day-1-celeb-front-row-looks-gossip/|work=[[Us Weekly|US Magazine]]|date=February 9, 2018|accessdate=March 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Activism and ambassador roles===\nIreland and [[National Football League]] (NFL) [[wide receiver]] [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] are ambassadors for 9-1-1 For Kids, a non-profit organization that specializes in making educational materials to assist emergency dispatchers in teaching children the proper use of 9-1-1 and other general emergency preparedness tips.<ref>{{cite web |first=Ryan |last=Dedmon |url=http://www.9-1-1magazine.com/Dedmon-911-Heroes-Golf-Tourney |title=Dispatchers and Children Honored as 9-1-1 Heroes at Celebrity Golf Tournament |work=9-1-1 Magazine |date=May 29, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130723215857/http://www.9-1-1magazine.com/Dedmon-911-Heroes-Golf-Tourney |archive-date=July 23, 2013}}</ref> In an effort to encourage equality in women's athletics, Ireland has hosted several [[LPGA]] Golf Tournaments, including the [[Kathy Ireland Championship]] from 1999 to 2001<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.lpga.com/content/Chronology90-99.pdf |title=LPGA Tournament Chronology 1990\u20131999 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070920192212/http://www.lpga.com/content/Chronology90-99.pdf |archive-date=September 20, 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lpga.com/content/Chronology2000-2008.pdf |title=LPGA Tournament Chronology 2000\u20132008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110304105055/http://www.lpga.com/content/Chronology2000-2008.pdf |archive-date=March 4, 2011 }}</ref> and the [[Kathy Ireland Greens.com LPGA Classic]] in 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/golfonline/tours/s/breakdown/ireland.html|publisher=ESPN|title=Kathy Ireland Greens.com Classic breakdown}}</ref> On October 15, 2009, Ireland became an international ambassador for the Friends of Sheba Medical Center.<ref>{{cite web|last=Arfa|first=Orit|title=Kathy Ireland Named Sheba Ambassador|url=http://jewishjournal.com/news/los_angeles/community/73684/kathy-ireland-named-sheba-ambassador/|publisher=JewishJournal.com|date=October 28, 2009|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> The following year, she traveled to Israel to film a promotional documentary for the Center; titled ''Holy Land Heroes,'' the film aims to reveal the work done at Sheba with wounded soldiers and terror victims.<ref name=Sheba>{{cite news|first=Ilan|last=Evyatar|title=Born-Again Zionist Supermodel|date=February 12, 2010|accessdate=August 24, 2018|url=https://www.jpost.com/Magazine/Features/Born-again-Zionist-supermodel|work=[[The Jerusalem Post]]}}</ref> In 2019, Ireland was added as the First Woman to the board of NFL Players Association.<ref>{{cite web |title=NFL Players, Inc. Adds Kathy Ireland and Jenny Abramson to Board of Directors |url=https://www.nflpa.com/news/nflplayersinc-adds-kathy-ireland-jenny-abramson-to-board |website=www.nflpa.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kathy Ireland Joins NFL Players Association, Lobbying for CBD |url=https://www.tmz.com/2019/01/31/kathy-ireland-nfl-cbd-marijuana/ |website=TMZ |language=en}}</ref> Ireland also joined the Womens' National Basketball Players Association's (WNBPA) Board of Advocates that same year.<ref>{{cite web |title=WNBA players' union creates board of advocates |url=https://www.espn.com/wnba/story/_/id/27491558? |website=www.ESPN.com}}</ref> Kathy Ireland Joins the National Pediatric Cancer Foundation in 2020 as International Youth Chair.<ref>{{cite web |title=Supermodel-Turned-Supermogul Kathy Ireland Joins National Pediatric Cancer Foundation in Quest to Fast Track Cure |url=https://nationalpcf.org/kathy-ireland-joins-npcf/ |website=www.nationalpcf.org}}</ref>\n\n===Honors and awards===\nOn June 23, 2011, Ireland was honored by the [[Anti-Defamation League]] with the American Heritage Award, presented by the National Home Furnishings Industry.<ref>{{cite web|last=Merritte|first=Tanya|title=ADL to honor Pasquale Natuzzi, Gary Fazio, Kathy Ireland|url=http://www.furnituretoday.com/article/536740-ADL_to_honor_Pasquale_Natuzzi_Gary_Fazio_Kathy_Ireland.php|work=Furniture Today|accessdate=October 7, 2012}}</ref> In 2012, Ireland received the Messenger of Peace Award at the [[Jewish National Fund]] [[Jewish National Fund Tree of Life Award|Tree of Life Gala]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|last=Gr\u0435\u0435nger|first=Nurit|title=Jewish National Fund Still Makes The Difference in Israel|url=http://newsblaze.com/world/israel/jewish-national-fund-still-makes-difference-in-israel_28240/|publisher=NewsBlaze|date=September 10, 2012|accessdate=August 31, 2017}}</ref> The same year, Ireland was presented with an honorary Doctorate of Humane Letters by the [[California State University]], which stated that she \"generously uses her power and influence to benefit others, supporting social causes including empowering women, supporting young girls through mentoring, and providing opportunities for girls and women at risk.\"<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://archive.li/20121202102250/http://www.calstate.edu/pa/News/2012/Story/honorary2012.shtml|date=June 20, 2012|archive-date=December 2, 2012|url=http://www.calstate.edu/pa/News/2012/Story/honorary2012.shtml|title=Degrees of Distinction|publisher=California State University|url-status = dead|df=}}</ref> Ireland has been nominated as one of 17 finalists for the first Global Business & Interfaith Peace Award given by the Religious Freedom & Business Foundation (a U.S.-based nonprofit), and the [[United Nations Global Compact]] Business for Peace initiative.<ref>{{cite press release|title=Kathy Ireland Among 17 International CEO Finalists for Religious Freedom & Business Foundation\u2019s Interfaith Peace Awards|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/pr/3014308|agency=Digital Journal|accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> On October 13, 2017, at the \"Meet Kathy Ireland Event\" hosted by Amini, Ireland was presented with [[List of Keys to the City in the United States|the key to the city]] of [[High Point, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eventbrite.com/e/meet-kathy-ireland-at-worlds-largest-furniture-expo-high-point-tickets-38253525324# |title=Meet Kathy Ireland at World's Largest Furniture Expo (High Point) |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=October 13, 2017 |via=[[Eventbrite]] |access-date=October 26, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027024908/https://www.eventbrite.com/e/meet-kathy-ireland-at-worlds-largest-furniture-expo-high-point-tickets-38253525324# |archive-date=October 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1988\n|''[[Alien from L.A.]]''\n|Wanda Saknussemm\n|The Movie appeared in an episode of [[Mystery Science Theater 3000]]\n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Journey to the Center of the Earth (1989 film)|Journey to the Center of the Earth]]''\n|Wanda Saknussemm\n|\n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Worth Winning]]''\n|Uncredited\n|\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Side Out]]''\n|Marie\n|\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Mr. Destiny]]''\n|Gina\n|\n|-\n|1991\n|''[[Necessary Roughness (film)|Necessary Roughness]]''\n|Lucy Draper\n|\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[Mom and Dad Save the World]]''\n|Semage, Raff's Daughter\n|\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[Danger Island (film)|Danger Island]]''\n|Laura\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Loaded Weapon 1]]''\n|Destiny Demeanor\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Amore!]]''\n|Taylor Christopher\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Perry Mason (TV movies)#A Perry Mason Mystery|A Perry Mason Mystery: The Case of the Wicked Wives]]''\n|Dee Morrison\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Bandit (film series)|Beauty and the Bandit]]''\n|Crystal\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|1995\n|''Backfire!''\n|Jessica Luvintryst\n|\n|-\n|1996\n|''Gridlock''\n|Michele Conner\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|1996\n|''Miami Hustle''\n|Marsha Thomas\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[Once Upon a Christmas (film)|Once Upon a Christmas]]''\n|Kristen Claus\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|2001\n|''[[Twice Upon a Christmas]]''\n|Kristen Claus\n|TV Movie\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Episodes\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[Charles in Charge]]''\n|Woman in Line\n|\"Snowed In\"\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Grand (TV series)|Grand]]''\n|Sheila\n|\"Carnegie Hall\"\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[Tales from the Crypt (TV series)|Tales from the Crypt]]''\n|Joyce\n|\"Beauty Rest\"\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Down the Shore]]''\n|Rachel\n|\"Computer Date\"\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[The Larry Sanders Show]]''\n|Herself\n|\"The Breakdown: Part 1\"\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Boy Meets World]]''\n|Alexis\n|\"Model Family\"\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Melrose Place]]''\n|Brittany Maddocks\n|\"Grand Delusions\", \"In-Laws and Outlaws\", \"It's a Bad World After All\" and \"I am Curious, Melrose\"\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[The Watcher (TV series)|The Watcher]]''\n|Pilot\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Deadly Games]]''\n|Amber\n|\"The Camp Counselor: Parts 1 & 2\"\n|-\n|1995\u20131996\n|''[[The Fantastic Four]]''\n|Crystal (Voice)\n|\"Doomsday\", \"The Sentry Sinister\", \"Inhumans Saga: Part 3: Beware the Hidden Land\" and \"Inhumans Saga: Part 2: The Inhumans Among Us\"\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Sabrina, the Teenage Witch]]''\n|Shelley\n|\"Trial by Fury\"\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Suddenly Susan]]''\n|Terri\n|\"Love and Divorce American Style: Part 2\" and \"Love and Divorce American Style: Part 3\"\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Duckman: Private Dick/Family Man|Duckman]]''\n|Susan/Susie\n|\"Vuuck, as in Duck\" and \"Aged Heat 2: Women in Heat\"\n|-\n|1996\u20131997\n|''[[The Incredible Hulk (1996 TV series)|The Incredible Hulk]]''\n|Ogress (Voice)\n|\"Fashion Warriors\", \"Down Memory Lane\" and \"Fantastic Fortitude\"\n|-\n|1998\n|''[[The Lionhearts]]''\n|Survive (Voice)\n|\n|-\n|1998\n|''[[King of the Hill]]''\n|Sylvia\n|\"Peggy's Pageant Fever\"\n|-\n|1999\n|''[[Cosby]]''\n|Kara\n|\"He Who Hesitates is Lucas\"\n|-\n|1999\n|''[[Pensacola: Wings of Gold]]''\n|Sarah\n|\"Tip of the Spear\"\n|-\n|1999\n|''[[Touched by an Angel]]''\n|Karla\n|\"The Last Day of the Rest of Your Life\"\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[Strong Medicine]]''\n|Amber Hutton\n|\"Trauma\"\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[For Your Love]]''\n|Rhonda\n|\"The Helpless Hand\"\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[Totally Spies!]]''\n|Julia Hastings\n|\"A Spy is Born: Part 1\"\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Family Guy]]''\n|Cardboard Cutout\n|\"[[Family Goy]]\"\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q262490|c=category:Kathy Ireland|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|s=no|wikt=no|species=no}}\n*{{official}}\n* {{IMDb name|0001387|Kathy Ireland}}\n* {{Tcmdb name}}\n* {{AllMovie name|34520|Kathy Ireland}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Kathy Ireland navigational boxes\n|list1=\n{{SI Swimsuit Cover Models}}\n{{1980\u20131989 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit}}\n{{1990\u20131999 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit}}\n{{Authority control}}\n}}\n\n{{portalbar|Biography|California|Fashion}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ireland, Kathy}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Glendale, California]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Santa Barbara, California]]\n[[Category:American businesspeople in retailing]]\n[[Category:American children's writers]]\n[[Category:American Christians]]\n[[Category:Female models from California]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:Writers from Glendale, California]]\n[[Category:Writers from Santa Barbara, California]]\n[[Category:Activists from California]]\n", "name_user": "SeoR", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reword, remove cap.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kathy_Ireland"}
{"title_page": "Pacific Northwest tree octopus", "text_new": "{{pp-semi-indef|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Internet hoax}}\nThe '''Pacific Northwest tree octopus''' is an [[Internet hoax]] created in 1998 by Lyle Zapato.<ref>{{cite web\n  |url=http://zapatopi.net/treeoctopus/\n  |title=Help Save The Endangered Pacific Northwest Tree Octopus From Extinction!\n  |author=Lyle Zapato\n}}</ref>  This fictitious endangered species of [[cephalopod]] was given the Latin name \"''Octopus paxarbolis''\" (the species name being coined from Latin ''pax'', the root of ''Pacific'', and Spanish ''arbol'' meaning \"tree\"). It was purportedly able to live both on land and in water, and was said to live in the [[Olympic National Forest]] and nearby rivers, [[spawn (biology)|spawning]] in water where its [[Egg (biology)|eggs]] are laid. Its major predator was said to be the [[Sasquatch]]. The Pacific Northwest tree octopus website is among a number of sites commonly used in [[Information literacy|Internet literacy]] classes in schools, although it was not created for that purpose.\n\n==Internet literacy studies==\n\n===Design===\nLeu et al. (2007) conducted an empirical study on 13-year old US school children's ability to critically evaluate online information for reliability.<ref>Leu, D. J., Reinking, D., Carter, A., Castek, J., Coiro, J., Henry, L. A., ... & Zawilinski, L. (2007). Defining online reading comprehension: Using think aloud verbal protocols to refine a preliminary model of Internet reading comprehension processes. ''D. Alvermann (Chair) 21st Century Literacy: What is it, How do students get it, and how do we know if they have it''.</ref> The sample included the top quartile of school children (n=53) in samples from the states of Connecticut and South Carolina. Each school child was exposed to the spoof site ''\"Save The Northwest Pacific Tree Octopus\"'', devoted to this rare species of octopus, complete with pictures of the animal itself and its environment. The school children then received a short, fictitious, message from another class, asking them to locate and evaluate the reliability of the website. They were to provide three reasons for their answer, and summarize the most important information from that website in one or two sentences. Then they were asked to send their information via IM, email, or to post this on a blog site. Following the activity, school children were interviewed to ensure that they were familiar with the term \"reliable,\" an important concept in the task.  When asked what this term meant, all responded with answers indicating that they understood the term (e.g., \"It means that you can trust it;\" \"It means it will always be there for you;\" or \"It's like a friend that you can trust\"). See also.<ref>{{cite journal\n  |url=http://advance.uconn.edu/2006/061113/06111308.htm\n  | title=Researchers find kids need better online academic skills\n  |journal=UComm Advance\n  |author=Beth Krane\n  |publisher=[[University of Connecticut]]\n  |date=November 13, 2006\n  |volume=25|issue=12\n  |quote=Don Leu, Chair in Literacy and Technology at UConn, \"All 25 students fell for the Internet hoax....anyone can publish anything on the Internet, and today's students are not prepared to critically evaluate the information they find there.\"\n  |accessdate=2008-01-11\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal\n  | url=http://www.inklingmagazine.com/articles/tentacled-tree-hugger-gets-legs-up-on-twelve-year-olds/\n  |date=March 14, 2007\n  |title = Tentacled Tree Hugger Disarms Seventh Graders\n  |journal=Inkling\n  |author=Matthew Bettelheim\n  |quote=Of the 25 seventh-graders identified as their schools\u2019 best online readers, 24 recommended this bogus website to another class that Leu had told them was also researching endangered species.\n|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070320203138/http://www.inklingmagazine.com/articles/tentacled-tree-hugger-gets-legs-up-on-twelve-year-olds/ |archive-date=2007-03-20 |access-date=13 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn the spring of 2017, Loos, Ivan & Leu (2018)<ref>Loos, E.F., Ivan, L., & Leu, D. (2018). Save The Pacific Northwest Tree Octopus\u201d: a hoax revisited. Or: how vulnerable are school children to Fake News? ''Information and'' ''Learning Science, 119'' (9, 10), 514-528. https://www.emeraldinsight.com/doi/abs/10.1108/ILS-04-2018-0031\n</ref> replicated the study in a Dutch school class of 27 children (13 girls and 14 boys, 11/12 years old) in the following way: The teacher and the school children were told by the first author of the study that the lesson that would follow would be an online reading comprehension exercise; the real purpose of the lesson was not revealed in advance. The children were asked by the scholar to visit the abovementioned website. They were given the following instructions: \u201cHave a look at this website. Look at the pictures, click on the links if you wish. Do not hurry, you have time enough. And this is not a test. It will not be graded.\u201d The website was automatically translated to Dutch, a facility offered by the [[Chromebook]] they all used. Then, they were asked to answer the following questions: (1) This website presents an octopus living in trees. What country does this animal live in?, (2) According to the website, this particular octopus is an endangered species. For what reason?, (3)  If Greenpeace were to ask you to save this octopus, would you support this and sign? YES, because ... NO, because ... (choose one), (4) Were there parts of the website you didn't understand? If so, please explain., (5) Are there any other comments about this website you would like to make?\" Hence, these school children thought the text was about their willingness to undertake action for an endangered animal. The pupils who answered \u2018YES\u2019 to question (3) were judged as perceiving the site as a reliable one. In this way, it was not necessary to explicitly ask about the reliability of the site, which would have risked priming them. The school children were debriefed after the session and they received a new media literacies training.\n\n===Results===\nThe 2007 US study found that slightly more than half (27) of the 53 school children taking part in the study reported the website as being very reliable. Only 6 out of the 53 school children (11%) viewed the website as unreliable.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/328611057|title=\"Save The Pacific Northwest Tree Octopus\": a hoax revisited. www.researchgate.net October 2018}}</ref> Each of these 6 school children had just participated in a lesson that used this website to teach them to be suspicious of information online.\n\nIn the 2017 Dutch study only 2 out of the total 27 school children (7%) recognized that the website was a hoax.<ref name=\":0\" /> The setting of the task (school environment), the trust in their teacher and the scholar, and the emotional involvement (the topic was an animal in danger) might have made it more difficult for them to perceive the information on the website as fake. Several told the scholar they were shocked that they had considered the digital information on the website to be reliable, as they had received several new literacies training at school over the past year.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Appalachian Mud Squid]]\n*[[Drop bear]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://zapatopi.net/treeoctopus/ Official site]\n* {{cite web |url= http://www.newliteracies.uconn.edu/event_files/New_Literacies_for_New_Times_handout.pdf |title= New Literacies for New Times: Preparing our Students for the 21st Century. |url-status= bot: unknown |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120210104505/http://www.newliteracies.uconn.edu/event_files/New_Literacies_for_New_Times_handout.pdf |archivedate= 2012-02-10 }}&nbsp;{{small|(178&nbsp;[[Kibibyte|KiB]])}} Professor Leu's teaching tool.\n\n[[Category:1998 hoaxes]]\n[[Category:Fictional octopuses]]\n[[Category:Hoaxes in science]]\n[[Category:Hoaxes in the United States]]\n[[Category:Internet hoaxes]]\n[[Category:Legendary creatures in popular culture]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-semi-indef|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Internet hoax}}\nThe '''Pacific Northwest tree octopus''' is an [[Internet hoax]] created in 1998 by Lyle Zapato.<ref>{{cite web\n  |url=http://zapatopi.net/treeoctopus/\n  |title=Help Save The Endangered Pacific Northwest Tree Octopus From Extinction!\n  |author=Lyle Zapato\n}}</ref>  This fictitious endangered species of [[cephalopod]] was given the Latin name \"''Octopus paxarbolis''\" (the species name being coined from Latin ''pax'', the root of ''Pacific'', and Spanish ''arbol'' meaning \"tree\"). It was purportedly able to live both on land and in water, and was said to live in the [[Olympic National Forest]] and nearby rivers, [[spawn (biology)|spawning]] in water where its [[Egg (biology)|eggs]] are laid. Its major predator was said to be the [[Sasquatch]]. The Pacific Northwest tree octopus website is among a number of sites commonly used in [[Information literacy|Internet literacy]] classes in schools, although it was not created for that purpose.\n\n==Internet literacy studies==\n\n===Design===\nLeu et al. (2007) conducted an empirical study on 13-year old US school children's ability to critically evaluate online information for reliability.<ref>Leu, D. J., Reinking, D., Carter, A., Castek, J., Coiro, J., Henry, L. A., ... & Zawilinski, L. (2007). Defining online reading comprehension: Using think aloud verbal protocols to refine a preliminary model of Internet reading comprehension processes. ''D. Alvermann (Chair) 21st Century Literacy: What is it, How do students get it, and how do we know if they have it''.</ref> The sample included the top quartile of school children (n=53) in samples from the states of Connecticut and South Carolina. Each school child was exposed to the spoof site ''\"Save The Northwest Pacific Tree Octopus\"'', devoted to this rare species of octopus, complete with pictures of the animal itself and its environment. The school children then received a short, fictitious, message from another class, asking them to locate and evaluate the reliability of the website. They were to provide three reasons for their answer, and summarize the most important information from that website in one or two sentences. Then they were asked to send their information via IM, email, or to post this on a blog site. Following the activity, school children were interviewed to ensure that they were familiar with the term \"reliable,\" an important concept in the task.  When asked what this term meant, all responded with answers indicating that they understood the term (e.g., \"It means that you can trust it;\" \"It means it will always be there for you;\" or \"It's like a friend that you can trust\"). See also.<ref>{{cite journal\n  |url=http://advance.uconn.edu/2006/061113/06111308.htm\n  | title=Researchers find kids need better online academic skills\n  |journal=UComm Advance\n  |author=Beth Krane\n  |publisher=[[University of Connecticut]]\n  |date=November 13, 2006\n  |volume=25|issue=12\n  |quote=Don Leu, Chair in Literacy and Technology at UConn, \"All 25 students fell for the Internet hoax....anyone can publish anything on the Internet, and today's students are not prepared to critically evaluate the information they find there.\"\n  |accessdate=2008-01-11\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal\n  | url=http://www.inklingmagazine.com/articles/tentacled-tree-hugger-gets-legs-up-on-twelve-year-olds/\n  |date=March 14, 2007\n  |title = Tentacled Tree Hugger Disarms Seventh Graders\n  |journal=Inkling\n  |author=Matthew Bettelheim\n  |quote=Of the 25 seventh-graders identified as their schools\u2019 best online readers, 24 recommended this bogus website to another class that Leu had told them was also researching endangered species.\n|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070320203138/http://www.inklingmagazine.com/articles/tentacled-tree-hugger-gets-legs-up-on-twelve-year-olds/ |archive-date=2007-03-20 |access-date=13 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn the spring of 2017, Loos, Ivan & Leu (2018)<ref>Loos, E.F., Ivan, L., & Leu, D. (2018). Save The Pacific Northwest Tree Octopus\u201d: a hoax revisited. Or: how vulnerable are school children to Fake News? ''Information and'' ''Learning Science, 119'' (9, 10), 514-528. https://www.emeraldinsight.com/doi/abs/10.1108/ILS-04-2018-0031\n</ref> replicated the study in a Dutch school class of 27 children (13 girls and 14 boys, 11/12 years old) in the following way: The teacher and the school children were told by the first author of the study that the lesson that would follow would be an online reading comprehension exercise; the real purpose of the lesson was not revealed in advance. The children were asked by the scholar to visit the abovementioned website. They were given the following instructions: \u201cHave a look at this website. Look at the pictures, click on the links if you wish. Do not hurry, you have time enough. And this is not a test. It will not be graded.\u201d The website was automatically translated to Dutch, a facility offered by the [[Chromebook]] they all used. Then, they were asked to answer the following questions: (1) This website presents an octopus living in trees. What country does this animal live in?, (2) According to the website, this particular octopus is an endangered species. For what reason?, (3)  If Greenpeace were to ask you to save this octopus, would you support this and sign? YES, because ... NO, because ... (choose one), (4) Were there parts of the website you didn't understand? If so, please explain., (5) Are there any other comments about this website you would like to make?\" Hence, these school children thought the text was about their willingness to undertake action for an endangered animal. The pupils who answered \u2018YES\u2019 to question (3) were judged as perceiving the site as a reliable one. In this way, it was not necessary to explicitly ask about the reliability of the site, which would have risked priming them. The school children were debriefed after the session and they received a new media literacies training.\n\n===Results===\nThe 2007 US study found that slightly more than half (27) of the 53 school children taking part in the study reported the website as being very reliable. Only 6 out of the 53 school children (11%) viewed the website as unreliable.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/328611057|title=\"Save The Pacific Northwest Tree Octopus\": a hoax revisited. www.researchgate.net October 2018}}</ref> Each of these 6 school children had just participated in a lesson that used this website to teach them to be suspicious of information online.\n\nIn the 2017 Dutch study only 2 out of the total 27 school children (7%) recognized that the website was a hoax.<ref name=\":0\" /> The setting of the task (school environment), the trust in their teacher and the scholar, and the emotional involvement (the topic was an animal in danger) might have made it more difficult for them to perceive the information on the website as fake. Several told the scholar they were shocked that they had considered the digital information on the website to be reliable, as they had received several new literacies training at school over the past year.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Appalachian Mud Squid]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://zapatopi.net/treeoctopus/ Official site]\n* {{cite web |url= http://www.newliteracies.uconn.edu/event_files/New_Literacies_for_New_Times_handout.pdf |title= New Literacies for New Times: Preparing our Students for the 21st Century. |url-status= bot: unknown |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120210104505/http://www.newliteracies.uconn.edu/event_files/New_Literacies_for_New_Times_handout.pdf |archivedate= 2012-02-10 }}&nbsp;{{small|(178&nbsp;[[Kibibyte|KiB]])}} Professor Leu's teaching tool.\n\n[[Category:1998 hoaxes]]\n[[Category:Fictional octopuses]]\n[[Category:Hoaxes in science]]\n[[Category:Hoaxes in the United States]]\n[[Category:Internet hoaxes]]\n[[Category:Legendary creatures in popular culture]]\n", "name_user": "Nickyonge", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added \"Drop bear\" to \"See also\" section", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_Northwest_tree_octopus"}
{"title_page": "Union Street station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)", "text_new": "{{For|the demolished station actually at Union Street & Fifth Avenue|Union Street (BMT Fifth Avenue Line)}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n\n{{Short description|New York City Subway station in Brooklyn}}\n{{Infobox NYCS\n| name = Union Street\n| font_color = black\n| bg_color = #FFC800\n| bg_color_2 = #874F17\n| image = Union Street - Northbound Platform.jpg\n| image_caption = Manhattan bound platform\n| address = Union Street &amp; [[Fourth Avenue (Brooklyn)|Fourth Avenue]]<br>Brooklyn, NY 11217<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.nyc.gov/assets/doh/downloads/pdf/epi/Brooklyn|title=Borough of Brooklyn, New York City|publisher=[[Government of New York City]]|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| borough = [[Brooklyn]]\n| locale = [[Park Slope, Brooklyn|Park Slope]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|40.678108|N|73.98391|W|display=inline,title}}\n| lat_dir = N\n| lon_dir = W\n| division = BMT\n| line = [[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]]\n| service = Fourth center local\n| service_header = Fourth center local header\n| connection = {{bus icon}} '''[[NYCT Bus]]''': {{NYC bus link|B37}} <small>(on [[Third Avenue (Brooklyn)|Third Avenue]])</small>; {{NYC bus link|B63}} <small>(on Fifth Avenue)</small><ref>{{cite NYC bus map|B}}</ref>\n| code = 028\n| accessible = planned\n| platforms = 2 [[side platform]]s\n| tracks = 4\n| structure = Underground\n| open_date = {{start date and age|June 22, 1915}}<ref name=\"Station Opening2\"/>\n| passengers = 2,090,848<ref name=\"ridership\">{{NYCS const|riderref}}</ref>\n| pass_year = 2018\n| pass_percent = 8.0\n| rank = 226<ref name=\"ridership\"/>\n| next_north = {{NYCS next | station=Atlantic Avenue\u2013Barclays Center | line=BMT Fourth Avenue Line | service=Fourth center local}}\n| next_south = {{NYCS next | station=Ninth Street | line=BMT Fourth Avenue Line | service=Fourth center local}}\n| legend = {{NYCS infobox legend|allexceptnights}}{{NYCS infobox legend|nightsonly}}{{NYCS infobox legend|rushonly}}{{NYCS infobox legend|rushpeak}}\n}}\n\n'''Union Street''' is a local [[metro station|station]] on the [[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]] of the [[New York City Subway]]. It is located at the corner of [[Fourth Avenue (Brooklyn)|Fourth Avenue]] and Union Street in [[Brooklyn]], [[New York City]], serving the communities of [[Park Slope, Brooklyn|Park Slope]], [[Gowanus, Brooklyn|Gowanus]] and [[Carroll Gardens, Brooklyn|Carroll Gardens]]. It is served by the [[R (New York City Subway service)|R]] train at all times. The [[D (New York City Subway service)|D]] and [[N (New York City Subway service)|N]] trains also stop here during late nights, and some rush-hour [[W (New York City Subway service)|W]] trains stop here in the peak direction.\n\nThe Union Street station was constructed as part of the Fourth Avenue Line, which was approved in 1905. Construction on the segment of the line that includes Union Street started on December 20, 1909, and was completed in September 1912. The station opened on June 22, 1915 as part of the initial portion of the BMT Fourth Avenue Line to [[59th Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|59th Street]]. The station's platforms were lengthened in 1925, and again in 1970. The station was also renovated in 1970 and in the mid-1990s.\n\n==History==\n===Construction and opening===\nThe Union Street station was constructed as part of the Fourth Avenue Line, the plan for which was initially adopted on June 1, 1905.<ref name=\":123\">{{Cite journal|last=Rogoff|first=David|date=May 1961|title=The Fourth Ave. Subway|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzKvSWhrQBW4d3pvOGZaSERiZEhpQ24xT19DTktkQUVlLW5j/view|journal=New York Division Bulletin|publisher=Electric Railroaders' Association|volume=|pages=2\u201310|access-date=May 8, 2017|via=}}</ref> The Rapid Transit Commission was succeeded on July 1, 1907, by the [[New York Public Service Commission|New York State Public Service Commission]] (PSC), which approved the plan for the line in late 1907.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/?id=XoxBAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA18&dq=4th+Avenue+line#v=onepage&q=4th%20Avenue%20line&f=false|page=18|title=Fourth Avenue Subway, Brooklyn's New Transportation Line: A Part of the Dual System of Rapid Transit of the City of New York|date=June 19, 1915|publisher=Public Service Commission|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":11\">{{Cite news|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48901678/|title=Fourth Avenue Subway Is Sent To A Committee|last=|first=|date=March 20, 1908|work=The Brooklyn Daily Eagle|access-date=May 4, 2017|pages=1\u20132|language=en}}</ref> The contract for the section of the line that included the Union Street station, Route 11A2, which extended from 10th Street to Sackett Street, was awarded on May 22, 1908, and approved by the [[New York City Board of Estimate]] on October 29, 1909.<ref name=\":10\" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://bklyn.newspapers.com/image/53922207/|title=Fourth Avenue Subway To Be Political Issue|date=December 11, 1908|work=The Brooklyn Daily Eagle|access-date=May 4, 2017|page=1|language=en}}</ref> Construction on the segment started on December 20, 1909, and was completed in September 1912.<ref name=\":123\"/>\n\nAs part of negotiations between New York City, the [[Brooklyn Rapid Transit Company]] (BRT), and the [[Interborough Rapid Transit Company]] for the expansion of the city's transit network, the line was leased to a subsidiary of the BRT. The agreement, known as Contract 4 of the [[Dual Contracts]], was signed on March 19, 1913.<ref name=\":10\"/> Union Street opened on June 22, 1915 as part of the initial portion of the Fourth Avenue Line to [[59th Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|59th Street]].<ref name=\"Station Opening2\">{{cite web|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48814840/|title=Through Tube to Coney, 48 Minutes: First Train on Fourth Avenue Route Beats West End Line Eleven Minutes|date=June 22, 1915|publisher=[[Brooklyn Daily Eagle]]|accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Station renovations ===\n\n==== 1920s ====\nOn June 27, 1922, the New York State Transit Commission directed its engineers to prepare plans to lengthen the platforms at 23 stations on the lines of the [[Brooklyn\u2013Manhattan Transit Corporation]] (BMT), the successor to the BRT, to accommodate eight-car trains. As part of the project, Union Street's platforms would have been lengthened from {{Convert|435|feet|meters}} to {{Convert|530|feet|meters}}.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Legislature|first=New York (State)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-ugaAQAAIAAJ&pg=RA3-PA100&dq=%22union+street%22+LENGTHENING&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj8_PLm7tboAhXBhOAKHVx0AzwQ6AEwA3oECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=%22union%20street%22%20LENGTHENING&f=false|title=Second Annual Report of the Transit Commission (For the Calendar Year 1922)|date=1923|publisher=New York State Transit Commission|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=100|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u5kT80_w6rYC&pg=PA1277&dq=%22union+street%22+%22530+feet%22&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjngqLU7dboAhVLTt8KHapMD8IQ6AEwCHoECAkQAg#v=onepage&q=%22union%20street%22%20%22530%20feet%22&f=false|title=Proceedings of the Transit Commission, State of New York Volume III From January 1 to December 31, 1923|date=1923|publisher=New York State Transit Commission|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=1277|language=en}}</ref> On February 16, 1925, the [[New York City Board of Transportation]] (NYCBOT) directed its engineers to prepare plans to lengthen the platforms at this and eleven other stations along the Fourth Avenue Line. It estimated the project's cost to be $633,000 ({{inflation|fmt=eq|index=US|value=633000|year=1925|r=-3}}). The BMT had been ordered by the Transit Commission to lengthen these platforms since September 1923.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1925/02/17/archives/12-bm-t-stations-to-be-lengthehed-transportation-board-orders.html|title=12 B-M. T. Stations To Be Lengthened; Transportation Board Orders Engineers to Prepare Contracts for Brooklyn Work. Cost Put At $633,000 ({{inflation|fmt=eq|index=US|value=633000|year=1925|r=-3}}) Letter to Commission Urges That Company Be Compelled to Buy New Cars.|last=|first=|date=February 17, 1925|work=The New York Times|access-date=May 4, 2017|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The NYCBOT received bids for the project on February 25, 1926.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48193500/the-brooklyn-citizen/|title=Board Receives Platform Bids For B.M.T. Lines. Six Companies Submit Prices for Extending Subway Stations|date=1926-02-26|work=The Brooklyn Citizen|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=5}}</ref> The contract was awarded to Corson Construction Company for $345,021 ({{inflation|fmt=eq|index=US|value=345021|year=1926|r=-3}}).<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48193684/the-standard-union/|title=Brooklyn Wins Big Improvement Fund|date=1926-03-18|work=Brooklyn Standard Union|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=20}}</ref>\n\n==== 1950s and 1960s ====\nIn July 1959, the [[New York City Transit Authority]] (NYCTA) announced that it would install [[fluorescent lighting]] at the Union Street station and five other stations along Fourth Avenue for between $175,000 and $200,000. Bids on the project were to be advertised on August 7, 1959 and completed by fall 1960.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/47783394/bay-ridge-home-reporter/|title=Our Subway Stations To Be Brighter|date=1959-07-10|work=Bay Ridge Home Reporter|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=2}}</ref>\n\nIn the 1960s, the NYCTA started a project to lengthen station platforms on its lines in Southern Brooklyn to {{Convert|615|feet|meters|abbr=}} to accommodate 10-car trains.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=New York City Transit Authority Annual Report For The Year June 30, 1960|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=1960|isbn=|location=|pages=16\u201317}}</ref> On July 14, 1967, the NYCTA awarded a contract to conduct test borings at eleven stations on the Fourth Avenue Line, including Union Street, to W. M. Walsh Corporation for $6,585 ({{inflation|fmt=eq|index=US|value=6585|year=1967}}) in preparation of the construction of platform extensions.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=HJTVAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22Union+Street,+9th+Street,%22&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=borings+JULY|title=Minutes and Proceedings|date=1967|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=379\u2013380|language=en}}</ref> The NYCTA issued an invitation for bids on the project to extend the platforms at stations along the Fourth Avenue Line between [[Pacific Street station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|Pacific Street]] and [[36th Street station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|36th Street]], including those at Union Street, on March 28, 1969.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=-HNIAQAAIAAJ&dq=Group+XXX%E2%80%94Broadway-Fourth+Avenue+Line:+pacific+Street,+Union+Street,+9th+Street&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Group+XXX|title=Engineering News-record|date=1969|publisher=McGraw-Hill|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=63|language=en}}</ref> The contract was awarded to Horn Construction Company on May 13, 1969 for $7,381,890. Funding for the renovation projects came out of the NYCTA's 1969\u20131970 Capital Budget, costing $8,177,890 in total.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=c-gxGpL_JNQC&dq=%22Pacific+Street+to+36th+Street+stations%22&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=10-car|title=Proceedings of the New York City Transit Authority Relating to Matters Other Than Operation|date=1969|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=280, 435, 487|language=en}}</ref>\n\nAs part of the renovation project, the station's platforms were extended {{Convert|85|feet|meters|abbr=}}<ref name=\":1\" /> to the north,<ref name=\":2\" /> and the station's elaborate mosaic tile walls were covered over with {{convert|8|by|16|in|cm|adj=on}} white cinderblock tiles. The latter change, which was also made to 15 other stations on the [[BMT Broadway Line|BMT Broadway]] and Fourth Avenue Line, was criticized for being dehumanizing. The NYCTA spokesman stated that the old tiles were in poor condition and that the change was made to improve the appearance of stations and provide uniformity. Furthermore, it did not consider the old mosaics to have \"any great artistic merit\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Burks|first=Edward C.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1970/02/21/archives/subways-colored-tile-gets-cover-up-job.html|title=Subways' Colored Tile Gets Cover\u2010Up Job|date=1970-02-21|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-07|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==== 1990s ====\n[[File:Union BMT track.jpg|thumb|175px|The colored tilework forms part of the station art installation|alt=]]\nThe station was renovated again from 1991 to 1994. The $2.397&nbsp;million contract for the project was awarded on February 28, 1991. During the closure of the Bay Ridge-bound platform, the glazed tiles at the station were heavily defaced with graffiti, and were cleaned prior to the station's reopening with a heavy duty cleaner, which damaged the glazing. A modification to the contract was approved on May 23, 1994. As part of the modification, new graffiti resistant ceramic tile was installed, signage, advertising panels, benches and trash bins were removed and reinstalled, exhaust systems were added in the porter rooms at both platforms, and the wall-mounted conductors board was replaced by a ceiling-mounted one. The modification cost $174,000, and change orders cost $111,004.<ref>{{Cite book|title=NYC Transit Committee Agenda May 1994|date=May 16, 1994|publisher=New York City Transit}}</ref>{{Rp|C-99, C-100}} The Brooklyn-bound platform was closed between July 15 and November 15, 1991,<ref>{{Cite news|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/29284935/daily_news/|title=Attention Brooklyn-Bound N R Subway Riders: Union Street Station Is Closing July 15th to November 15th|last=|first=|date=July 12, 1991|work=New York Daily News|access-date=March 8, 2019}}</ref> while the Manhattan-bound platform was closed between February 19 and June 20, 1992.<ref>{{Cite news|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/29283657/daily_news/|title=Attention N, R Customers: Beginning June 20, 1992: Union Street Station Manhattan-bound platform reopens.|last=|first=|date=June 19, 1992|work=New York Daily News|access-date=March 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/29284140/daily_news/|title=Attention N & R Subway Customers: Union St Manhattan-bound platform is closing February 19th to June 19th.|last=|first=|date=February 18, 1992|work=New York Daily News|access-date=March 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to upgrading the same elements that were replaced in the previous overhaul, floors and track wall tiling, the public announcement system, and safety treads along platform edges and track-beds were replaced. It also included an art installation by Emmett Wigglesworth called ''CommUnion''. It features twenty-two panels of various designs in the recessed area of the platform tiles above the station signs and other designs on the openings in the track walls.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?1167|title=Showing Image 1167|last=Whitehorne|first=Wayne|date=January 15, 2000|website=www.nycsubway.org|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/mta/aft/permanentart/permart.html?agency=n&line=R&station=22|title=Arts for Transit: CommUnion|work=MTA Arts for Transit|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|accessdate=June 2, 2007}}</ref>\n\n==== Proposed accessibility ====\nAs part of the 2015\u20132019 [[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]] Capital Program, $300&nbsp;million was allocated to enhance station access and provide ADA-accessibility at 15 stations chosen by the city. Four stations were being evaluated for such improvements, including the Union Street station.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BJRM36BCciU|title=MTA Board - NYCT/Bus Committee Meeting - 02/20/2018|date=February 20, 2018|publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|accessdate=March 4, 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/capitaldashboard/allframenew_head.html?PROJNUM=t7160521&PLTYPE=1&DISPLAYALL=Y|title=T7160521 Station Capacity Enhancements at Union Street on the 4 Avenue Line - Design Only|website=mta.info|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear|left}}\n\n==Station layout==\n{{stack|float=right|\n{{NYCS 4-tracked local station\n|1=Atlantic Avenue\u2013Barclays Center\n|l1=Atlantic Av\n|2=Ninth Street\n|l2=9 St\n|code=BMT Fourth Avenue Line\n|color=yellow\n|textcolor=black\n|deg=330\n}}\n}}\n{{NYCS Platform Layout IND Fulton Street Line}}\n[[File:Union Street BMT Stairs.jpg|thumb|220px|Entrance|alt=]]\nThis underground station has four tracks and two [[side platform]]s.<ref name=\"tracks2\">{{NYCS const|trackref|trackbook}}</ref> The R stops here at all times;<ref name=\"ttr\">{{NYCS const|timetable|r}}</ref> some rush-hour W trains stop here in the peak direction;<ref name=\"ttw\">{{NYCS const|timetable|w}}</ref> and the D and N stop here during late nights, but use the center express tracks to bypass the station during daytime hours.<ref name=\"ttd\">{{NYCS const|timetable|d}}</ref><ref name=\"ttn\">{{NYCS const|timetable|n}}</ref> A white tiled curtain wall separates the express tracks from the local tracks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm3.jpg|title=Looking down the simple Manhattan-bound platform at Union Street.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=December 22, 2008|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nBoth platforms are columnless except for a section at their extreme north ends,<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm3.jpg|title=Looking down the simple Manhattan-bound platform at Union Street.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=December 22, 2008|website=subwaynut.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 7, 2020}}</ref> where they were extended in 1970 to accommodate 10-car trains. Here, the columns are cream colored I-beams. The ceiling is lower in this section.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm6.jpg|title=The ceiling gets extremely low right at the northern end of the station at Union Street.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=December 22, 2008|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nPrior to the station's 1970 renovation, it was finished all in white and marble tile, and it had its own color scheme to allow regular passengers to identify the station based only on the color of the marble trimmings.<ref name=\":10\" /> Since the renovation, the station walls have consisted of white cinderblock tiles, except for small recesses in the walls, which contain gray-painted cinderblock tiles. The gray cinderblock field contains the station-name signs and white text pointing to the exits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm4.jpg|title=A close up of a Union Street station sign on the platform wall, with the 1960s arrow pointing for the exit beneath it.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=December 22, 2008|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Exits===\nEach platform has one same-level [[fare control]] area in the center and there are no crossovers or crossunders to allow free transfer between directions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?122221|title=Bay Ridge-bound fare control|last=Tobar|first=Roberto C.|date=May 20, 2011|website=www.nycsubway.org|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> The Manhattan-bound side has a fare control area, a [[turnstile]] bank, token booth, and two street stairs. The stairs on the Manhattan-bound platform go up to the southeast corner of Union Street and Fourth Avenue while those on the Bay Ridge-bound platform goes up to the southwest corner. The Bay Ridge-bound side has a fare control area, a [[turnstile]] bank without a token booth, and two street stairs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm11.jpg|title=Going down to the now unstaffed Bay Ridge-bound fare control area|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=May 9, 2013|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"MTA-ParkSlopeMap-2015\">{{cite web|title=MTA Neighborhood Maps: Park Slope|url=http://web.mta.info/maps/neighborhoods/bkn/B3_Park_Slope_2015.pdf|website=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority|mta.info]]|publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|accessdate=August 2, 2015|date=2015}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear|left}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|position=right|Union Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)}}\n* {{NYCS ref|http://www.nycsubway.org/perl/stations?216:2870|BMT 4th Avenue|Union Street}}\n* The Subway Nut \u2014 [http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/index.php Union Street Pictures]\n* MTA's Arts For Transit \u2014 [https://web.archive.org/web/20110606073450/http://mta.info/mta/aft/permanentart/permart.html?agency=nyct&line=M&station=13&xdev=1339 Union Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)]\n* [https://maps.google.com/?ie=UTF8&ll=40.677115,-73.983328&spn=0,359.986567&z=17&lci=transit&layer=c&cbll=40.677228,-73.983256&panoid=21WG-nYiOCICM5t9pabhQg&cbp=12,336.54,,0,3.63 Union Street entrance from Google Maps Street View]\n* [https://www.google.com/maps/@40.6772079,-73.9830475,3a,75y,62.15h,83.78t/data=!3m7!1e1!3m5!1s-51z5J31USnI%2FWG3GwzS1EZI%2FAAAAAAAAYTo%2FRqvXDLDF-hww1DY9gHkftwOWZaiTYALUQCLIB!2e4!6s%2F%2Flh4.googleusercontent.com%2F-51z5J31USnI%2FWG3GwzS1EZI%2FAAAAAAAAYTo%2FRqvXDLDF-hww1DY9gHkftwOWZaiTYALUQCLIB%2Fw203-h100-p-k-no%2F!7i7168!8i3584!4m3!8m2!3m1!1e1 Platform from Google Maps Street View]\n\n{{NYCS stations navbox by service|lr=y}}\n{{NYCS stations navbox by line|4ave=yes}}\n\n[[Category:BMT Fourth Avenue Line stations]]\n[[Category:New York City Subway stations in Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1915]]\n[[Category:1915 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Park Slope]]\n[[Category:New York City Subway stations located underground]]\n", "text_old": "{{good article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{For|the demolished station actually at Union Street & Fifth Avenue|Union Street (BMT Fifth Avenue Line)}}\n\n{{Short description|New York City Subway station in Brooklyn}}\n{{Infobox NYCS\n| name = Union Street\n| font_color = black\n| bg_color = #FFC800\n| bg_color_2 = #874F17\n| image = Union Street - Northbound Platform.jpg\n| image_caption = Manhattan bound platform\n| address = Union Street &amp; [[Fourth Avenue (Brooklyn)|Fourth Avenue]]<br>Brooklyn, NY 11217<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.nyc.gov/assets/doh/downloads/pdf/epi/Brooklyn|title=Borough of Brooklyn, New York City|publisher=[[Government of New York City]]|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| borough = [[Brooklyn]]\n| locale = [[Park Slope, Brooklyn|Park Slope]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|40.678108|N|73.98391|W|display=inline,title}}\n| lat_dir = N\n| lon_dir = W\n| division = BMT\n| line = [[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]]\n| service = Fourth center local\n| service_header = Fourth center local header\n| connection = {{bus icon}} '''[[NYCT Bus]]''': {{NYC bus link|B37}} <small>(on [[Third Avenue (Brooklyn)|Third Avenue]])</small>; {{NYC bus link|B63}} <small>(on Fifth Avenue)</small><ref>{{cite NYC bus map|B}}</ref>\n| code = 028\n| accessible = planned\n| platforms = 2 [[side platform]]s\n| tracks = 4\n| structure = Underground\n| open_date = {{start date and age|June 22, 1915}}<ref name=\"Station Opening2\"/>\n| passengers = 2,090,848<ref name=\"ridership\">{{NYCS const|riderref}}</ref>\n| pass_year = 2018\n| pass_percent = 8.0\n| rank = 226<ref name=\"ridership\"/>\n| next_north = {{NYCS next | station=Atlantic Avenue\u2013Barclays Center | line=BMT Fourth Avenue Line | service=Fourth center local}}\n| next_south = {{NYCS next | station=Ninth Street | line=BMT Fourth Avenue Line | service=Fourth center local}}\n| legend = {{NYCS infobox legend|allexceptnights}}{{NYCS infobox legend|nightsonly}}{{NYCS infobox legend|rushonly}}{{NYCS infobox legend|rushpeak}}\n}}\n\n'''Union Street''' is a local [[metro station|station]] on the [[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]] of the [[New York City Subway]]. It is located at the corner of [[Fourth Avenue (Brooklyn)|Fourth Avenue]] and Union Street in [[Brooklyn]], [[New York City]], serving the communities of [[Park Slope, Brooklyn|Park Slope]], [[Gowanus, Brooklyn|Gowanus]] and [[Carroll Gardens, Brooklyn|Carroll Gardens]]. It is served by the [[R (New York City Subway service)|R]] train at all times. The [[D (New York City Subway service)|D]] and [[N (New York City Subway service)|N]] trains also stop here during late nights, and some rush-hour [[W (New York City Subway service)|W]] trains stop here in the peak direction.\n\nThe Union Street station was constructed as part of the Fourth Avenue Line, which was approved in 1905. Construction on the segment of the line that includes Union Street started on December 20, 1909, and was completed in September 1912. The station opened on June 22, 1915 as part of the initial portion of the BMT Fourth Avenue Line to [[59th Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|59th Street]]. The station's platforms were lengthened in 1925, and again in 1970. The station was also renovated in 1970 and in the mid-1990s.\n\n==History==\n===Construction and opening===\nThe Union Street station was constructed as part of the Fourth Avenue Line, the plan for which was initially adopted on June 1, 1905.<ref name=\":123\">{{Cite journal|last=Rogoff|first=David|date=May 1961|title=The Fourth Ave. Subway|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzKvSWhrQBW4d3pvOGZaSERiZEhpQ24xT19DTktkQUVlLW5j/view|journal=New York Division Bulletin|publisher=Electric Railroaders' Association|volume=|pages=2\u201310|access-date=May 8, 2017|via=}}</ref> The Rapid Transit Commission was succeeded on July 1, 1907, by the [[New York Public Service Commission|New York State Public Service Commission]] (PSC), which approved the plan for the line in late 1907.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/?id=XoxBAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA18&dq=4th+Avenue+line#v=onepage&q=4th%20Avenue%20line&f=false|page=18|title=Fourth Avenue Subway, Brooklyn's New Transportation Line: A Part of the Dual System of Rapid Transit of the City of New York|date=June 19, 1915|publisher=Public Service Commission|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":11\">{{Cite news|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48901678/|title=Fourth Avenue Subway Is Sent To A Committee|last=|first=|date=March 20, 1908|work=The Brooklyn Daily Eagle|access-date=May 4, 2017|pages=1\u20132|language=en}}</ref> The contract for the section of the line that included the Union Street station, Route 11A2, which extended from 10th Street to Sackett Street, was awarded on May 22, 1908, and approved by the [[New York City Board of Estimate]] on October 29, 1909.<ref name=\":10\" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://bklyn.newspapers.com/image/53922207/|title=Fourth Avenue Subway To Be Political Issue|date=December 11, 1908|work=The Brooklyn Daily Eagle|access-date=May 4, 2017|page=1|language=en}}</ref> Construction on the segment started on December 20, 1909, and was completed in September 1912.<ref name=\":12\">{{Cite journal|last=Rogoff|first=David|date=May 1961|title=The Fourth Ave. Subway|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzKvSWhrQBW4d3pvOGZaSERiZEhpQ24xT19DTktkQUVlLW5j/view|journal=New York Division Bulletin|publisher=Electric Railroaders' Association|volume=|pages=2\u201310|access-date=May 8, 2017|via=}}</ref>\n\nAs part of negotiations between New York City, the [[Brooklyn Rapid Transit Company]] (BRT) and the [[Interborough Rapid Transit Company]] for the expansion of the city's transit network, the line was leased to a subsidiary of the BRT. The agreement, known as Contract 4 of the [[Dual Contracts]], was signed on March 19, 1913.<ref name=\":10\"/> Union Street opened on June 22, 1915 as part of the initial portion of the Fourth Avenue Line to [[59th Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|59th Street]].<ref name=\"Station Opening2\">{{cite web|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48814840/|title=Through Tube to Coney, 48 Minutes: First Train on Fourth Avenue Route Beats West End Line Eleven Minutes|date=June 22, 1915|publisher=[[Brooklyn Daily Eagle]]|accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Station renovations ===\n\n==== 1920s ====\nOn June 27, 1922, the New York State Transit Commission directed its engineers to prepare plans to lengthen the platforms at 23 stations on the lines of the [[Brooklyn\u2013Manhattan Transit Corporation]] (BMT), the successor to the BRT, to accommodate eight-car trains. As part of the project, Union Street's platforms would have been lengthened from {{Convert|435|feet|meters}} to {{Convert|530|feet|meters}}.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Legislature|first=New York (State)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-ugaAQAAIAAJ&pg=RA3-PA100&dq=%22union+street%22+LENGTHENING&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj8_PLm7tboAhXBhOAKHVx0AzwQ6AEwA3oECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=%22union%20street%22%20LENGTHENING&f=false|title=Second Annual Report of the Transit Commission (For the Calendar Year 1922)|date=1923|publisher=New York State Transit Commission|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=100|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u5kT80_w6rYC&pg=PA1277&dq=%22union+street%22+%22530+feet%22&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjngqLU7dboAhVLTt8KHapMD8IQ6AEwCHoECAkQAg#v=onepage&q=%22union%20street%22%20%22530%20feet%22&f=false|title=Proceedings of the Transit Commission, State of New York Volume III From January 1 to December 31, 1923|date=1923|publisher=New York State Transit Commission|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=1277|language=en}}</ref> On February 16, 1925, the [[New York City Board of Transportation]] (NYCBOT) directed its engineers to prepare plans to lengthen the platforms at this and eleven other stations along the Fourth Avenue Line. It estimated the project's cost to be $633,000. The BMT had been ordered by the Transit Commission to lengthen these platforms since September 1923.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url-access=subscription|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1925/02/17/archives/12-bm-t-stations-to-be-lengthehed-transportation-board-orders.html|title=12 B-M. T. Stations To Be Lengthened; Transportation Board Orders Engineers to Prepare Contracts for Brooklyn Work. Cost Put At $633,000 Letter to Commission Urges That Company Be Compelled to Buy New Cars.|last=|first=|date=February 17, 1925|work=The New York Times|access-date=May 4, 2017|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The NYCBOT received bids for the project on February 25, 1926.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48193500/the-brooklyn-citizen/|title=Board Receives Platform Bids For B.M.T. Lines. Six Companies Submit Prices for Extending Subway Stations|date=1926-02-26|work=The Brooklyn Citizen|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=5}}</ref> The contract was awarded to Corson Construction Company for $345,021.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48193684/the-standard-union/|title=Brooklyn Wins Big Improvement Fund|date=1926-03-18|work=Brooklyn Standard Union|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=20}}</ref>\n\n==== 1950s and 1960s ====\nIn July 1959, the [[New York City Transit Authority]] (NYCTA) announced that it would install [[fluorescent lighting]] at the Union Street station and five other stations along Fourth Avenue for between $175,000 and $200,000. Bids on the project were to be advertised on August 7, 1959 and completed by fall 1960.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/47783394/bay-ridge-home-reporter/|title=Our Subway Stations To Be Brighter|date=1959-07-10|work=Bay Ridge Home Reporter|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=2}}</ref> \n\nIn the 1960s, the NYCTA started a project to lengthen station platforms on its lines in Southern Brooklyn to {{Convert|615|feet|meters|abbr=}} to accommodate 10-car trains.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=New York City Transit Authority Annual Report For The Year June 30, 1960|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=1960|isbn=|location=|pages=16-17}}</ref> On July 14, 1967, the NYCTA awarded a contract to conduct test borings at eleven stations on the Fourth Avenue Line, including Union Street, to W. M. Walsh Corporation for $6,585 in preparation of the construction of platform extensions.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=HJTVAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22Union+Street,+9th+Street,%22&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=borings+JULY|title=Minutes and Proceedings|date=1967|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=379-380|language=en}}</ref> The NYCTA issued an invitation for bids on the project to extend the platforms at stations along the Fourth Avenue Line between [[Pacific Street station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|Pacific Street]] and [[36th Street station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|36th Street]], including those at Union Street, on March 28, 1969.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=-HNIAQAAIAAJ&dq=Group+XXX%E2%80%94Broadway-Fourth+Avenue+Line:+pacific+Street,+Union+Street,+9th+Street&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Group+XXX|title=Engineering News-record|date=1969|publisher=McGraw-Hill|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=63|language=en}}</ref> The contract was awarded to Horn Construction Company on May 13, 1969 for $7,381,890. Funding for the renovation projects came out of the NYCTA's 1969\u20131970 Capital Budget, costing $8,177,890 in total.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=c-gxGpL_JNQC&dq=%22Pacific+Street+to+36th+Street+stations%22&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=10-car|title=Proceedings of the New York City Transit Authority Relating to Matters Other Than Operation|date=1969|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=280, 435, 487|language=en}}</ref>\n\nAs part of the renovation project, the station's platforms were extended {{Convert|85|feet|meters|abbr=}}<ref name=\":1\" /> to the north,<ref name=\":2\" /> and the station's elaborate mosaic tile walls were covered over with {{convert|8|by|16|in|cm|adj=on}} white cinderblock tiles. The latter change, which was also made to 15 other stations on the [[BMT Broadway Line|BMT Broadway]] and Fourth Avenue Line, was criticized for being dehumanizing. The NYCTA spokesman stated that the old tiles were in poor condition and that the change was made to improve the appearance of stations and provide uniformity. Furthermore, it did not consider the old mosaics to have \"any great artistic merit\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Burks|first=Edward C.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1970/02/21/archives/subways-colored-tile-gets-cover-up-job.html|title=Subways' Colored Tile Gets Cover\u2010Up Job|date=1970-02-21|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-07|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==== 1990s ====\n[[File:Union BMT track.jpg|thumb|175px|The colored tilework forms part of the station art installation|alt=]]\nThe station was renovated again from 1991 to 1994. The $2.397 million contract for the project was awarded on February 28, 1991. During the closure of the Bay Ridge-bound platform, the glazed tiles at the station were heavily defaced with graffiti, and were cleaned prior to the station's reopening with a heavy duty cleaner, which damaged the glazing. A modification to the contract was approved on May 23, 1994. As part of the modification, new graffiti resistant ceramic tile was installed, signage, advertising panels, benches and trash bins were removed and reinstalled, exhaust systems were added in the porter rooms at both platforms, and the wall-mounted conductors board was replaced by a ceiling-mounted one. The modification cost $174,000, and change orders cost $111,004.<ref>{{Cite book|title=NYC Transit Committee Agenda May 1994|date=May 16, 1994|publisher=New York City Transit}}</ref>{{Rp|C-99, C-100}} The Brooklyn-bound platform was closed between July 15 and November 15, 1991,<ref>{{Cite news|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/29284935/daily_news/|title=Attention Brooklyn-Bound N R Subway Riders: Union Street Station Is Closing July 15th to November 15th|last=|first=|date=July 12, 1991|work=New York Daily News|access-date=March 8, 2019}}</ref> while the Manhattan-bound platform was closed between February 19 and June 20, 1992.<ref>{{Cite news|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/29283657/daily_news/|title=Attention N, R Customers: Beginning June 20, 1992: Union Street Station Manhattan-bound platform reopens.|last=|first=|date=June 19, 1992|work=New York Daily News|access-date=March 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/29284140/daily_news/|title=Attention N & R Subway Customers: Union St Manhattan-bound platform is closing February 19th to June 19th.|last=|first=|date=February 18, 1992|work=New York Daily News|access-date=March 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to upgrading the same elements that were replaced in the previous overhaul, floors and track wall tiling, the public announcement system, and safety treads along platform edges and track-beds were replaced. It also included an art installation by Emmett Wigglesworth called ''CommUnion''. It features twenty-two panels of various designs in the recessed area of the platform tiles above the station signs and other designs on the openings in the track walls.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?1167|title=Showing Image 1167|last=Whitehorne|first=Wayne|date=January 15, 2000|website=www.nycsubway.org|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/mta/aft/permanentart/permart.html?agency=n&line=R&station=22|title=Arts for Transit: CommUnion|work=MTA Arts for Transit|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|accessdate=June 2, 2007}}</ref>\n\n==== Proposed accessibility ====\nAs part of the 2015\u20132019 [[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]] Capital Program, $300 million was allocated to enhance station access and provide ADA-accessibility at 15 stations chosen by the city. Four stations were being evaluated for such improvements, including the Union Street station.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BJRM36BCciU|title=MTA Board - NYCT/Bus Committee Meeting - 02/20/2018|date=February 20, 2018|publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|accessdate=March 4, 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/capitaldashboard/allframenew_head.html?PROJNUM=t7160521&PLTYPE=1&DISPLAYALL=Y|title=T7160521 Station Capacity Enhancements at Union Street on the 4 Avenue Line - Design Only|website=mta.info|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref> \n\n{{Clear|left}}\n\n==Station layout==\n{{stack|float=right|\n{{NYCS 4-tracked local station\n|1=Atlantic Avenue\u2013Barclays Center\n|l1=Atlantic Av\n|2=Ninth Street\n|l2=9 St\n|code=BMT Fourth Avenue Line\n|color=yellow\n|textcolor=black\n|deg=330\n}}\n}}\n{{NYCS Platform Layout IND Fulton Street Line}}\n[[File:Union Street BMT Stairs.jpg|thumb|220px|Entrance|alt=]]\nThis underground station has four tracks and two [[side platform]]s.<ref name=\"tracks2\">{{NYCS const|trackref|trackbook}}</ref> The R stops here at all times;<ref name=\"ttr\">{{NYCS const|timetable|r}}</ref> some rush-hour W trains stop here in the peak direction;<ref name=\"ttw\">{{NYCS const|timetable|w}}</ref> and the D and N stop here during late nights, but use the center express tracks to bypass the station during daytime hours.<ref name=\"ttd\">{{NYCS const|timetable|d}}</ref><ref name=\"ttn\">{{NYCS const|timetable|n}}</ref> A white tiled curtain wall separates the express tracks from the local tracks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm3.jpg|title=Looking down the simple Manhattan-bound platform at Union Street.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=December 22, 2008|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nBoth platforms are columnless except for a section at their extreme north ends,<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm3.jpg|title=Looking down the simple Manhattan-bound platform at Union Street.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=December 22, 2008|website=subwaynut.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 7, 2020}}</ref> where they were extended in 1970 to accommodate 10-car trains. Here, the columns are cream colored I-beams. The ceiling is lower in this section.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm6.jpg|title=The ceiling gets extremely low right at the northern end of the station at Union Street.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=December 22, 2008|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nPrior to the station's 1970 renovation, it was finished all in white and marble tile, and it had its own color scheme to allow regular passengers to identify the station based only on the color of the marble trimmings.<ref name=\":10\" /> Since the renovation, the station walls have consisted of white cinderblock tiles, except for small recesses in the walls, which contain gray-painted cinderblock tiles. The gray cinderblock field contains the station-name signs and white text pointing to the exits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm4.jpg|title=A close up of a Union Street station sign on the platform wall, with the 1960s arrow pointing for the exit beneath it.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=December 22, 2008|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Exits===\nEach platform has one same-level [[fare control]] area in the center and there are no crossovers or crossunders to allow free transfer between directions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?122221|title=Bay Ridge-bound fare control|last=Tobar|first=Roberto C.|date=May 20, 2011|website=www.nycsubway.org|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> The Manhattan-bound side has a fare control area, a [[turnstile]] bank, token booth, and two street stairs. The stairs on the Manhattan-bound platform go up to the southeast corner of Union Street and Fourth Avenue while those on the Bay Ridge-bound platform goes up to the southwest corner. The Bay Ridge-bound side has a fare control area, a [[turnstile]] bank without a token booth, and two street stairs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/unionm11.jpg|title=Going down to the now unstaffed Bay Ridge-bound fare control area|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=May 9, 2013|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"MTA-ParkSlopeMap-2015\">{{cite web|title=MTA Neighborhood Maps: Park Slope|url=http://web.mta.info/maps/neighborhoods/bkn/B3_Park_Slope_2015.pdf|website=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority|mta.info]]|publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|accessdate=August 2, 2015|date=2015}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear|left}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|position=right|Union Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)}}\n* {{NYCS ref|http://www.nycsubway.org/perl/stations?216:2870|BMT 4th Avenue|Union Street}}\n* The Subway Nut \u2014 [http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/unionm/index.php Union Street Pictures]\n* MTA's Arts For Transit \u2014 [https://web.archive.org/web/20110606073450/http://mta.info/mta/aft/permanentart/permart.html?agency=nyct&line=M&station=13&xdev=1339 Union Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)]\n* [https://maps.google.com/?ie=UTF8&ll=40.677115,-73.983328&spn=0,359.986567&z=17&lci=transit&layer=c&cbll=40.677228,-73.983256&panoid=21WG-nYiOCICM5t9pabhQg&cbp=12,336.54,,0,3.63 Union Street entrance from Google Maps Street View]\n* [https://www.google.com/maps/@40.6772079,-73.9830475,3a,75y,62.15h,83.78t/data=!3m7!1e1!3m5!1s-51z5J31USnI%2FWG3GwzS1EZI%2FAAAAAAAAYTo%2FRqvXDLDF-hww1DY9gHkftwOWZaiTYALUQCLIB!2e4!6s%2F%2Flh4.googleusercontent.com%2F-51z5J31USnI%2FWG3GwzS1EZI%2FAAAAAAAAYTo%2FRqvXDLDF-hww1DY9gHkftwOWZaiTYALUQCLIB%2Fw203-h100-p-k-no%2F!7i7168!8i3584!4m3!8m2!3m1!1e1 Platform from Google Maps Street View]\n\n{{NYCS stations navbox by service|lr=y}}\n{{NYCS stations navbox by line|4ave=yes}}\n\n[[Category:BMT Fourth Avenue Line stations]]\n[[Category:New York City Subway stations in Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1915]]\n[[Category:1915 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Park Slope]]\n[[Category:New York City Subway stations located underground]]\n", "name_user": "Epicgenius", "label": "safe", "comment": "add inflation templates, fix grammar and other issues", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Union_Street_station_(BMT_Fourth_Avenue_Line)"}
{"title_page": "HTTP 404", "text_new": "{{Redirect|404 Not Found|the TV episode|404 Not Found (Mr. Robot)}}\n{{short description|HTTP status code indicating that the resource was not found}}\n{{HTTP}}{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\nThe '''HTTP 404''', '''404 Not Found''', '''404''', '''Page Not Found''', or '''Server Not Found''' [[error message]] is a [[Hypertext Transfer Protocol]] (HTTP) [[List of HTTP status codes|standard response code]], in computer network communications, to indicate that the [[Web browser|browser]] was able to communicate with a given [[Server (computing)|server]], but the server could not find what was requested. The error may also be used when a server does not wish to disclose whether it has the requested information or not.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.4|title=RFC 7231, HTTP/1.1 Semantics and Content, Section 6.5.4 404 Not Found|publisher=ietf.org|date=June 2014|accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref>\n\nThe website hosting server will typically generate a \"404 Not Found\" web page when a user attempts to follow a [[link rot|broken or dead link]]; hence the 404 error is one of the most recognizable errors encountered on the [[World Wide Web]].\n\n==Overview==\n\nWhen communicating via HTTP, a server is required to respond to a request, such as a [[web browser]] request for a [[web page]], with a numeric response code and an optional, mandatory, or disallowed (based upon the status code) message. In the code 404, the first digit indicates a client error, such as a mistyped [[Uniform Resource Locator]] (URL). The following two digits indicate the specific error encountered. HTTP's use of three-digit codes is similar to the use of such codes in earlier protocols such as [[File Transfer Protocol|FTP]] and [[Network News Transfer Protocol|NNTP]]. At the HTTP level, a 404 response code is followed by a human-readable \"reason phrase\". The HTTP specification suggests the phrase \"Not Found\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.4|title=RFC 7231, HTTP/1.1 Semantics and Content, Section 6.5.4 404 Not Found|publisher=ietf.org|date=June 2014|accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> and many web servers by default issue an HTML page that includes both the 404 code and the \"Not Found\" phrase.\n\nA 404 error is often returned when pages have been moved or deleted. In the first case, it is better to employ [[URL mapping]] or [[URL redirection]] by returning a 301 Moved Permanently response, which can be configured in most server configuration files, or through [[URL rewriting]]; in the second case, a 410 Gone should be returned. Because these two options require special server configuration, most websites do not make use of them.\n\n404 errors should not be confused with [[Domain Name System|DNS]] errors, which appear when the given URL refers to a server name that does not exist. A 404 error indicates that the server itself was found, but that the server was not able to retrieve the requested page.\n\n==Soft 404 errors==\n{{anchor|Soft 404}}\n\nSome websites report a \"not found\" error by returning a standard web page with a \"200 OK\" response code, falsely reporting that the page loaded properly; this is known as a ''soft 404''. The term \"soft 404\" was introduced in 2004 by Ziv Bar-Yossef ''et al''.\u044e\u0439\u0445\u0439\u0431\u043c\u043d <ref>{{Cite book |title=Sic Transit Gloria Telae: Towards an Understanding of the Web's Decay |journal=Proceedings of the 13th International Conference on World Wide Web (WWW) |author1=Ziv Bar-Yossef |author2=Andrei Z. Broder |author3=Ravi Kumar |author4=Andrew Tompkins |date=2004 |volume= |number= |pages=328\u2013337 |doi=10.1145/988672.988716 |isbn=978-1581138443 }}</ref>\n\nSoft 404s are problematic for automated methods of discovering whether a link is broken. Some search engines, like Yahoo and Google, use automated processes to detect soft 404s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://help.yahoo.com/l/nl/yahoo/ysearch/slurp/slurp-10.html |title=Why is your crawler asking for strange URLs that have never existed on my site? |publisher=Yahoo Ysearch Help page |accessdate=4 September 2013}}</ref> Soft 404s can occur as a result of configuration errors when using certain HTTP server software, for example with the [[Apache HTTP Server|Apache]] software, when an Error Document 404 (specified in a [[.htaccess]] file) is specified as an absolute path (e.g. <nowiki>http://example.com/error.html</nowiki>) rather than a relative path (/error.html).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://googlewebmastercentral.blogspot.com/2008/08/farewell-to-soft-404s.html|title=Farewell to soft 404s |publisher=Google Official Blog|accessdate=20 September 2008}}</ref> This can also be done on purpose to force some browsers (like [[Internet Explorer]]) to display a customized 404 error message rather than replacing what is served with a browser-specific \"friendly\" error message (in Internet Explorer, this behavior is triggered when a 404 is served and the received HTML is shorter than a certain length, and can be manually disabled by the user).\n\nThere are also \"soft 3XX\" errors where content is returned with a status 200 but it comes from a redirected page, such as when missing pages are redirected to the domain root/home page.\n\n=== Proxy servers ===\nSome [[proxy server]]s generate a 404 error when a [[List of HTTP status codes#List of HTTP status codes|500-range error code]] would be more correct. If the proxy server is unable to satisfy a request for a page because of a problem with the remote host (such as hostname resolution failures or refused TCP connections), this should be described as a 5xx Internal Server Error, but might deliver a 404 instead. This can confuse programs that expect and act on specific responses, as they can no longer easily distinguish between an absent web server and a missing web page on a web server that is present.\n\n=== Intentional 404s ===\nIn July 2004, the UK telecom provider [[BT Group]] deployed the [[Cleanfeed (content blocking system)|Cleanfeed]] content blocking system, which returns a 404 error to any request for content identified as potentially illegal by the [[Internet Watch Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://publicaffairs.linx.net/news/?p=154 |title=LINX Public Affairs \u00bb Cleanfeed: the facts |publisher=Publicaffairs.linx.net |date=10 September 2004 |accessdate=6 March 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513071912/https://publicaffairs.linx.net/news/?p=154 |archive-date=13 May 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Other ISPs return a [[HTTP 403]] \"forbidden\" error in the same circumstances.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://airbrake.io/blog/http-errors/403-forbidden-error|title=DEMON \u2013 Error 403|accessdate=14 June 2012}}</ref> The practice of employing fake 404 errors as a means to conceal [[censorship]] has also been reported in [[Thailand]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/tech/technews/11872/the-old-fake-404-not-found-routine |title=The old fake '404 Not Found' routine |newspaper =Bangkok Post |date=18 February 2009 | first = Don | last = Sambandaraksa |accessdate=12 September 2010}}</ref> and [[Tunisia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://opennet.net/node/950 |title=Tunisian journalist sues government agency for blocking Facebook, claims damage for the use of 404 error message instead of 403 |first=Helmi |last=Noman |date=12 September 2008 |publisher= Open Net Initiative |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> In Tunisia, where censorship was severe before the [[Tunisian Revolution|2011 revolution]], people became aware of the nature of the fake 404 errors and created an imaginary character named \"[[Ammar 404#Censorship during the Ben Ali regime|Ammar 404]]\" who represents \"the invisible censor\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://advocacy.globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/27/anti-censorship-movement-in-tunisia-creativity-courage-and-hope/ |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120707/http://advocacy.globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/27/anti-censorship-movement-in-tunisia-creativity-courage-and-hope/ |archivedate=7 July 2012 |title=Anti-censorship movement in Tunisia: creativity, courage and hope! |publisher=Global Voices Advocacy |date=27 May 2010 |accessdate=28 August 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Microsoft Internet Server 404 substatus error codes==\nThe webserver software developed by Microsoft, [[Internet Information Services|Microsoft's Internet Information Services]] (IIS), returns a set of substatus codes with its 404 responses. The substatus codes take the form of decimal numbers appended to the 404 status code. The substatus codes are not officially recognized by [[Internet Assigned Numbers Authority|IANA]] and are not returned by non-Microsoft servers.\n\n===Substatus codes===\n[[File:404 Store Not Found.jpg|thumb|right|300px|A laundry in the Fenway neighborhood of Boston using humor to show a business is closed.]]\nMicrosoft's IIS 7.0, IIS 7.5, and IIS 8.0 servers define the following HTTP substatus codes to indicate a more specific cause of a 404 error:\n\n* 404.0   \u2013 Not found.\n* 404.1   \u2013 Site Not Found.\n* 404.2   \u2013 [[ISAPI]] or [[Common Gateway Interface|CGI]] restriction.\n* 404.3   \u2013 [[MIME]] type restriction.\n* 404.4   \u2013 No handler configured.\n* 404.5   \u2013 Denied by request filtering configuration.\n* 404.6   \u2013 Verb denied.\n* 404.7   \u2013 File extension denied.\n* 404.8   \u2013 Hidden namespace.\n* 404.9   \u2013 File attribute hidden.\n* 404.10 \u2013 Request header too long.\n* 404.11 \u2013 Request contains double escape sequence.\n* 404.12 \u2013 Request contains high-bit characters.\n* 404.13 \u2013 Content length too large.\n* 404.14 \u2013 Request URL too long.\n* 404.15 \u2013 Query string too long.\n* 404.16 \u2013 DAV request sent to the static file handler.\n* 404.17 \u2013 Dynamic content mapped to the static file handler via a wildcard MIME mapping.\n* 404.18 \u2013 Query string sequence denied.\n* 404.19 \u2013 Denied by filtering rule.\n* 404.20 \u2013 Too Many URL Segments.\n\n==Custom error pages==\n[[File:Wikimedia error 404.png|thumb|The Wikimedia 404 message]]\n\n[[Web server]]s can typically be configured to display a customised 404 error page, including a more natural description, the parent site's branding, and sometimes a site map, a search form or 404 page widget. The protocol level phrase, which is hidden from the user, is rarely customized. [[Internet Explorer]], however, will not display custom pages unless they are larger than 512 bytes, opting instead to display a \"friendly\" error page.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.msdn.com/b/ieinternals/archive/2010/08/19/http-error-pages-in-internet-explorer.aspx|title=Friendly HTTP Error Pages|date=18 August 2010|publisher=msdn.com|accessdate=14 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101202044514/http://blogs.msdn.com/b/ieinternals/archive/2010/08/19/http-error-pages-in-internet-explorer.aspx|archive-date=2 December 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Google Chrome]] included similar functionality, where the 404 is replaced with alternative suggestions generated by Google algorithms, if the page is under 512 bytes in size.{{Citation needed|date=January 2013}} Another problem is that if the page does not provide a [[favicon]], and a separate custom 404 page exists, extra traffic and longer loading times will be generated on every page view.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thesitewizard.com/archive/favicon.shtml|title=What is Favicon.ico and How to Create a Favicon Icon for Your Website|last=Heng|first=Christopher|date=7 September 2008|website=The Site Wizard|accessdate=23 February 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://internetfolks.com/dastardly-favicon-ico-found-error/|title=The Dastardly \"favicon.ico not found\" Error|date=3 August 1999|work=Internet Folks}}</ref>\n\nMany organizations use 404 error pages as an opportunity to inject humor into what may otherwise be a serious website. For example, Metro UK shows a polar bear on a skateboard, and the web development agency Left Logic has a simple drawing program.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2013/04/16/from-skateboarding-bears-to-missing-children-the-power-of-the-404-not-found-error-page-3591031/|title=From skateboarding bears to missing children: The power of the 404 Not Found error page|date=6 June 2011|accessdate=16 April 2013|publisher=Metro}}</ref> During the [[2015 United Kingdom general election|2015 UK general election]] campaign the main political parties all used their 404 pages to either take aim at political opponents or show relevant policies to potential supporters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/32480181/the-political-page-404-war|title=The political Page 404 war|date=27 April 2015|website=BBC Newsbeat|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref> In Europe, the [[NotFound project]], created by multiple European organizations including [[Missing Children Europe]] and [[Child Focus]], encourages site operators to add a [[Snippet (programming)|snippet of code]] to serve customised 404 error pages<ref>{{cite web|url=http://notfound.org/notfound|title=Notfound.org|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902081543/http://notfound.org/notfound|archivedate=2 September 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> which provide data about [[missing children]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-19741350|title=Missing children messages go on 404 error pages|date=27 September 2012|work=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=20 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nWhile many websites send additional information in a 404 error message\u2014such as a link to the [[homepage]] of a website or a search box\u2014some also endeavor to find the correct web page the user wanted. Extensions are available for some [[content management system]]s  (CMSs) to do this.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://googlewebmastercentral.blogspot.com/2008/08/make-your-404-pages-more-useful.html|title=Make your 404 pages more useful|last=Swenson|first=Sahala|date=19 August 2008|work=Official Google Webmaster Central Blog|publisher=Google, Inc|accessdate=28 August 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Tracking 404 errors==\nA number of tools exist that crawl through a website to find pages that return 404 status codes. These tools can be helpful in finding links that exist within a particular website. The limitation of these tools is that they only find links within one particular website, and ignore 404s resulting from links on other websites. As a result, these tools miss out on 83% of the 404s on websites.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://springtrax.com/key-stats-about-404-errors/default.htm#/section4|title=Sources Leading To 404s|publisher=SpringTrax|accessdate=11 February 2013}}</ref> One way around this is to find 404 errors by analyzing external links.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://searchengineland.com/a-data-centric-approach-to-identifying-404-pages-worth-saving-152844|title=A Data-Centric Approach To Identifying 404 Pages Worth Saving|last=Cushing|first=Anne|date=2 April 2013|publisher=Search Engine Land|accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nAnother common method is tracking traffic to 404 pages using log file analysis.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.404errorpages.com/#tracking|title=Tracking and Preventing 404 Errors|publisher=404errorpages.com|accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref> This can be useful to understand more about what 404s users reached on the site. Another method of tracking traffic to 404 pages is using JavaScript-based traffic tracking tools.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://springtrax.com/how-springtrax-helps/understand-your-websites-404-errors.htm|title=Understand 404 Errors|publisher=SpringTrax.com|accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Internet|Computer programming}}\n* [[Blue screen of death]]\n* [[Funky caching]]\n* [[Link rot]]\n* [[List of HTTP status codes]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://alistapart.com/article/amoreuseful404 A More Useful 404]\n* [http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.4 404 Not Found] of the ''Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP/1.1): Semantics and [[Content delivery network|Content]]'' specification, at the [[Internet Engineering Task Force]]\n* [http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/core.html#errordocument ErrorDocument Directive]&nbsp;\u2013 instructions on custom error pages for the [[Apache HTTP Server|Apache 2.0 web server]]\n* [http://www.ovff.org/pegasus/songs/404-not-found.html 404: Not Found]&nbsp;\u2013 an award-winning song about the error code\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2011}}\n\n{{Error messages}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Http 404}}\n[[Category:Computer errors]]\n[[Category:Hypertext Transfer Protocol status codes]]\n[[Category:Internet terminology]]\n", "text_old": "{{Redirect|404 Not Found|the TV episode|404 Not Found (Mr. Robot)}}\n{{short description|HTTP status code indicating that the resource was not found}}\n{{HTTP}}{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\nThe '''HTTP 404''', '''404 Not Found''', '''404''', '''Page Not Found''', or '''Server Not Found''' [[error message]] is a [[Hypertext Transfer Protocol]] (HTTP) [[List of HTTP status codes|standard response code]], in computer network communications, to indicate that the [[Web browser|browser]] was able to communicate with a given [[Server (computing)|server]], but the server could not find what was requested. The error may also be used when a server does not wish to disclose whether it has the requested information or not.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.4|title=RFC 7231, HTTP/1.1 Semantics and Content, Section 6.5.4 404 Not Found|publisher=ietf.org|date=June 2014|accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref>\n\nThe website hosting server will typically generate a \"404 Not Found\" web page when a user attempts to follow a [[link rot|broken or dead link]]; hence the 404 error is one of the most recognizable errors encountered on the [[World Wide Web]].\n\n==Overview==\n\nWhen communicating via HTTP, a server is required to respond to a request, such as a [[web browser]] request for a [[web page]], with a numeric response code and an optional, mandatory, or disallowed (based upon the status code) message. In the code 404, the first digit indicates a client error, such as a mistyped [[Uniform Resource Locator]] (URL). The following two digits indicate the specific error encountered. HTTP's use of three-digit codes is similar to the use of such codes in earlier protocols such as [[File Transfer Protocol|FTP]] and [[Network News Transfer Protocol|NNTP]]. At the HTTP level, a 404 response code is followed by a human-readable \"reason phrase\". The HTTP specification suggests the phrase \"Not Found\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.4|title=RFC 7231, HTTP/1.1 Semantics and Content, Section 6.5.4 404 Not Found|publisher=ietf.org|date=June 2014|accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> and many web servers by default issue an HTML page that includes both the 404 code and the \"Not Found\" phrase.\n\nA 404 error is often returned when pages have been moved or deleted. In the first case, it is better to employ [[URL mapping]] or [[URL redirection]] by returning a 301 Moved Permanently response, which can be configured in most server configuration files, or through [[URL rewriting]]; in the second case, a 410 Gone should be returned. Because these two options require special server configuration, most websites do not make use of them.\n\n404 errors should not be confused with [[Domain Name System|DNS]] errors, which appear when the given URL refers to a server name that does not exist. A 404 error indicates that the server itself was found, but that the server was not able to retrieve the requested page.\n\n==Soft 404 errors==\n{{anchor|Soft 404}}\n\nSome websites report a \"not found\" error by returning a standard web page with a \"200 OK\" response code, falsely reporting that the page loaded properly; this is known as a ''soft 404''. The term \"soft 404\" was introduced in 2004 by Ziv Bar-Yossef ''et al''.<ref>{{Cite book |title=Sic Transit Gloria Telae: Towards an Understanding of the Web's Decay |journal=Proceedings of the 13th International Conference on World Wide Web (WWW) |author1=Ziv Bar-Yossef |author2=Andrei Z. Broder |author3=Ravi Kumar |author4=Andrew Tompkins |date=2004 |volume= |number= |pages=328\u2013337 |doi=10.1145/988672.988716 |isbn=978-1581138443 }}</ref>\n\nSoft 404s are problematic for automated methods of discovering whether a link is broken. Some search engines, like Yahoo and Google, use automated processes to detect soft 404s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://help.yahoo.com/l/nl/yahoo/ysearch/slurp/slurp-10.html |title=Why is your crawler asking for strange URLs that have never existed on my site? |publisher=Yahoo Ysearch Help page |accessdate=4 September 2013}}</ref> Soft 404s can occur as a result of configuration errors when using certain HTTP server software, for example with the [[Apache HTTP Server|Apache]] software, when an Error Document 404 (specified in a [[.htaccess]] file) is specified as an absolute path (e.g. <nowiki>http://example.com/error.html</nowiki>) rather than a relative path (/error.html).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://googlewebmastercentral.blogspot.com/2008/08/farewell-to-soft-404s.html|title=Farewell to soft 404s |publisher=Google Official Blog|accessdate=20 September 2008}}</ref> This can also be done on purpose to force some browsers (like [[Internet Explorer]]) to display a customized 404 error message rather than replacing what is served with a browser-specific \"friendly\" error message (in Internet Explorer, this behavior is triggered when a 404 is served and the received HTML is shorter than a certain length, and can be manually disabled by the user).\n\nThere are also \"soft 3XX\" errors where content is returned with a status 200 but it comes from a redirected page, such as when missing pages are redirected to the domain root/home page.\n\n=== Proxy servers ===\nSome [[proxy server]]s generate a 404 error when a [[List of HTTP status codes#List of HTTP status codes|500-range error code]] would be more correct. If the proxy server is unable to satisfy a request for a page because of a problem with the remote host (such as hostname resolution failures or refused TCP connections), this should be described as a 5xx Internal Server Error, but might deliver a 404 instead. This can confuse programs that expect and act on specific responses, as they can no longer easily distinguish between an absent web server and a missing web page on a web server that is present.\n\n=== Intentional 404s ===\nIn July 2004, the UK telecom provider [[BT Group]] deployed the [[Cleanfeed (content blocking system)|Cleanfeed]] content blocking system, which returns a 404 error to any request for content identified as potentially illegal by the [[Internet Watch Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://publicaffairs.linx.net/news/?p=154 |title=LINX Public Affairs \u00bb Cleanfeed: the facts |publisher=Publicaffairs.linx.net |date=10 September 2004 |accessdate=6 March 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513071912/https://publicaffairs.linx.net/news/?p=154 |archive-date=13 May 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Other ISPs return a [[HTTP 403]] \"forbidden\" error in the same circumstances.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://airbrake.io/blog/http-errors/403-forbidden-error|title=DEMON \u2013 Error 403|accessdate=14 June 2012}}</ref> The practice of employing fake 404 errors as a means to conceal [[censorship]] has also been reported in [[Thailand]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/tech/technews/11872/the-old-fake-404-not-found-routine |title=The old fake '404 Not Found' routine |newspaper =Bangkok Post |date=18 February 2009 | first = Don | last = Sambandaraksa |accessdate=12 September 2010}}</ref> and [[Tunisia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://opennet.net/node/950 |title=Tunisian journalist sues government agency for blocking Facebook, claims damage for the use of 404 error message instead of 403 |first=Helmi |last=Noman |date=12 September 2008 |publisher= Open Net Initiative |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> In Tunisia, where censorship was severe before the [[Tunisian Revolution|2011 revolution]], people became aware of the nature of the fake 404 errors and created an imaginary character named \"[[Ammar 404#Censorship during the Ben Ali regime|Ammar 404]]\" who represents \"the invisible censor\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://advocacy.globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/27/anti-censorship-movement-in-tunisia-creativity-courage-and-hope/ |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120707/http://advocacy.globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/27/anti-censorship-movement-in-tunisia-creativity-courage-and-hope/ |archivedate=7 July 2012 |title=Anti-censorship movement in Tunisia: creativity, courage and hope! |publisher=Global Voices Advocacy |date=27 May 2010 |accessdate=28 August 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Microsoft Internet Server 404 substatus error codes==\nThe webserver software developed by Microsoft, [[Internet Information Services|Microsoft's Internet Information Services]] (IIS), returns a set of substatus codes with its 404 responses. The substatus codes take the form of decimal numbers appended to the 404 status code. The substatus codes are not officially recognized by [[Internet Assigned Numbers Authority|IANA]] and are not returned by non-Microsoft servers.\n\n===Substatus codes===\n[[File:404 Store Not Found.jpg|thumb|right|300px|A laundry in the Fenway neighborhood of Boston using humor to show a business is closed.]]\nMicrosoft's IIS 7.0, IIS 7.5, and IIS 8.0 servers define the following HTTP substatus codes to indicate a more specific cause of a 404 error:\n\n* 404.0   \u2013 Not found.\n* 404.1   \u2013 Site Not Found.\n* 404.2   \u2013 [[ISAPI]] or [[Common Gateway Interface|CGI]] restriction.\n* 404.3   \u2013 [[MIME]] type restriction.\n* 404.4   \u2013 No handler configured.\n* 404.5   \u2013 Denied by request filtering configuration.\n* 404.6   \u2013 Verb denied.\n* 404.7   \u2013 File extension denied.\n* 404.8   \u2013 Hidden namespace.\n* 404.9   \u2013 File attribute hidden.\n* 404.10 \u2013 Request header too long.\n* 404.11 \u2013 Request contains double escape sequence.\n* 404.12 \u2013 Request contains high-bit characters.\n* 404.13 \u2013 Content length too large.\n* 404.14 \u2013 Request URL too long.\n* 404.15 \u2013 Query string too long.\n* 404.16 \u2013 DAV request sent to the static file handler.\n* 404.17 \u2013 Dynamic content mapped to the static file handler via a wildcard MIME mapping.\n* 404.18 \u2013 Query string sequence denied.\n* 404.19 \u2013 Denied by filtering rule.\n* 404.20 \u2013 Too Many URL Segments.\n\n==Custom error pages==\n[[File:Wikimedia error 404.png|thumb|The Wikimedia 404 message]]\n\n[[Web server]]s can typically be configured to display a customised 404 error page, including a more natural description, the parent site's branding, and sometimes a site map, a search form or 404 page widget. The protocol level phrase, which is hidden from the user, is rarely customized. [[Internet Explorer]], however, will not display custom pages unless they are larger than 512 bytes, opting instead to display a \"friendly\" error page.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.msdn.com/b/ieinternals/archive/2010/08/19/http-error-pages-in-internet-explorer.aspx|title=Friendly HTTP Error Pages|date=18 August 2010|publisher=msdn.com|accessdate=14 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101202044514/http://blogs.msdn.com/b/ieinternals/archive/2010/08/19/http-error-pages-in-internet-explorer.aspx|archive-date=2 December 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Google Chrome]] included similar functionality, where the 404 is replaced with alternative suggestions generated by Google algorithms, if the page is under 512 bytes in size.{{Citation needed|date=January 2013}} Another problem is that if the page does not provide a [[favicon]], and a separate custom 404 page exists, extra traffic and longer loading times will be generated on every page view.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thesitewizard.com/archive/favicon.shtml|title=What is Favicon.ico and How to Create a Favicon Icon for Your Website|last=Heng|first=Christopher|date=7 September 2008|website=The Site Wizard|accessdate=23 February 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://internetfolks.com/dastardly-favicon-ico-found-error/|title=The Dastardly \"favicon.ico not found\" Error|date=3 August 1999|work=Internet Folks}}</ref>\n\nMany organizations use 404 error pages as an opportunity to inject humor into what may otherwise be a serious website. For example, Metro UK shows a polar bear on a skateboard, and the web development agency Left Logic has a simple drawing program.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2013/04/16/from-skateboarding-bears-to-missing-children-the-power-of-the-404-not-found-error-page-3591031/|title=From skateboarding bears to missing children: The power of the 404 Not Found error page|date=6 June 2011|accessdate=16 April 2013|publisher=Metro}}</ref> During the [[2015 United Kingdom general election|2015 UK general election]] campaign the main political parties all used their 404 pages to either take aim at political opponents or show relevant policies to potential supporters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/32480181/the-political-page-404-war|title=The political Page 404 war|date=27 April 2015|website=BBC Newsbeat|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref> In Europe, the [[NotFound project]], created by multiple European organizations including [[Missing Children Europe]] and [[Child Focus]], encourages site operators to add a [[Snippet (programming)|snippet of code]] to serve customised 404 error pages<ref>{{cite web|url=http://notfound.org/notfound|title=Notfound.org|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902081543/http://notfound.org/notfound|archivedate=2 September 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> which provide data about [[missing children]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-19741350|title=Missing children messages go on 404 error pages|date=27 September 2012|work=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=20 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nWhile many websites send additional information in a 404 error message\u2014such as a link to the [[homepage]] of a website or a search box\u2014some also endeavor to find the correct web page the user wanted. Extensions are available for some [[content management system]]s  (CMSs) to do this.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://googlewebmastercentral.blogspot.com/2008/08/make-your-404-pages-more-useful.html|title=Make your 404 pages more useful|last=Swenson|first=Sahala|date=19 August 2008|work=Official Google Webmaster Central Blog|publisher=Google, Inc|accessdate=28 August 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Tracking 404 errors==\nA number of tools exist that crawl through a website to find pages that return 404 status codes. These tools can be helpful in finding links that exist within a particular website. The limitation of these tools is that they only find links within one particular website, and ignore 404s resulting from links on other websites. As a result, these tools miss out on 83% of the 404s on websites.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://springtrax.com/key-stats-about-404-errors/default.htm#/section4|title=Sources Leading To 404s|publisher=SpringTrax|accessdate=11 February 2013}}</ref> One way around this is to find 404 errors by analyzing external links.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://searchengineland.com/a-data-centric-approach-to-identifying-404-pages-worth-saving-152844|title=A Data-Centric Approach To Identifying 404 Pages Worth Saving|last=Cushing|first=Anne|date=2 April 2013|publisher=Search Engine Land|accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nAnother common method is tracking traffic to 404 pages using log file analysis.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.404errorpages.com/#tracking|title=Tracking and Preventing 404 Errors|publisher=404errorpages.com|accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref> This can be useful to understand more about what 404s users reached on the site. Another method of tracking traffic to 404 pages is using JavaScript-based traffic tracking tools.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://springtrax.com/how-springtrax-helps/understand-your-websites-404-errors.htm|title=Understand 404 Errors|publisher=SpringTrax.com|accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Internet|Computer programming}}\n* [[Blue screen of death]]\n* [[Funky caching]]\n* [[Link rot]]\n* [[List of HTTP status codes]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://alistapart.com/article/amoreuseful404 A More Useful 404]\n* [http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.4 404 Not Found] of the ''Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP/1.1): Semantics and [[Content delivery network|Content]]'' specification, at the [[Internet Engineering Task Force]]\n* [http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/core.html#errordocument ErrorDocument Directive]&nbsp;\u2013 instructions on custom error pages for the [[Apache HTTP Server|Apache 2.0 web server]]\n* [http://www.ovff.org/pegasus/songs/404-not-found.html 404: Not Found]&nbsp;\u2013 an award-winning song about the error code\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2011}}\n\n{{Error messages}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Http 404}}\n[[Category:Computer errors]]\n[[Category:Hypertext Transfer Protocol status codes]]\n[[Category:Internet terminology]]\n", "name_user": "79.100.105.250", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eSoft 404 errors)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP_404"}
{"title_page": "Prospect Avenue station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Prospect Avenue (IRT White Plains Road Line)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Short description|New York City Subway station in Brooklyn}}\n{{Infobox NYCS\n| name = Prospect Avenue\n| font_color = black\n| font_color_2 = white\n| bg_color = #FFC800\n| bg_color_2 = #874F17\n| image = File:NYCT 8692 (38090305082).jpg\n| image_caption =Southbound platform\n| address = Prospect Avenue &amp; Fourth Avenue<br>Brooklyn, NY 11215<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.nyc.gov/assets/doh/downloads/pdf/epi/Brooklyn|title=Borough of Brooklyn, New York City|publisher=[[Government of New York City]]|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| borough = [[Brooklyn]]\n| locale = [[Gowanus, Brooklyn|Gowanus]], [[Greenwood Heights, Brooklyn|Greenwood Heights]], [[Park Slope]], [[South Park Slope]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|40.666789|N|73.994079|W|display=inline,title}}\n| lat_dir = N\n| lon_dir = W\n| division = BMT\n| line = [[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]]\n| service = Fourth center local\n| service_header = Fourth center local header\n| connection = {{Bus icon}} '''[[NYCT Bus]]''': {{NYC bus link|B37}} <small>(on [[Third Avenue (Brooklyn)|Third Avenue]])</small>; {{NYC bus link|B63}} <small>(on Fifth Avenue)</small><ref>{{cite NYC bus map|B}}</ref>\n| code = 030\n| platforms = 2 [[side platform]]s\n| tracks = 4\n| structure = Underground\n| wifi = yes\n| open_date = {{start date and age|June 22, 1915}}<ref name=\"Station Opening\" />\n| close_date = {{start date and age|2017|6|5}} (reconstruction)\n| rebuilt = {{start date and age|2017|11|2}}\n| passengers = 1,638,002<ref name=\"ridership\">{{NYCS const|riderref}}</ref>\n| pass_year = 2018\n| pass_percent = 70.3\n| rank = 275<ref name=\"ridership\"/>\n| next_north = {{NYCS next | station=Ninth Street | line=BMT Fourth Avenue Line | service= Fourth center local}}\n| next_south = {{NYCS next | station=25th Street | line=BMT Fourth Avenue Line | service= Fourth center local}}\n| legend = {{NYCS infobox legend|allexceptnights}}{{NYCS infobox legend|nightsonly}}{{NYCS infobox legend|rushonly}}{{NYCS infobox legend|rushpeak}}\n}}\n\n'''Prospect Avenue''' is a local [[New York City Subway]] [[metro station|station]] on the [[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]] in [[Brooklyn]]. It is located at Prospect Avenue and Fourth Avenue near the convergence of the [[Gowanus, Brooklyn|Gowanus]], [[Greenwood Heights, Brooklyn|Greenwood Heights]], [[Park Slope]], and [[South Park Slope]] neighborhoods. It is served by the [[R (New York City Subway service)|R]] train at all times. The [[D (New York City Subway service)|D]] and [[N (New York City Subway service)|N]] trains also stop here during late nights, and some rush-hour [[W (New York City Subway service)|W]] trains stop here in the peak direction.\n\nThe Prospect Avenue station was constructed as part of the Fourth Avenue Line, which was approved in 1905. Construction on the segment of the line that includes Prospect Avenue started on December 20, 1909, and was completed in May 1912. The station opened on June 22, 1915 as part of the initial portion of the BMT Fourth Avenue Line to [[59th Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|59th Street]]. The station's platforms were lengthened in 1925, and again in 1970. The station was also renovated in 1970 and 2017.\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Prospect Av station before renewal (38060731396).jpg|thumb|left|The station prior to renovation]]\n\n=== Construction ===\nThe Prospect Avenue station was constructed as part of the Fourth Avenue Line, the plan for which was initially adopted on June 1, 1905.<ref name=\":123\">{{Cite journal|last=Rogoff|first=David|date=May 1961|title=The Fourth Ave. Subway|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzKvSWhrQBW4d3pvOGZaSERiZEhpQ24xT19DTktkQUVlLW5j/view|journal=New York Division Bulletin|publisher=Electric Railroaders' Association|volume=|pages=2\u201310|access-date=May 8, 2017|via=}}</ref> The Rapid Transit Commission was succeeded on July 1, 1907, by the [[New York Public Service Commission|New York State Public Service Commission]] (PSC), which approved the plan for the line in late 1907.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/?id=XoxBAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA18&dq=4th+Avenue+line#v=onepage&q=4th%20Avenue%20line&f=false|page=18|title=Fourth Avenue Subway, Brooklyn's New Transportation Line: A Part of the Dual System of Rapid Transit of the City of New York|date=June 19, 1915|publisher=Public Service Commission|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":11\">{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48901678/|title=Fourth Avenue Subway Is Sent To A Committee|date=March 20, 1908|work=The Brooklyn Daily Eagle|access-date=May 4, 2017|pages=1\u20132|language=en}}</ref> The contract for the section of the line that included the Prospect Avenue station, Route 11A3, which extended from 10th Street to 27th Street, was awarded on May 22, 1908, and approved by the [[New York City Board of Estimate]] on October 29, 1909.<ref name=\":10\" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://bklyn.newspapers.com/image/53922207/|title=Fourth Avenue Subway To Be Political Issue|date=December 11, 1908|work=The Brooklyn Daily Eagle|access-date=May 4, 2017|page=1|language=en}}</ref> Construction on the segment started on December 20, 1909, and was completed in May 1912.<ref name=\":123\"/>\n\nAs part of negotiations between New York City, the [[Brooklyn Rapid Transit Company]] (BRT), and the [[Interborough Rapid Transit Company]] for the expansion of the city's transit network, the line was leased to a subsidiary of the BRT. The agreement, known as Contract 4 of the [[Dual Contracts]], was signed on March 19, 1913.<ref name=\":10\" /> Prospect Avenue opened on June 22, 1915 as part of the initial portion of the Fourth Avenue Line to [[59th Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|59th Street]].<ref name=\"Station Opening\">{{cite web|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48814840/|title=Through Tube to Coney, 48 Minutes: First Train on Fourth Avenue Route Beats West End Line Eleven Minutes|date=June 22, 1915|publisher=[[Brooklyn Daily Eagle]]|accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Renovations ===\n\n==== 1920s ====\nOn June 27, 1922, the New York State Transit Commission directed its engineers to prepare plans to lengthen the platforms at 23 stations on the lines of the [[Brooklyn\u2013Manhattan Transit Corporation]] (BMT), the successor to the BRT, to accommodate eight-car trains. As part of the project, Prospect Avenue's platforms would have been lengthened from {{Convert|435|feet|meters}} to {{Convert|530|feet|meters}}.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Legislature|first=New York (State)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-ugaAQAAIAAJ&pg=RA3-PA100&dq=%22union+street%22+LENGTHENING&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj8_PLm7tboAhXBhOAKHVx0AzwQ6AEwA3oECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=%22union%20street%22%20LENGTHENING&f=false|title=Second Annual Report of the Transit Commission (For the Calendar Year 1922)|date=1923|publisher=New York State Transit Commission|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=100|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u5kT80_w6rYC&pg=PA1277&dq=%22union+street%22+%22530+feet%22&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjngqLU7dboAhVLTt8KHapMD8IQ6AEwCHoECAkQAg#v=onepage&q=%22union%20street%22%20%22530%20feet%22&f=false|title=Proceedings of the Transit Commission, State of New York Volume III From January 1 to December 31, 1923|date=1923|publisher=New York State Transit Commission|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=1277|language=en}}</ref> On February 16, 1925, the [[New York City Board of Transportation]] (NYCBOT) directed its engineers to prepare plans to lengthen the platforms at this and eleven other stations along the Fourth Avenue Line. It estimated the project's cost to be $633,000 ({{inflation|fmt=eq|index=US|value=633000|year=1925|r=-3}}). The BMT had been ordered by the Transit Commission to lengthen these platforms since September 1923.<ref name=\":02\">{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1925/02/17/archives/12-bm-t-stations-to-be-lengthehed-transportation-board-orders.html|title=12 B-M. T. Stations To Be Lengthened; Transportation Board Orders Engineers to Prepare Contracts for Brooklyn Work. Cost Put At $633,000 ({{inflation|fmt=eq|index=US|value=633000|year=1925|r=-3}}) Letter to Commission Urges That Company Be Compelled to Buy New Cars.|date=February 17, 1925|work=The New York Times|access-date=May 4, 2017|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The NYCBOT received bids for the project on February 25, 1926.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48193500/the-brooklyn-citizen/|title=Board Receives Platform Bids For B.M.T. Lines. Six Companies Submit Prices for Extending Subway Stations|date=1926-02-26|work=The Brooklyn Citizen|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=5}}</ref> The contract was awarded to Corson Construction Company for $345,021 ({{inflation|fmt=eq|index=US|value=345021|year=1926|r=-3}}).<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48193684/the-standard-union/|title=Brooklyn Wins Big Improvement Fund|date=1926-03-18|work=Brooklyn Standard Union|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=20}}</ref>\n\n==== 1950s and 1960s ====\nIn July 1959, the [[New York City Transit Authority]] (NYCTA) announced that it would install [[fluorescent lighting]] at the Prospect Avenue station and five other stations along Fourth Avenue for between $175,000 and $200,000. Bids on the project were to be advertised on August 7, 1959 and completed by fall 1960.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/47783394/bay-ridge-home-reporter/|title=Our Subway Stations To Be Brighter|date=1959-07-10|work=Bay Ridge Home Reporter|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=2}}</ref>\n\nIn the 1960s, the [[New York City Transit Authority]] (NYCTA) started a project to lengthen station platforms on its lines in Southern Brooklyn to {{Convert|615|feet|meters|abbr=}} to accommodate 10-car trains.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=New York City Transit Authority Annual Report For The Year June 30, 1960|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=1960|isbn=|location=|pages=16\u201317}}</ref> On July 14, 1967, the NYCTA awarded a contract to conduct test borings at eleven stations on the Fourth Avenue Line, including Prospect Avenue, to W. M. Walsh Corporation for $6,585 ({{inflation|fmt=eq|index=US|value=6585|year=1967}}) in preparation of the construction of platform extensions.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=HJTVAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22Union+Street,+9th+Street,%22&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=borings+JULY|title=Minutes and Proceedings|date=1967|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=379\u2013380|language=en}}</ref> The NYCTA issued an invitation for bids on the project to extend the platforms at stations along the Fourth Avenue Line between [[Pacific Street station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|Pacific Street]] and [[36th Street station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|36th Street]], including those at Prospect Avenue, on March 28, 1969.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=-HNIAQAAIAAJ&dq=Group+XXX%E2%80%94Broadway-Fourth+Avenue+Line:+pacific+Street,+Union+Street,+9th+Street&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Group+XXX|title=Engineering News-record|date=1969|publisher=McGraw-Hill|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=63|language=en}}</ref> Funding for the renovation projects came out of the NYCTA's 1969\u20131970 Capital Budget, costing $8,177,890 in total.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=c-gxGpL_JNQC&dq=%22Pacific+Street+to+36th+Street+stations%22&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=10-car|title=Proceedings of the New York City Transit Authority Relating to Matters Other Than Operation|date=1969|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=280, 435, 487|language=en}}</ref>\n\nAs part of the renovation project, the station's platforms were extended,<ref name=\":1\" /> and the station's elaborate mosaic tile walls were covered over with {{convert|8|by|16|in|cm|adj=on}} white cinderblock tiles. The latter change, which was also made to 15 other stations on the [[BMT Broadway Line|BMT Broadway]] and Fourth Avenue Lines, was criticized for being dehumanizing. The NYCTA spokesman stated that the old tiles were in poor condition and that the change was made to improve the appearance of stations and provide uniformity. Furthermore, it did not consider the old mosaics to have \"any great artistic merit\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Burks|first=Edward C.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1970/02/21/archives/subways-colored-tile-gets-cover-up-job.html|title=Subways' Colored Tile Gets Cover\u2010Up Job|date=1970-02-21|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-07|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==== 2017 ====\nUnder the [[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]'s 2015\u20142019 Capital Program, the station, along with thirty other New York City Subway stations, were scheduled to undergo a complete overhaul as part of the [[Enhanced Station Initiative]]. Updates were to include cellular service, Wi-Fi, USB charging stations, interactive service advisories and maps.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gothamist.com/2016/01/08/subway_facelift_shutdown.php|title=MTA Will Completely Close 30 Subway Stations For Months-Long \"Revamp\"|date=January 8, 2016|publisher=Gothamist|accessdate=July 18, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160801200338/http://gothamist.com/2016/01/08/subway_facelift_shutdown.php|archivedate=August 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.governor.ny.gov/sites/governor.ny.gov/files/atoms/files/MTAStations.pdf|title=MTAStations|last=|first=|date=|website=governor.ny.gov|publisher=Government of the State of New York|access-date=July 18, 2016}}</ref> From January to May 2016, [[Grimshaw Architects]] worked on a design for the station's renovation, with [[Arup Group]] acting as a consultant.<ref name=\":0\" /> The award for Package 1 of the renovations, which covers renovations at the Prospect Avenue, [[53rd Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|53rd Street]], and [[Bay Ridge Avenue (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|Bay Ridge Avenue]] stations on the BMT Fourth Avenue Line, was awarded on November 30, 2016.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/mta/news/books/pdf/161114_1345_CPOC.pdf|title=Capital Program Oversight Committee Meeting|last=|first=|date=November 2016|website=mta.info|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|access-date=November 27, 2016}}</ref> The station closed on June 5, 2017 for these renovations,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.brooklynpaper.com/stories/40/3/br-no-shuttle-buses-at-_bay-ridge-avenue-2017-01-20-bk.html|title=Shuttle scuttle: Riders demand extra buses during three subway stations\u2019 closure|last=Spivack|first=Caroline|date=January 16, 2017|work=|newspaper=Brooklyn Paper|access-date=January 27, 2017|language=en|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ny.curbed.com/2017/3/22/15028712/mta-subway-station-closures-renovations|title=MTA will close these Brooklyn subway stops to facilitate upgrades|date=March 22, 2017|website=Curbed NY|access-date=March 24, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mta.info/press-release/nyc-transit/prospect-av-r-station-close-major-renovation|title=Prospect Av R Station to Close for Major Renovation|last=|first=|date=May 25, 2017|website=www.mta.info|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|access-date=May 26, 2017}}</ref> and reopened on November 2, 2017, a month ahead of schedule.<ref>{{cite web |last=Barone |first=Vincent | title=Prospect Avenue subway station reopens with modern amenities | website=am New York | date=November 2, 2017 | url=https://www.amny.com/transit/prospect-avenue-subway-station-1.14729272 | access-date=November 3, 2017}}</ref> Citnalta-Forte Joint Venture was selected to renovate the three stations under a $72&nbsp;million [[design\u2013build]] contract, the first such contract in the subway system's history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mta.info/news-nyct-subways/2017/03/22/three-brooklyn-r-stations-are-first-major-subway-station-modernization|title=Three Brooklyn R Stations are First in Major Subway Station Modernization Project|last=|first=|date=March 22, 2017|website=|publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|access-date=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Station layout==\n{{stack|float=right|\n{{NYCS 4-tracked local station\n|1=Ninth Street\n|l1=9 St\n|2=25th Street\n|l2=25 St\n|code=BMT Fourth Avenue Line\n|color=yellow\n|textcolor=black\n|deg=315\n}}\n}}\n{{NYCS Platform Layout IND Fulton Street Line}}\n[[File:NYCT_8787_(38121751271).jpg|right|thumb|250px|Entrance to the southbound platform on the west side of Fourth Avenue]]\n\nThis underground station is a local station with four tracks and two [[side platform]]s.<ref name=\"tracks2\">{{NYCS const|trackref|trackbook}}</ref> The R stops here at all times;<ref name=\"ttr\">{{NYCS const|timetable|r}}</ref> some rush-hour W trains stop here in the peak direction;<ref name=\"ttw\">{{NYCS const|timetable|w}}</ref> and the D and N stop here during late nights, but use the center express tracks to bypass the station during daytime hours.<ref name=\"ttd\">{{NYCS const|timetable|d}}</ref><ref name=\"ttn\">{{NYCS const|timetable|n}}</ref> The station has a full curtain wall separating the local and express tracks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm18.jpg|title=The low ceiling of the extension at the northern end of the Bay Ridge-bound platform|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=October 1, 2012|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe platforms have no columns except on the north ends, where the platforms were extended in 1970. These I-beam columns are cream colored. The ceiling in this area is lower.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm18.jpg|title=The low ceiling of the extension at the northern end of the Bay Ridge-bound platform|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=October 1, 2012|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nPrior to the station's 1970 renovation, it was finished all in white and marble tile, and it had its own color scheme to allow regular passengers to identify the station based only on the color of the marble trimmings.<ref name=\":10\" /> Since that renovation, the station walls have consisted of white cinderblock tiles, except for small recesses in the walls, which contain blue-painted cinderblock tiles. The blue cinderblock field contains the station-name signs and white text pointing to the exits. During the 2017 renovation, the cinder block tiles installed in the 1970s were restored, and new black floor tiles and yellow platform treads were installed. The blue cinder block recessions installed in the 1970s were covered with small black mosaic tiles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/mtaphotos/38090305082/in/album-72157665791153429/|title=Reopening of the Prospect Av R Station|last=Cashin|first=Patrick|date=November 2, 2017|website=Flickr|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe 2017 artwork at this station consists of mosaics by [[Monika Bravo]].<ref>{{cite web | last=Plitt | first=Amy | title=Brooklyn\u2019s Prospect Ave subway station reopens after six-month revamp | website=Curbed NY | date=November 3, 2017 | url=https://ny.curbed.com/2017/11/3/16601592/mta-nyc-subway-brooklyn-prospect-avenue | access-date=November 4, 2017}}</ref> They signify local landmarks such as the [[Brooklyn Army Terminal]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.brooklynpaper.com/stories/40/45/dtg-prospect-avenue-station-reopens-2017-11-10-bk.html|title=Back on tracks: Refurbished Prospect Avenue station reopens, delighting local straphangers|last=Mixson|first=Colin|date=November 3, 2017|work=Brooklyn Paper|access-date=November 4, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Exits===\nThe station's only [[fare control]]s are platform-level near the center.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm20.jpg|title=Approaching the turnstiles to leave the station from the Bay Ridge-bound platform, the waiting area doesn't allow the token clerk to provide a mindful eye anymore, the only token clerk is now on the Manhattan-bound platform|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=October 1, 2012|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> Until the 2017 renovations,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/mtaphotos/38067569996/in/album-72157665791153429/|title=Prospect Av Station Reopens|last=Hermann|first=Marc A.|date=November 2, 2017|website=Flickr|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> they had their original trim line, colored brown with \"P\" at regular intervals, a bank of turnstiles, and token booth.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm8.jpg|title=Looking through the fence to the area outside of fare control at a P in the station's trim at Prospect Avenue.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=June 5, 2009|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> The Manhattan-bound side has two street stairs to the east sidewalk of Fourth Avenue near the [[Prospect Expressway]], while the Bay Ridge-bound side has one to the southwest corner of Prospect Avenue and Fourth Avenue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm22.jpg|title=The one streetstair from the Bay Ridge-bound platform|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=October 1, 2012|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=MTA-ParkSlopeMap-2015>{{cite web|title=MTA Neighborhood Maps: Park Slope|url=http://web.mta.info/maps/neighborhoods/bkn/B3_Park_Slope_2015.pdf|website=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority|mta.info]]|publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|accessdate=August 2, 2015|date=2015}}</ref> There are no crossovers or crossunders to allow free transfer between directions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm15.jpg|title=The other entrance the Manhattan-bound platform at Prospect Av, with the Expressway as the backdrop.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=June 29, 2009|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm13.jpg|title=Looking out from the Prospect Expressway's overpass at the single staircase down to the Bensonhurst & Bay Ridge side at Prospect Ave.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=June 29, 2009|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear|left}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Prospect Avenue (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)}}\n* {{NYCS ref|http://www.nycsubway.org/perl/stations?216:2385|BMT 4th Avenue|Prospect Avenue}}\n* The Subway Nut \u2014 [http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/index.php Prospect Avenue Pictures]\n* [https://maps.google.com/?ll=40.665291,-73.992866&spn=0.005249,0.009645&layer=c&cbll=40.665382,-73.992782&panoid=IPQM7B22_P6iKJC8_p2EDA&cbp=12,190.39,,0,-0.2&t=m&z=17 Entrance beneath Prospect Expressway from Google Maps Street View]\n* [https://www.google.com/maps/@40.6654329,-73.9929524,3a,75y,91.16h,87.82t/data=!3m7!1e1!3m5!1s-Vj_worse-4E%2FWG3GyGUO3TI%2FAAAAAAAAYT0%2F9PX3dKFqNLoZLqVV-laK54NkgyILQGTzQCLIB!2e4!6s%2F%2Flh5.googleusercontent.com%2F-Vj_worse-4E%2FWG3GyGUO3TI%2FAAAAAAAAYT0%2F9PX3dKFqNLoZLqVV-laK54NkgyILQGTzQCLIB%2Fw203-h100-p-k-no%2F!7i7168!8i3584!4m3!8m2!3m1!1e1 Platform from Google Maps Street View] (Pre-2017 Overhaul)\n* [https://www.google.com/maps/@40.6652031,-73.992897,3a,75y,71h,90t/data=!3m8!1e1!3m6!1sAF1QipONFTnr5AjWY1_LqabVYUVOJQDMmmA_FjqmDjXw!2e10!3e11!6shttps:%2F%2Flh5.googleusercontent.com%2Fp%2FAF1QipONFTnr5AjWY1_LqabVYUVOJQDMmmA_FjqmDjXw%3Dw234-h106-k-no-pi-0-ya289-ro-0-fo100!7i8704!8i4352 Platform from Google Maps Street View] (Post-2017 Overhaul)  \n* [https://www.google.com/maps/@40.660099,-73.9983749,3a,75y,209h,90t/data=!3m7!1e1!3m5!1sAF1QipMM0mmQwvOUiCfRvy6ODDiVmkQg-8-J2exV2iwm!2e10!6shttps:%2F%2Flh5.googleusercontent.com%2Fp%2FAF1QipMM0mmQwvOUiCfRvy6ODDiVmkQg-8-J2exV2iwm%3Dw203-h100-p-k-no!7i8704!8i4352 Platform Artwork from Google Maps Street View] (Post-2017 Overhaul)  \n{{NYCS stations navbox by service|lr=y}}\n{{NYCS stations navbox by line|4ave=yes}}\n\n[[Category:BMT Fourth Avenue Line stations]]\n[[Category:New York City Subway stations in Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:New York City Subway stations located underground]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in the United States opened in 1915]]\n[[Category:1915 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Park Slope]]\n[[Category:South Brooklyn]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{distinguish|Prospect Avenue (IRT White Plains Road Line)}}\n{{Short description|New York City Subway station in Brooklyn}}\n{{Infobox NYCS\n| name = Prospect Avenue\n| font_color = black\n| font_color_2 = white\n| bg_color = #FFC800\n| bg_color_2 = #874F17\n| image = File:NYCT 8692 (38090305082).jpg\n| image_caption =Southbound platform\n| address = Prospect Avenue &amp; Fourth Avenue<br>Brooklyn, NY 11215<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.nyc.gov/assets/doh/downloads/pdf/epi/Brooklyn|title=Borough of Brooklyn, New York City|publisher=[[Government of New York City]]|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| borough = [[Brooklyn]]\n| locale = [[Gowanus, Brooklyn|Gowanus]], [[Greenwood Heights, Brooklyn|Greenwood Heights]], [[Park Slope]], [[South Park Slope]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|40.666789|N|73.994079|W|display=inline,title}}\n| lat_dir = N\n| lon_dir = W\n| division = BMT\n| line = [[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]]\n| service = Fourth center local\n| service_header = Fourth center local header\n| connection = {{Bus icon}} '''[[NYCT Bus]]''': {{NYC bus link|B37}} <small>(on [[Third Avenue (Brooklyn)|Third Avenue]])</small>; {{NYC bus link|B63}} <small>(on Fifth Avenue)</small><ref>{{cite NYC bus map|B}}</ref>\n| code = 030\n| platforms = 2 [[side platform]]s\n| tracks = 4\n| structure = Underground\n| wifi = yes\n| open_date = {{start date and age|June 22, 1915}}<ref name=\"Station Opening\" />\n| close_date = {{start date and age|2017|6|5}} (reconstruction)\n| rebuilt = {{start date and age|2017|11|2}}\n| passengers = 1,638,002<ref name=\"ridership\">{{NYCS const|riderref}}</ref>\n| pass_year = 2018\n| pass_percent = 70.3\n| rank = 275<ref name=\"ridership\"/>\n| next_north = {{NYCS next | station=Ninth Street | line=BMT Fourth Avenue Line | service= Fourth center local}}\n| next_south = {{NYCS next | station=25th Street | line=BMT Fourth Avenue Line | service= Fourth center local}}\n| legend = {{NYCS infobox legend|allexceptnights}}{{NYCS infobox legend|nightsonly}}{{NYCS infobox legend|rushonly}}{{NYCS infobox legend|rushpeak}}\n}}\n\n'''Prospect Avenue''' is a local [[New York City Subway]] [[metro station|station]] on the [[BMT Fourth Avenue Line]] in [[Brooklyn]]. It is located at Prospect Avenue and Fourth Avenue near the convergence of the [[Gowanus, Brooklyn|Gowanus]], [[Greenwood Heights, Brooklyn|Greenwood Heights]], [[Park Slope]], and [[South Park Slope]] neighborhoods. It is served by the [[R (New York City Subway service)|R]] train at all times. The [[D (New York City Subway service)|D]] and [[N (New York City Subway service)|N]] trains also stop here during late nights, and some rush-hour [[W (New York City Subway service)|W]] trains stop here in the peak direction.\n\nThe Prospect Avenue station was constructed as part of the Fourth Avenue Line, which was approved in 1905. Construction on the segment of the line that includes Prospect Avenue started on December 20, 1909, and was completed in May 1912. The station opened on June 22, 1915 as part of the initial portion of the BMT Fourth Avenue Line to [[59th Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|59th Street]]. The station's platforms were lengthened in 1925, and again in 1970. The station was also renovated in 1970 and 2017.\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Prospect Av station before renewal (38060731396).jpg|thumb|left|The station prior to renovation]]\n\n=== Construction ===\nThe Prospect Avenue station was constructed as part of the Fourth Avenue Line, the plan for which was initially adopted on June 1, 1905.<ref name=\":123\">{{Cite journal|last=Rogoff|first=David|date=May 1961|title=The Fourth Ave. Subway|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzKvSWhrQBW4d3pvOGZaSERiZEhpQ24xT19DTktkQUVlLW5j/view|journal=New York Division Bulletin|publisher=Electric Railroaders' Association|volume=|pages=2\u201310|access-date=May 8, 2017|via=}}</ref> The Rapid Transit Commission was succeeded on July 1, 1907, by the [[New York Public Service Commission|New York State Public Service Commission]] (PSC), which approved the plan for the line in late 1907.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/?id=XoxBAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA18&dq=4th+Avenue+line#v=onepage&q=4th%20Avenue%20line&f=false|page=18|title=Fourth Avenue Subway, Brooklyn's New Transportation Line: A Part of the Dual System of Rapid Transit of the City of New York|date=June 19, 1915|publisher=Public Service Commission|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":11\">{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48901678/|title=Fourth Avenue Subway Is Sent To A Committee|date=March 20, 1908|work=The Brooklyn Daily Eagle|access-date=May 4, 2017|pages=1\u20132|language=en}}</ref> The contract for the section of the line that included the Prospect Avenue station, Route 11A3, which extended from 10th Street to 27th Street, was awarded on May 22, 1908, and approved by the [[New York City Board of Estimate]] on October 29, 1909.<ref name=\":10\" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://bklyn.newspapers.com/image/53922207/|title=Fourth Avenue Subway To Be Political Issue|date=December 11, 1908|work=The Brooklyn Daily Eagle|access-date=May 4, 2017|page=1|language=en}}</ref> Construction on the segment started on December 20, 1909, and was completed in May 1912.<ref name=\":12\">{{Cite journal|last=Rogoff|first=David|date=May 1961|title=The Fourth Ave. Subway|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzKvSWhrQBW4d3pvOGZaSERiZEhpQ24xT19DTktkQUVlLW5j/view|journal=New York Division Bulletin|publisher=Electric Railroaders' Association|volume=|pages=2\u201310|access-date=May 8, 2017|via=}}</ref>\n\nAs part of negotiations between New York City, the [[Brooklyn Rapid Transit Company]] (BRT) and the [[Interborough Rapid Transit Company]] for the expansion of the city's transit network, the line was leased to a subsidiary of the BRT. The agreement, known as Contract 4 of the [[Dual Contracts]], was signed on March 19, 1913.<ref name=\":10\" /> Prospect Avenue opened on June 22, 1915 as part of the initial portion of the Fourth Avenue Line to [[59th Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|59th Street]].<ref name=\"Station Opening\">{{cite web|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48814840/|title=Through Tube to Coney, 48 Minutes: First Train on Fourth Avenue Route Beats West End Line Eleven Minutes|date=June 22, 1915|publisher=[[Brooklyn Daily Eagle]]|accessdate=June 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Renovations ===\n\n==== 1920s ====\nOn June 27, 1922, the New York State Transit Commission directed its engineers to prepare plans to lengthen the platforms at 23 stations on the lines of the [[Brooklyn\u2013Manhattan Transit Corporation]] (BMT), the successor to the BRT, to accommodate eight-car trains. As part of the project, Prospect Avenue's platforms would have been lengthened from {{Convert|435|feet|meters}} to {{Convert|530|feet|meters}}.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Legislature|first=New York (State)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-ugaAQAAIAAJ&pg=RA3-PA100&dq=%22union+street%22+LENGTHENING&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj8_PLm7tboAhXBhOAKHVx0AzwQ6AEwA3oECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=%22union%20street%22%20LENGTHENING&f=false|title=Second Annual Report of the Transit Commission (For the Calendar Year 1922)|date=1923|publisher=New York State Transit Commission|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=100|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u5kT80_w6rYC&pg=PA1277&dq=%22union+street%22+%22530+feet%22&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjngqLU7dboAhVLTt8KHapMD8IQ6AEwCHoECAkQAg#v=onepage&q=%22union%20street%22%20%22530%20feet%22&f=false|title=Proceedings of the Transit Commission, State of New York Volume III From January 1 to December 31, 1923|date=1923|publisher=New York State Transit Commission|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=1277|language=en}}</ref> On February 16, 1925, the [[New York City Board of Transportation]] (NYCBOT) directed its engineers to prepare plans to lengthen the platforms at this and eleven other stations along the Fourth Avenue Line. It estimated the project's cost to be $633,000. The BMT had been ordered by the Transit Commission to lengthen these platforms since September 1923.<ref name=\":02\">{{Cite news|last=|first=|url-access=subscription|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1925/02/17/archives/12-bm-t-stations-to-be-lengthehed-transportation-board-orders.html|title=12 B-M. T. Stations To Be Lengthened; Transportation Board Orders Engineers to Prepare Contracts for Brooklyn Work. Cost Put At $633,000 Letter to Commission Urges That Company Be Compelled to Buy New Cars.|date=February 17, 1925|work=The New York Times|access-date=May 4, 2017|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The NYCBOT received bids for the project on February 25, 1926.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48193500/the-brooklyn-citizen/|title=Board Receives Platform Bids For B.M.T. Lines. Six Companies Submit Prices for Extending Subway Stations|date=1926-02-26|work=The Brooklyn Citizen|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=5}}</ref> The contract was awarded to Corson Construction Company for $345,021.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48193684/the-standard-union/|title=Brooklyn Wins Big Improvement Fund|date=1926-03-18|work=Brooklyn Standard Union|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=20}}</ref>\n\n==== 1950s and 1960s ====\nIn July 1959, the [[New York City Transit Authority]] (NYCTA) announced that it would install [[fluorescent lighting]] at the Prospect Avenue station and five other stations along Fourth Avenue for between $175,000 and $200,000. Bids on the project were to be advertised on August 7, 1959 and completed by fall 1960.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/47783394/bay-ridge-home-reporter/|title=Our Subway Stations To Be Brighter|date=1959-07-10|work=Bay Ridge Home Reporter|access-date=2020-04-07|url-status=live|pages=2}}</ref> \n\nIn the 1960s, the [[New York City Transit Authority]] (NYCTA) started a project to lengthen station platforms on its lines in Southern Brooklyn to {{Convert|615|feet|meters|abbr=}} to accommodate 10-car trains.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=New York City Transit Authority Annual Report For The Year June 30, 1960|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=1960|isbn=|location=|pages=16-17}}</ref> On July 14, 1967, the NYCTA awarded a contract to conduct test borings at eleven stations on the Fourth Avenue Line, including Prospect Avenue, to W. M. Walsh Corporation for $6,585 in preparation of the construction of platform extensions.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=HJTVAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22Union+Street,+9th+Street,%22&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=borings+JULY|title=Minutes and Proceedings|date=1967|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=379-380|language=en}}</ref> The NYCTA issued an invitation for bids on the project to extend the platforms at stations along the Fourth Avenue Line between [[Pacific Street station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|Pacific Street]] and [[36th Street station (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|36th Street]], including those at Prospect Avenue, on March 28, 1969.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=-HNIAQAAIAAJ&dq=Group+XXX%E2%80%94Broadway-Fourth+Avenue+Line:+pacific+Street,+Union+Street,+9th+Street&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Group+XXX|title=Engineering News-record|date=1969|publisher=McGraw-Hill|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=63|language=en}}</ref> Funding for the renovation projects came out of the NYCTA's 1969\u20131970 Capital Budget, costing $8,177,890 in total.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=c-gxGpL_JNQC&dq=%22Pacific+Street+to+36th+Street+stations%22&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=10-car|title=Proceedings of the New York City Transit Authority Relating to Matters Other Than Operation|date=1969|publisher=New York City Transit Authority|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=280, 435, 487|language=en}}</ref>\n\nAs part of the renovation project, the station's platforms were extended,<ref name=\":1\" /> and the station's elaborate mosaic tile walls were covered over with {{convert|8|by|16|in|cm|adj=on}} white cinderblock tiles. The latter change, which was also made to 15 other stations on the [[BMT Broadway Line|BMT Broadway]] and Fourth Avenue Lines, was criticized for being dehumanizing. The NYCTA spokesman stated that the old tiles were in poor condition and that the change was made to improve the appearance of stations and provide uniformity. Furthermore, it did not consider the old mosaics to have \"any great artistic merit\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Burks|first=Edward C.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1970/02/21/archives/subways-colored-tile-gets-cover-up-job.html|title=Subways' Colored Tile Gets Cover\u2010Up Job|date=1970-02-21|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-07|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==== 2017 ====\nUnder the [[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]'s 2015\u20142019 Capital Program, the station, along with thirty other New York City Subway stations, were scheduled to undergo a complete overhaul as part of the [[Enhanced Station Initiative]]. Updates were to include cellular service, Wi-Fi, USB charging stations, interactive service advisories and maps.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gothamist.com/2016/01/08/subway_facelift_shutdown.php|title=MTA Will Completely Close 30 Subway Stations For Months-Long \"Revamp\"|date=January 8, 2016|publisher=Gothamist|accessdate=July 18, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160801200338/http://gothamist.com/2016/01/08/subway_facelift_shutdown.php|archivedate=August 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.governor.ny.gov/sites/governor.ny.gov/files/atoms/files/MTAStations.pdf|title=MTAStations|last=|first=|date=|website=governor.ny.gov|publisher=Government of the State of New York|access-date=July 18, 2016}}</ref> From January to May 2016, [[Grimshaw Architects]] worked on a design for the station's renovation, with [[Arup Group]] acting as a consultant.<ref name=\":0\" /> The award for Package 1 of the renovations, which covers renovations at the Prospect Avenue, [[53rd Street (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|53rd Street]], and [[Bay Ridge Avenue (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)|Bay Ridge Avenue]] stations on the BMT Fourth Avenue Line, was awarded on November 30, 2016.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/mta/news/books/pdf/161114_1345_CPOC.pdf|title=Capital Program Oversight Committee Meeting|last=|first=|date=November 2016|website=mta.info|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|access-date=November 27, 2016}}</ref> The station closed on June 5, 2017 for these renovations,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.brooklynpaper.com/stories/40/3/br-no-shuttle-buses-at-_bay-ridge-avenue-2017-01-20-bk.html|title=Shuttle scuttle: Riders demand extra buses during three subway stations\u2019 closure|last=Spivack|first=Caroline|date=January 16, 2017|work=|newspaper=Brooklyn Paper|access-date=January 27, 2017|language=en|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ny.curbed.com/2017/3/22/15028712/mta-subway-station-closures-renovations|title=MTA will close these Brooklyn subway stops to facilitate upgrades|date=March 22, 2017|website=Curbed NY|access-date=March 24, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mta.info/press-release/nyc-transit/prospect-av-r-station-close-major-renovation|title=Prospect Av R Station to Close for Major Renovation|last=|first=|date=May 25, 2017|website=www.mta.info|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|access-date=May 26, 2017}}</ref> and reopened on November 2, 2017, a month ahead of schedule.<ref>{{cite web |last=Barone |first=Vincent | title=Prospect Avenue subway station reopens with modern amenities | website=am New York | date=November 2, 2017 | url=https://www.amny.com/transit/prospect-avenue-subway-station-1.14729272 | access-date=November 3, 2017}}</ref> Citnalta-Forte Joint Venture was selected to renovate the three stations under a $72 million [[design\u2013build]] contract, the first such contract in the subway system's history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mta.info/news-nyct-subways/2017/03/22/three-brooklyn-r-stations-are-first-major-subway-station-modernization|title=Three Brooklyn R Stations are First in Major Subway Station Modernization Project|last=|first=|date=March 22, 2017|website=|publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|access-date=August 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Station layout==\n{{stack|float=right|\n{{NYCS 4-tracked local station\n|1=Ninth Street\n|l1=9 St\n|2=25th Street\n|l2=25 St\n|code=BMT Fourth Avenue Line\n|color=yellow\n|textcolor=black\n|deg=315\n}}\n}}\n{{NYCS Platform Layout IND Fulton Street Line}}\n[[File:NYCT_8787_(38121751271).jpg|right|thumb|250px|Entrance to the southbound platform on the west side of Fourth Avenue]]\n\nThis underground station is a local station with four tracks and two [[side platform]]s.<ref name=\"tracks2\">{{NYCS const|trackref|trackbook}}</ref> The R stops here at all times;<ref name=\"ttr\">{{NYCS const|timetable|r}}</ref> some rush-hour W trains stop here in the peak direction;<ref name=\"ttw\">{{NYCS const|timetable|w}}</ref> and the D and N stop here during late nights, but use the center express tracks to bypass the station during daytime hours.<ref name=\"ttd\">{{NYCS const|timetable|d}}</ref><ref name=\"ttn\">{{NYCS const|timetable|n}}</ref> The station has a full curtain wall separating the local and express tracks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm18.jpg|title=The low ceiling of the extension at the northern end of the Bay Ridge-bound platform|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=October 1, 2012|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe platforms have no columns except on the north ends, where the platforms were extended in 1970. These I-beam columns are cream colored. The ceiling in this area is lower.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm18.jpg|title=The low ceiling of the extension at the northern end of the Bay Ridge-bound platform|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=October 1, 2012|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> \n\nPrior to the station's 1970 renovation, it was finished all in white and marble tile, and it had its own color scheme to allow regular passengers to identify the station based only on the color of the marble trimmings.<ref name=\":10\" /> Since that renovation, the station walls have consisted of white cinderblock tiles, except for small recesses in the walls, which contain blue-painted cinderblock tiles. The blue cinderblock field contains the station-name signs and white text pointing to the exits. During the 2017 renovation, the cinder block tiles installed in the 1970s were restored, and new black floor tiles and yellow platform treads were installed. The blue cinder block recessions installed in the 1970s were covered with small black mosaic tiles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/mtaphotos/38090305082/in/album-72157665791153429/|title=Reopening of the Prospect Av R Station|last=Cashin|first=Patrick|date=November 2, 2017|website=Flickr|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe 2017 artwork at this station consists of mosaics by [[Monika Bravo]].<ref>{{cite web | last=Plitt | first=Amy | title=Brooklyn\u2019s Prospect Ave subway station reopens after six-month revamp | website=Curbed NY | date=November 3, 2017 | url=https://ny.curbed.com/2017/11/3/16601592/mta-nyc-subway-brooklyn-prospect-avenue | access-date=November 4, 2017}}</ref> They signify local landmarks such as the [[Brooklyn Army Terminal]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.brooklynpaper.com/stories/40/45/dtg-prospect-avenue-station-reopens-2017-11-10-bk.html|title=Back on tracks: Refurbished Prospect Avenue station reopens, delighting local straphangers|last=Mixson|first=Colin|date=November 3, 2017|work=Brooklyn Paper|access-date=November 4, 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Exits===\nThe station's only [[fare control]]s are platform-level near the center.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm20.jpg|title=Approaching the turnstiles to leave the station from the Bay Ridge-bound platform, the waiting area doesn't allow the token clerk to provide a mindful eye anymore, the only token clerk is now on the Manhattan-bound platform|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=October 1, 2012|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> Until the 2017 renovations,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/mtaphotos/38067569996/in/album-72157665791153429/|title=Prospect Av Station Reopens|last=Hermann|first=Marc A.|date=November 2, 2017|website=Flickr|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> they had their original trim line, colored brown with \"P\" at regular intervals, a bank of turnstiles, and token booth.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm8.jpg|title=Looking through the fence to the area outside of fare control at a P in the station's trim at Prospect Avenue.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=June 5, 2009|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref> The Manhattan-bound side has two street stairs to the east sidewalk of Fourth Avenue near the [[Prospect Expressway]], while the Bay Ridge-bound side has one to the southwest corner of Prospect Avenue and Fourth Avenue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm22.jpg|title=The one streetstair from the Bay Ridge-bound platform|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=October 1, 2012|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=MTA-ParkSlopeMap-2015>{{cite web|title=MTA Neighborhood Maps: Park Slope|url=http://web.mta.info/maps/neighborhoods/bkn/B3_Park_Slope_2015.pdf|website=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority|mta.info]]|publisher=[[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|accessdate=August 2, 2015|date=2015}}</ref> There are no crossovers or crossunders to allow free transfer between directions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm15.jpg|title=The other entrance the Manhattan-bound platform at Prospect Av, with the Expressway as the backdrop.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=June 29, 2009|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/prospectm13.jpg|title=Looking out from the Prospect Expressway's overpass at the single staircase down to the Bensonhurst & Bay Ridge side at Prospect Ave.|last=Cox|first=Jeremiah|date=June 29, 2009|website=subwaynut.com|access-date=December 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear|left}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Prospect Avenue (BMT Fourth Avenue Line)}}\n* {{NYCS ref|http://www.nycsubway.org/perl/stations?216:2385|BMT 4th Avenue|Prospect Avenue}}\n* The Subway Nut \u2014 [http://www.subwaynut.com/bmt/prospectm/index.php Prospect Avenue Pictures]\n* [https://maps.google.com/?ll=40.665291,-73.992866&spn=0.005249,0.009645&layer=c&cbll=40.665382,-73.992782&panoid=IPQM7B22_P6iKJC8_p2EDA&cbp=12,190.39,,0,-0.2&t=m&z=17 Entrance beneath Prospect Expressway from Google Maps Street View]\n* [https://www.google.com/maps/@40.6654329,-73.9929524,3a,75y,91.16h,87.82t/data=!3m7!1e1!3m5!1s-Vj_worse-4E%2FWG3GyGUO3TI%2FAAAAAAAAYT0%2F9PX3dKFqNLoZLqVV-laK54NkgyILQGTzQCLIB!2e4!6s%2F%2Flh5.googleusercontent.com%2F-Vj_worse-4E%2FWG3GyGUO3TI%2FAAAAAAAAYT0%2F9PX3dKFqNLoZLqVV-laK54NkgyILQGTzQCLIB%2Fw203-h100-p-k-no%2F!7i7168!8i3584!4m3!8m2!3m1!1e1 Platform from Google Maps Street View] (Pre-2017 Overhaul)\n* [https://www.google.com/maps/@40.6652031,-73.992897,3a,75y,71h,90t/data=!3m8!1e1!3m6!1sAF1QipONFTnr5AjWY1_LqabVYUVOJQDMmmA_FjqmDjXw!2e10!3e11!6shttps:%2F%2Flh5.googleusercontent.com%2Fp%2FAF1QipONFTnr5AjWY1_LqabVYUVOJQDMmmA_FjqmDjXw%3Dw234-h106-k-no-pi-0-ya289-ro-0-fo100!7i8704!8i4352 Platform from Google Maps Street View] (Post-2017 Overhaul)  \n* [https://www.google.com/maps/@40.660099,-73.9983749,3a,75y,209h,90t/data=!3m7!1e1!3m5!1sAF1QipMM0mmQwvOUiCfRvy6ODDiVmkQg-8-J2exV2iwm!2e10!6shttps:%2F%2Flh5.googleusercontent.com%2Fp%2FAF1QipMM0mmQwvOUiCfRvy6ODDiVmkQg-8-J2exV2iwm%3Dw203-h100-p-k-no!7i8704!8i4352 Platform Artwork from Google Maps Street View] (Post-2017 Overhaul)  \n{{NYCS stations navbox by service|lr=y}}\n{{NYCS stations navbox by line|4ave=yes}}\n\n[[Category:BMT Fourth Avenue Line stations]]\n[[Category:New York City Subway stations in Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:New York City Subway stations located underground