ats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] in yellow, [[Green Party of England and Wales|Greens]] in light green and [[Morley Borough Independents]] in dark green.</small>\n\n| title = Council control\n| posttitle = Council control after election\n| before_election = [[Majority government|Majority administration]]\n| before_party = [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n| after_election = [[Majority government|Majority administration]]\n| after_party = [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2016 Leeds City Council election''' took place on 5 May 2016 to elect members of [[Leeds City Council]] in England.<ref>{{cite web\n |url= http://www.leeds.gov.uk/council/Pages/Leeds-City-Council-election.aspx\n |title= Leeds City Council Election\n |work= Leeds City Council\n |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref>\nThis was on the same day as other [[2016 United Kingdom local elections|local elections]].\n\nAs per the election cycle, one third of the council's seats were up for election. The councillors subsequently elected replaced those elected when their individual seats were previously contested in [[2012 Leeds City Council election|2012]].\n\n{{Election Summary Begin|title = Leeds City Council Election Result 2016<ref name=\"2016results\">{{Cite web |url=https://files.datapress.com/leeds/dataset/election-results-local/Local%20Election.csv |title=Election results - Local 2016 |publisher=[[Leeds City Council]] |accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref>}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |seats      = 21\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = 0\n  |seats %    = 63.6\n  |votes %    = 43.0\n  |votes      = 79,442\n  |plus/minus = +4.4%\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |seats      = 6\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = 0\n  |seats %    = 18.2\n  |votes %    = 23.0\n  |votes      = 42,465\n  |plus/minus = +1.5%\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = United Kingdom Independence Party\n  |seats  