8 Leeds City Council election|2018]]\n| seats_for_election = {{nowrap|One third (33) of 99 seats on [[Leeds City Council]]}}\n| majority_seats     = 50\n| election_date      = 5 May 2016\n| turnout            = 34.7% ({{decrease}}29.39%)\n\n<!-- Labour -->\n| image1 = \n| leader1 = {{nowrap|[[Judith Blake]]}}\n| party1 = Labour Party (UK)\n| leaders_seat1 = [[Middleton Park (ward)|Middleton Park]]\n| last_election1 = 21 seats, 39.8%\n| seats1 = '''21'''\n| seat_change1 = {{steady}}\n| popular_vote1 = '''79,442'''\n| percentage1 = '''43.0%'''\n| swing1 =\n\n<!-- Conservative -->\n| image2 = \n| leader2 = {{nowrap|Andrew Carter}}\n| party2 = Conservative Party (UK)\n| leaders_seat2 = [[Calverley and Farsley (ward)|Calverley & Farsley]]\n| last_election2 = 6 seats, 27.4%\n| seats2 = 6\n| seat_change2 = {{steady}}\n| popular_vote2 = 42,465\n| percentage2 = 23.0%\n| swing2 =\n\n<!-- Liberal Democrat -->\n| image3 = \n| leader3 = {{nowrap|Stewart Golton}}\n| party3 = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n| leaders_seat3 = [[Rothwell (ward)|Rothwell]]\n| last_election3 = 3 seats, 8.4%\n| seats3 = 3\n| seat_change3 = {{steady}}\n| popular_vote3 = 18,525\n| percentage3 = 10.0%\n| swing3 =\n\n| map_image = Leeds Wards 2016.png\n| map_size = 300px\n| map_caption = <small>[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] in red, [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]] in blue, [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] in yellow, [[Green Party of England and Wales|Greens]] in light green and [[Morley Borough Independents]] in dark green.</small>\n\n| title = Council control\n| posttitle = Council control after election\n| before_election = [[Majority government|Majority administration]]\n| before_party = [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n| after_election = [[Majority government|Majority administration]]\n| after_party = [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2016 Leeds City Council election''' took place on 5 May 2016 to elect members of [[Leeds City Council]] in England.<ref>{{cite web\n |url= http://www.leeds.gov.uk/council/Pages/Leeds-City-Council-election.aspx\n |title= Leeds City Council Election\n |work= Leeds City Council\n |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref>\nThis was on the same day as other [[2016 United Kingdom local elections|local elections]].\n\nAs per the election cycle, one third of the council's seats were up for election. The councillors subsequently elected replaced those elected when their individual seats were previously contested in [[2012 Leeds City Council election|2012]].\n\n{{Election Summary Begin|title = Leeds City Council Election Result 2016<ref name=\"2016results\">{{Cite web |url=https://files.datapress.com/leeds/dataset/election-results-local/Local%20Election.csv |title=Election results - Local 2016 |publisher=[[Leeds City Council]] |accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref>}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |seats      = 21\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = 0\n  |seats %    = 63.6\n  |votes %    = 43.0\n  |votes      = 79,442\n  |plus/minus = +4.4%\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |seats      = 6\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = 0\n  |seats %    = 18.2\n  |votes %    = 23.0\n  |votes      = 42,465\n  |plus/minus = +1.5%\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = United Kingdom Independence Party\n  |seats      = 0\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = 0\n  |seats %    = 0\n  |votes %    = 12.5\n  |votes      = 23,166\n  |plus/minus = -4.2%\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n  |seats      = 3\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = 0\n  |seats %    = 9.1\n  |votes %    = 10.0\n  |votes      = 18,525\n  |plus/minus = -0.2%\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Green Party of England and Wales\n  |seats      = 1\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = 0\n  |seats %    = 3.0\n  |votes %    = 7.1\n  |votes      = 13,021\n  |plus/minus =